Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Acolyte_of_the_Lost_Arts:
Aeons before he was recognized as the most dangerous magician alive--an ageless master of the arcane arts--the Invoker endured scholastic life as the adolescent star pupil at an ancient wizard's academy. Even as he excelled at every task set before him, and basked in the praise such aptitude afforded, the young Invoker dreamt of a future in which he answered to no one but himself, where he might finally be free to wield his growing powers however he saw fit.
Now, harnessing dangerous magics purloined from his headmaster's secret archives, young Carl has discovered the means to journey forward into his own timeline. Eager to insert himself prematurely into the moment of his greatest triumph, Carl is determined to prove to the world that aged or not, the illustrious arts of the Invoker can be bested by no one. While he's confident that he's bound for triumphant adventure, had he read the entire description of the spell before casting it, the young magus would know that failure to accomplish his elder self's fated mission will result in each timeline's certain demise.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Adage_of_the_Smoldering_S:

And those of the flesh who entered this domain took great care, for the King was first and foremost a collector, and nothing moved in the Empire of Bone without summoning the gaze of his unblinking eyes.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Auto_Chess_Pass:
This pass activates premium content in the DOTA AUTO CHESS custom game and supports the creators of this custom game.
Owning a DOTA AUTO CHESS Custom Game Pass will Unlock:
● Golden border of your avatar, golden paint of your chat message, golden effect of your damage projectile.
● Daily First Win Bonus (5 bonus candy for your first top 3, and 5 bonus candy for your first top 1)
● Right to vote for the special chess pieces, including new chess pieces and chess pieces need to be rebalanced.
● A Baby Roshan courier as your chess player on your first purchase.
Most importantly, purchasing a premium ticket supports the game and allows us to build content better, faster, more consistently.
100% of the game's content will remain available to free tier players. Premium players just receive these quality of life benefits and support the game's development.
Expires 30 days after purchase.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Belt_of_the_Hazhadal_Mage: After besting the young mages of his order, Nortrom put his newfound skills to use suppressing the godless outlaws of the Hazhadall Barrens, routinely making short work of their vaunted enthrallers.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blessed_Luckvessel: No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. The items in this treasure will not be tradable or marketable until March 1st, 2015.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blessing_of_the_Crested_D: Includes all of the items in the 'Blessing of the Crested Dawn' set for Skywrath Mage plus a loading screen and ability icons.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blessing_of_the_Crested_U: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Blessing of the Crested Umbra' set for Vengeful Spirit plus a loading screen and icons.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blessings_of_Lucentyr_Set: Includes all of the items in the 'Blessings of Lucentyr' set for Luna:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blessings_of_the_Eternal_: Includes all of the items in the 'Blessings of the Eternal Eclipse' set for Luna:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blessings_of_the_Solar_Di: The acolytes of the Solar Goddess said Lina's hair was \"touched by the light\", and so gifted her with trinkets made to reflect the warming love of the sun.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blindfold_from_the_Gloom: Few can predict the price to be paid for piercing the veil.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blink_DotA_League: Amateur League aiming to build the UK DotA2 scene from the trench up!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blistering_Shade: On his return passage through the murky veil, Ostarion was beset by a swirling fire that struggled to drive him back towards the endless abyss. Grasping at the flame with his mailed fist, the Wraith King thrashed and tore against the ethereal force until he found himself returned to the earthly realm.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blistering_Shade_of_the_C: On his return passage through the murky veil, Ostarion was beset by a swirling fire that struggled to drive him back towards the endless abyss. Grasping at the flame with his mailed fist, the Wraith King thrashed and tore against the ethereal force until he found himself returned to the earthly realm.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blood_Covenant_Pack: Pack includes both the main and off-hand Blood Covenant Blades.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blood_Drainer_Hook: A hook designed to pierce foes in multiple areas upon impact and draw blood as Pudge reels in his prey.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blood_In_The_Streets_BITS:
BITS is an 8 team double-elimination Dota 2â¢ tournament.
	$5,000 prize pool (1st $2500, 2nd $1500, 3rd $1000). 
	7 invited teams and 1 team selected through open qualifiers.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blood_Vial:
Auctioned from the estate of a brilliant but failed alchemist, these mystical vials have the power to transform liquid water into nearly any substance. However, a steady hand is required. The next item on the auction block was the seeping corpse of the sneezing thaumaturge himself. Vial art, indeed.

Stand in the river to reveal the vial interface. Pour the contents into the river to transform it for 3 minutes. Each vial can be used once per game.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodfeather_Feast: The strike of Akasha's blade is boon to the unkind wings that eagerly await her torments from aloft.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodfeather_Wings: The ravens who feast upon the corpses of the cursed oft grow vile and monstrous. From horror devoured was woven a span worthy of agony's mistress. Includes ambient particle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodletter: A ceremonial blade, used to prepare sacrifice to the Flayed Ones.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodletter__OffHand: A ceremonial blade, used to prepare sacrifice to the Flayed Ones.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodletters: Pack includes both the main and off-hand Bloodletter.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodmayne_Avenger: Daring a mission to the sacked remnants of his family estate, Banehallow gathered enough scraps of precious metals and keepsakes to meet the enchanter's price and the demands of her ingredient list. When the fires of her forge had cooled and her spells were fully woven, Banehallow knew he'd found the last face his enemies would ever see.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodmist_Belt: With the Army of Red Mist now a bloody heap, the Bloodmist Army rises to fill the void.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodmist_Crescent_Axe: Where the Army of Red Mist trained to aim for the neck, the Bloodmist prefer to aim for the belly.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodmist_Helm: This helm sits heavily on the head to strengthen the neck below.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodmist_Pauldrons: These pauldrons were once owned by a mighty officer of the Bloodmist Army.  Axe is only too pleased to tell the tale of their encounter.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodrage_Axe: On the proving grounds of Omex, the victorious have right to the weapons of any warrior they vanquish.  This Bloodrage Axe was taken by the Bradwarden in remembrance of his 100th victory.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodroot_Guard: Contains the Bloodroot Guard set for Phantom Assassin, Including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodstained_Briches: \"You don't get this good at butchery without spending a bit of time on a farm.\"
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodstone_Blade_Pack: This bundle contains both the main and off-hand Bloodstone Blade.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodstone_of_the_Ancesto: For those who came before and sang the word, gathering friends as they began their crusade, the light of gratitude swirls within the stone.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodstone_of_the_Founder: For those who came before and sang the word, gathering friends as they began their crusade, the light of gratitude swirls within the stone.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodstone_of_the_Precurs: For those who came before and sang the word, gathering friends as they began their crusade, the light of gratitude swirls within the stone.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodwood_Arc: Carved from the corewood of a five-thousand-year-old-tree, this magnificent brings an ancient strength to any battle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloodwood_Reserve: A beautiful quiver of the finest polished bloodwood.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloody_Ripper: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Bloody Ripper' set for Lifestealer plus loading screen and ability icons.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bloom_Harvest: Open to receive a random reward unique to the New Bloom!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blossom_of_the_Merry_Wand: There are many theories amongst the \"mundane\" fae regarding the true nature of Faerie Dragons. Entire careers have been founded, fortunes made, and families embarrassed in pursuit of the subject. And a Revtel party is hardly complete without much pontification on the finer points of the one known as Puck.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blossoming_Harmony: Contains the Blossoming Harmony set for Storm Spirit, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blotto_and_Stick: A former gambler and shyster, the antics of Blotto were once known in every watering hole, gambling den and sleaze pit from here to Slom.  Now on the slow path to reform, he's taken up courier duties to con a bit of extra coin and brought his trusty Stick along for the ride!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blouse_of_Forsaken_Beauty: A soft blouse from the days of her abandoned vanity.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blue_Minnow_Ward_Upgrade: This International 2017 reward enables an upgraded color style to be unlocked for the Shifty Minnow ward in the style menu.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blue_Stone_Shoulder_of_th: Kunkka is no pirate. Still, the stones were just lying there and would have gone to waste had he not seized them. Technically, that might well constitute plundering.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blueheart_Sovereign: Contains the Blueheart Sovereign set for Crystal Maiden, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Blueheart_Tails: The hairstyle worn by Rylai during her lessons atop the great glacier of the north.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bobusangs_Tobacco_Fix: This item comes with a custom particle effect on the pipe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bobusangs_Traveling_Neces: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Bobusang's Traveling Necessities' set for Tusk:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bogduggs_Baldric:
Required Level: 10

Bonus Armor: 10
Stun Duration Reduction: 50%
Move Speed Reduction: 30
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bogduggs_Cudgel:
Required Level: 13

Passive: Smash - MELEE ONLY - All attack speed is halved, but attacks deal splash damage in a 250 area around the target and stun for 1.0 second.

Bonus Strength: 20
Bonus Damage: 20
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bogduggs_Lucky_Femur:
Required Level: 12

Passive: Skillshot - After an ability is cast, it has a 25% chance to be immediately refreshed.

Max Mana Reduction: 200
Intelligence Reduction: 5
Bonus Mana Regen: 10
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bonds_of_Vincere_Set: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Bonds of Vincere' set for Queen of Pain:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bone_Bracer_of_the_Brave: The great beast that gave the bone to make these bracers did not do so willingly, or without struggle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bone_Knife_of_the_First_H:
A kit's first tools must come from the remains of its prey.

This item can be upgraded with the 'Kit of the First Hunt Style Unlock' granted to players who complete at least 40 stars on the Path of the Saboteur.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bonehunter_Belt: The crimson pattern which covers this garment must be regularly restored with fresh blood.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bonehunter_Bracers: To the west lie the drylands, where the Bonehunters stalk.  Their tribute to the Flayed Ones is small, but their ferocity is unmatched.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bonehunter_Skullguard: The beasts that wander the drylands are fierce, but no few are match for the Bonehunters.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bonehunter_Slicer: The Bonehunters adhere to the ways of a time before weapons could be forged from steel.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bonehunter_Slicer__OffHan: The Bonehunters adhere to the ways of a time before weapons could be forged from steel.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bonehunter_Slicers: Pack includes both the main and off-hand Bonehunter Slicer.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bonehunter_Spineguard: The Bonehunters believe that if it is good enough to protect from within, then it must also be good enough to protect from without.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bonehunter_Tuskguard: It is tradition that a Bonehunter adorns himself with the teeth of their fiercest kill.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bones_of_the_Slain_Dragon: Includes all of the items in the 'Bones of the Slain Dragon' set for Dragon Knight:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Boneslayer: When Ostarion came to conquer, this blade was presented as a gift in hope of negotiating a peaceful surrender.  It didn't work.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bonkers_the_Mad: From the treetops, Bonkers watched. He saw the sick and infirm tended to, the malicious cursed, the rituals, the rites, the traditions of a Witch Doctor. Bonkers brought this wild knowledge to his kin, and for doing so was banished, called mad in his tongue. Perhaps he is, but now he knows his true calling.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bonus_Gift: A gift for being awesome! Open it up to receive a prize.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Book_of_the_Infernal_Maw: While some amongst the Ultimyr faculty share concerns regarding the peculiar nature of Chief Curator Lannik's studies, none can deny that under his watch the Academy's archives of arcane knowledge have grown incomparably.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Boots_of_Travel_Shell_Sty: This International 2017 reward enables an upgraded shell to be unlocked for Hermes the Hermit Crab in the style menu.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_BoraDota: 32 teams in Brazil compete for R$600 in this World Cup style format tournament!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_BoraDota_2nd_Edition: The BoraDota 2nd edition Brazilian Cup consists of 64 teams divided into 16 groups competing for a R$2,000 prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_BoraDota_STARS_2: Second BoraDota STARS with the best sixteen teams in South America in a professional tournment.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_BoraDota_Stars: The best teams in South America compete in the BoraDota Stars for a prize pool of R$1,500!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Boredgamercouk_Dota2_One_: One Day EU West Dota 2 Tournament
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Boston_Major_Open_Qualifi: Witness teams from all around the world compete for a place at The Boston Major 2016.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bottom_Watcher: From far below, a dweller of the deeps has been pressed into service at the surface!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bounty_Hunter_Series: The Dota 2 King of the Hill Bounty Hunter Series returns! Two invited teams teams to go head-to-head for a chance to win $1000. Bundle includes Raiq courier!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bounty_Hunter_Series_Tick: The Dota 2 King of the Hill Bounty Hunter Series returns! Two invited teams teams to go head-to-head for a chance to win $1000. This ticket only gives you access to view games in the Bounty Hunter Series.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_Forsaken_Beauty: Twin snakes coil around a bow of wood and stone.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Battleranger:
To some authorities, the line between ranger and ruffian is nearly nonexistent.

This item can be upgraded with the 'Bindings of the Battleranger Style Unlock' granted to players who complete all fifteen Three-Star objectives on the Path of the Spellbinder.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Burning_Decree: The unsleeping huntsman patrols all reaches of The Hoven, one anguished step after another.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Crypt_Guardian: A jagged bow for a burning soul.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Crystal_Caves: Beneath her secret glades, Drow found a passage lit by crystal shards. Following the glittering light to the farthest cavern, she discovered this bow, embedded in the rock as if it had formed there.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Eldwurms_Touch: Includes ability icons and ambient particles.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Frostfangs: A great bow of unknown origins, it was wielded by a snow demon that came to challenge the Drow Ranger. The Demon's skill was found wanting and so Traxex found a new weapon for herself.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Moon_Rider: The power of the lunar lioness purrs  in this bow's enchanted string.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Oyoloe: Once thought to be a mythical beast, the Windranger slew the elusive, green oyoloe, and made a bow from its antlers.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Searing_Soul: A bow brought back from hell itself.   With this weapon, enemies will feel the searing burn of your anger.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Serpent: A grove of ancient and magical trees rises from the tangled heart of the Yama Raskav Jungle, and in its gnarled roots and branches may be found a unique and singularly deadly species of viper. The tribes of Yama Raskav tell of a bow crafted from the wood of this grove, infused with the crystallized venom of the serpents which dwell there. In MedusaÃÂ¢ÃÂÃÂs vengeful hands, the Bow of the Serpent is as swift and deadly as the bite of the viper for which it is named.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Shadowcat: A bow made of skin, fur, ebony and finest pieces of drow metal.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Sun_Vine: This beautiful bow, modeled after the delicate and poisonous sun vine, is even more deadly than its namesake.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bow_of_the_Urushin_Huntsm:
Though known for a violent and capricious temper, the burning bowman is much revered throughout The Hoven.

This item can be upgraded with the 'Urushin Huntsman Style Unlock' granted to players who complete all fifteen Three-Star objectives on the Path of the Rogue.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracelets_of_the_Mothbind: Dim though it has become, the spark of life that holds fast within the heart of the Death Prophet blazes like a signal beacon in the endless darkness of death's abyss, beckoning all manner of feasting shades that long to taste the essence of the animate world.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracer_and_Band: Rare is the ogre that can recall their lineage and lucky is the one with claim to an inheritance.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracer_of_Petaluna: Though the priests of Dezun believe they alone possess the secrets of the ethereal shade, Dazzle's discovery of a race of insects in the lost jungles of Fellstrath capable of suckling energy directly from the Nothl Realm puts that claim to rest. But these creatures are inefficient with their feeding, and each puncture they create allows a bit of influence from the Nothl Realm to bleed into our own.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracer_of_Sir_Davion: Achieving mastery against dragons is impossible without first achieving mastery of the self.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracer_of_the_Burning_Cab: Manipulation of the fire elements requires a delicate touch, lest the sorcerer burn. This pair of bracers have been imbued with minor fire protection enchantments.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracer_of_the_Mage_Slayer: These bracers are made to defend against both swords and sorcery.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracer_of_the_Purist_Cham: Omniknight wears his feelings on his sleeve.  That and a red bracer, which he'll use to smite his enemies in the name of the Omniscience.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracer_of_the_Tahlin_Watc: As he fled his family's slaughter, Riki disguised himself with the armor of his royal watch in order to escape undetected.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_Sleek: The mighty centaur needs no shield when protected by these durable bracers of Omexe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Aeons: Rare even in the realms of Claszureme, the Jewels of Aeons call out to their sister stones.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Aeons_Crimson_:
Rare even in the realms of Claszureme, the Jewels of Aeons call out to their sister stones.
	
	This item was received after witnessing First Blood at The International 2017.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Claszureme: The spikes on the wrist are said to sample the flow of time, while the runes report the findings to the wearer.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Desolate_Conqu: And when the war to end all wars has at last been won, who might remain to celebrate such triumph?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Eldritch_Ice: The charmed ropes that once bound him should have rotted away, but Lich has preserved them as reminder to all that no power in creation can hope to hold him.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Forlorn_Precip: Though he uses his powers in battle unflinchingly and without pause, Ish'Kafel silently yearns to do more than just grasp and manipulate the tendrils of his home. But he must balance his desire to explore the boundaries of his growing influence with the knowledge that such experiments have the potential to destroy his current world, or worse, unleash new terrors upon the land of his own kind.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Forsaken_Beaut: Rubies stud these bracers. Medusa now mocks the beauty which she once held dear.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Fury: These arm  guards protect against the occasional wayward strike of your own flail.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Impending_Tran: The better to kill and cauterize.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Profound_Perfe: While many wizards are jealous of the Invoker's unimaginable power, others are merely jealous of his peerless taste.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Shifting_Forms: In battle, these bracers, ever before Morphling's gaze, remind him of the power of Polymorphia.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_The_Howling_Wo: Bone-carved arm bracers display the ceremonial markings of the Frosted Winds tribe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Unfettered_Mal: Cursed chains forged by the Order of Ra'hul to bind the Night Stalker and bring his ancient power to heel. And bind Balanar they did, until darkness fell.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_Yoskreth: As the Anti-Mage grew in power and prestige, the sovereign of Yoskreth sought his services to topple the fearsome sorcerer Sahsk.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Archivist: For turning pages that wish not to be turned, the Archivist's bracers have been imbued with persuasive powers.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Ardalan_In: While nothing can get Kardel to divulge his means of transit to the Ardalan Nebula, he's more than happy to swap hogwhompers of his adventures there. Keep him in his cups long enough and he might even tell you about the mishap with the princess and the plasma gun.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Awakened: \"May thine Hatred lend thee the strength to shatter the symbol of thine bretheren's demise, for within its remains lies absolute power!\" - Taken from Tael'Am
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Cavern_Lum: In the deepest grip of earth-bound slumber, the being who would become Raigor Stonehoof sensed a multitude of creatures moving at the edges of awareness. They crawled in simple patterns, casting a wakeful luminescence across the walls of stonelocked caves where celestial light would never shine.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Clergy_Asc: A constant reminder of the world he left behind when he struck off on the ascetic's path.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Crystallin: Hard as ice, but strong as steel, these bracers bring a chill to the heart of those who would oppose the maiden of the north.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Dark_Magic: Those who practiced the magical arts are often feared for their power.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Death_Char:
With these bracers, the Spirit Breaker is prepared for any brouhaha.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Drake: Made from the scales of a drake's underbelly, this light and colorful armor is an honor to wear into battle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Ebony_Towe: A lord so adorned will bend the will of many.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Fervent_Co: As the young orphan outgrew adolescence and his mastery of the Turstarkuri scrolls improved, he became eager to test his blades and begin his longed-for crusade to rid the world of magic, ultimately finding first opportunity as a volunteer in the failed defense of Bakhwarren.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Frozen_Fea: A day before the wizard descended into the glacier to begin his hibernation, he offered Crystal Maiden these last, precious gifts: armor and a staff, strong as ice but light as a feather, believed to have once belonged to a winter deity.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Guardian_C:
Though depictions of his body and form differ in the telling, the crackle of the Lightning Revenant's whip is known to all of the blessed few who have returned to life from the Narrow Maze.

This item can be upgraded with the 'Compact of the Guardian Construct Style Unlock' granted to players who complete at least 40 stars on the Path of the Dominator.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Gwimyeon_W: One must never neglect the protection of one's swordhand.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Hazhadal_M: After besting the young mages of his order, Nortrom put his newfound skills to use suppressing the godless outlaws of the Hazhadall Barrens, routinely making short work of their vaunted enthrallers.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Hidden_Tal: These bracers bespeak a man who will brook no magical manipulations!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Hierophant: A Hierophant of the Omniscience must always guard against any threat.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Infernal_M: While some amongst the Ultimyr faculty share concerns regarding the peculiar nature of Chief Curator Lannik's studies, none can deny that under his watch the Academy's archives of arcane knowledge have grown incomparably.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Lost_Star: Created in partnership with Era, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Malicious_: Of flowing dark and unknown aethers come arms of dangerous beauty.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Moon_Rider: The moon shines with mystic lustre on Mirana's forearms...or is it the glow of these polished bracers?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Occultists: Mundane prey attracts the uninspired predator. A distinguished huntsman, on the other hand, seeks a prize not bound by earthly coils.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_One_True_K: In an age lost even to his own memory, Ostarion fed his lust for eternal life not with spectral essence, but a nigh-unending harvest of bone. The walls of his palace were formed of fired bone; the streets paved with bones of every sort of creature and every enemy. And those of the flesh who entered this domain took great care, for the King was first and foremost a collector, and nothing moved in the Empire of Bone without summoning the gaze of his unblinking eyes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Radiant_Cr: They are as pristine as the day they were made, but do not be fooled into thinking they have never seen combat.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Revenant: A new storm is blowing across the battlefield.  Where there is thunder, there is sure to be lighting.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Seasoned_H: Rule number one, always come prepared!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Shifting_S:
The eccentric sorcerer Throsho required unique armaments able to conform to his shapeshifting form.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Silent_Gua: These powerful bracers protect their wearer from the ravages battle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Sunken_Gao: During his long-ago tenure as a Dark Reef Enforcer, Slardar sharpened his spines breaking up escape attempts and quelling constant insurrections.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Sunwarrior: These items were created in partnership with Alliance, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Survivor: As even the faces of favored kin fade from recollection, the unholy forms of the Turstarkuri faithful rise perversely in the mind's eye.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Truebark_A: When Virga Truebark defied the Iron Princeling and sounded the Oakfall Horn, let it be known that Verodicia's favored son stood with her, fighting loyally by her side.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bracers_of_the_Violent_Pr: And here Rigwarl thought \"Crystalback\" had a nice ring to it...
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Braces_of_the_Atniw: A projection of will.  A show of might.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Braided_Tail_of_the_Conqu: A braid woven into the tail of a centaur signifies that battle is soon at hand.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bramblehorn: She who rides a tiger is afraid to dismount.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Brawler_of_the_Glacier_Se: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Brawler of the Glacier Sea' set for Tusk plus a loading screen and ability icons.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Buckle_of_the_Royal_Butch: Though the carnage may go on without end, there are those alive still who can recall when it began. Ah, to be young and in the employ of the bloody King Brandalon once more.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bucktooth_Jerry: A fan of the forest, Jerry fashioned wings and horns from the wood of a sacred Windwood tree. But don't believe the rumors that he made his famous teeth out of the same stuff. They're real. Just ask any nut he's bitten.

This is the second season for the Bulgarian Amateur League. It's an open league with up to 50 teams competing for a prize.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Bulgarian_Dota_2_League: This is the first Bulgarian Dota 2 League which will be held for a whole year and will include many Bulgarian amateur teams.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Burden_of_the_Exiled_Roni: Upon Juggernaut's exile, a mask was bestowed upon his neck that would impart he was indeed a Ronin without a master.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Burden_of_the_Highborn: To restore his family's rule, and to govern those of his kingdom; these are the burdens Riki strives toward.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Burning_Iron: Belching fire and death, he screams across burning skies. Can't stop the rider!

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Butter_Blunder: As busy as they are clumsy, butter blunders are known for their butterfingers.  What they lack in dexterity, they make up for in their earnest desire to please.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Buttercup: The dead of battle can breed many an odd fungus.  That suits Buttercup just fine.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Buttercups_Barding: It is a strange thing that such a calm and gentle creature as Buttercup be made to seem so fierce.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Butterfly_Cup_Ve_Dota2: Ve_Dota2 community presents the Butterfly Cup! Sixteen Latin American teams will fight for more than $300 in prizes and glory.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Button_Down_of_the_Voyage: A dozen brass buttons, and triple-stitched by a master sailmaker, it would take an unusually determined prospective mate to surmount this formidable fortress of...chastity?

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CDEC_Classic: CDEC Classic is the second level league of CDEC, which Pro players and high-skilled amaeur players can join. Each Classic season lasts two weeks. The game mode is mainly CM. Every end of the season, top players will have rewards.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CDEC_Master: CDEC Master is the highest level of CDEC league. Only the Pro players and the high-lever amaeur players can join this league. Each Master season lasts two weeks. The game mode is the Captain Mode. At the end of the season, the top players will have some rewards.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CDEC_Qualifiers: CDEC Qualifiers is one of the division in our CDEC League. The purpose of CDEC Qualifiers is discover more players who are good at DOTA2 Captain Mode. The Qualifiers is suitable for the amateur players. The Qualifiers will be held in the season cycles. Each season included two weeks of regular matches and a week of playoffs. When the season is over, the players in the top of the ranking list will be promoted to higher division which is CDEC Semi-Pro. Each season we will prepare 20000yuan for those players who performed very well in the season.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CDEC_Season_24: CDEC is an in house league consisting if the best Chinese players. Each day the top three games will be broadcasted. There will also be a top 10 players match each week. This is a unique format that allows you to see different pro players working together.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CDEC_Season_24__ADMIN: CDEC is an in house league consisting if the best Chinese players. Each day the top three games will be broadcasted. There will also be a top 10 players match each week. This is a unique format that allows you to see different pro players working together.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CDEC_University_League: CDEC College League, is a single matching to individual points race, the game is through the system matching looking for teammates and opponents, Captain game mode, then and his teammates to win games to increase integration. As long as the registration can be involved in the match at any time after the match, there is no traditional event schedule restrictions.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CEVO_Season_3: CEVO DOTA 2 Season 3 is an event that is open to both amateur and professional players in North America. Teams compete in a 8 week regular season followed by a double-elimination playoff bracket where they compete for cash prizes and a chance to advance to higher skill divisions in future seasons.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CEVO_Season_4: CEVO Season 4 is a North American Pro-Am event where teams compete in an 8-week regular season, followed by playoffs for over $5,000 and the chance to advance to higher skill divisions in future seasons.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CEVO_Season_5: CEVO Season 5 is a North American Pro-Am event where teams compete in an 8-week regular season, followed by Playoffs for over $1,000 and the chance to advance to higher skill divisions in future seasons. Bundle includes the Bladesrunner Juggernaut set and gives $1.25 to the prize pool!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CEVO_Season_5_Ticket: CEVO Season 5 is a North American Pro-Am event where teams compete in an 8-week regular season, followed by Playoffs for over $1,000 and the chance to advance to higher skill divisions in future seasons. This ticket only gives you access to view games from CEVO Season 5.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CEVO_Season_6: CEVO Season 6 is a North American Pro-Am event where teams compete in an 8-week regular season, followed by Playoffs for over $1,000 + bundle sales and the chance to advance to higher skill divisions in future seasons. This bundle grants the Dark Curator of Ultimyr Warlock Set and access to view games from CEVO Season 6.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_CEVO_Season_6_Ticket: CEVO Season 6 is a North American Pro-Am event where teams compete in an 8-week regular season, followed by Playoffs for over $1,000 + bundle sales and the chance to advance to higher skill divisions in future seasons. Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Call_of_the_Bladeform_Leg:
The Juggernaut now speaks with the power of an ancient lineage of revered warriors. Connected once again to the land of the living, these progenitors of the Isle of Masks shall not fall silent again.

This voice pack is available to owners of the Bladeform Legacy Arcana for Juggernaut, and can be equipped to replace Juggernaut's default voice with an exclusive Arcana version.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Call_of_the_Dendrochron: This item changes the appearance of the treant warriors summoned by Nature's Call. Even the dreaded axe cannot hold their kind in check.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cannon_of_the_Occultists_:
Mundane prey attracts the uninspired predator. A distinguished huntsman, on the other hand, seeks a prize not bound by earthly coils.

Includes custom muzzle flash.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cannonade:
Within an admiral's hand Cannonade shines brightly, pointing the way for the blast to come.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Canser_Cup: The fifth season  of \"KUBOK RAKOV\"  will include 64 teams and pass through a system of exciting playoffs.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cap_of_the_Exact_Marksman: Created in partnership with YYF, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cap_of_the_Fungal_Lord: Infused with the essence of the Father Mushroom.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cap_of_the_Smoldering_Sag: In life, the warrior-poet's later-day accomplishments were even more impressive than those of his youth, as the wisdom of his years finally grew to match the purity of his martial arts.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_Arcane_Artistry: An archmagister must be the greatest at all things magical: spell-casting, scroll-reading, and costume-wearing.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_Thunderwraths_Cal: Only those who are called in service to the Omniscient can wear a cape such as this.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_Verdant_Dreaming: Wrapped in the power of the ancient woods.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Blackguard_Ma: In the early days following his escape from academia, long before he assumed the title of Invoker, the young magus sought to test his growing skill by any means attainable. Like many other young talents burning for a taste of adventure, it was not long before he answered the call to war.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Burning_Cabal: The invokers of the Burning Cabal favor Exort over all other disciplines.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Crystalline_Q: Nights are cold in the contested lands, but for some, not cold enough.  This frost-charmed cape keeps cold what the sun would warm.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Dark_Magic: To the Invoker, those without the gifts of magic are insects to be ignored or destroyed.  For at time, his ferocity was such that the magical arts were treated with superstition and fear by all.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Drake: A long cape designed in honor of all drakes who have died in battle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Dreadborn_Reg: In the eyes of King Ostarion, the lives of his champions lost fighting to fuel the Wraith-Night rituals were merely his due tribute.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_First_Dawn: All who see him shall know.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Flameguard: The Flameguard wear capes as blue as the Holy Flame they are sworn to protect. On the back is their sigil: a circle representing the Inner Colannade with an inscribed triangle symbolizing the Flame itself.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Frozen_Feathe: A day before the wizard descended into the glacier to begin his hibernation, he offered Crystal Maiden these last, precious gifts: armor and a staff, strong as ice but light as a feather, believed to have once belonged to a winter deity.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Glacier_Duste:
A well-woven cape of dyed wolf pelt.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Gleaming_Seal:
A sweep of movement, a shift of dark leather, are all that the dead will have time to see.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Great_Safari: Simple, elegant, ripped from a corpse.  The scap of banner taken from a Vigil Knight now makes a fine cape for a Keen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Hazhadal_Mage: After besting the young mages of his order, Nortrom put his newfound skills to use suppressing the godless outlaws of the Hazhadall Barrens, routinely making short work of their vaunted enthrallers.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Hunters_Glory: Even the most skilled trackers may only hope to earn in a lifetime what Gondar claims on a single hunt.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Rising_Gale: The mysteries of her birth had always enchanted Lyralei and her adopted family. But as she grew, and her strange connection with the guardian wind became ever stronger, an unease about her origins began to take hold. And though she thought to run from it, her headlong path led only to the discovery of a difficult truth — that her village and blood kin had been destroyed by wind elementals on a night of righteous reckoning, and that such destruction was necessary to reclaim her as one of their own.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Rowdy_Firebra: \"I'm all for a good riot. But never got on much with looters. They don't like my style. They complain about it, but their screams stop eventually.\"
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Truebark_Adhe: When Virga Truebark defied the Iron Princeling and sounded the Oakfall Horn, let it be known that Verodicia's favored son stood with her, fighting loyally by her side.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cape_of_the_Wind_Leaf: A cape for all weather, this is a garment that any falconer would be proud to wear.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Capo_League: Capo League is an online-only tournament for amateur teams. The leagus consists of a group stage and a play-off for the 16 best teams.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Capo_League_Open_Qualific:
Capo League Open Qualification  is an online-only tournament for amateur and semi-professional teams.
	
	Winning teams will take part in the winter event!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Captain_Bamboo: Not just a Panda, He's a Captain!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Captains_Draft_30_Present: Captains Draft 3.0 brings you more unique gameplay consisting of some of the best teams in the world. Team captains are forced out of their comfort zone in the only professional tournament played in Captains Draft mode.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Captains_Draft_40_Minor:
Captains Draft, the most unique tournament in Dota 2, returns with its 4th installment as a LAN Minor taking place in Washington D.C. 
	
	CD 4.0 will yet again pit the best and brightest Dota minds together while they try and mash together diabolical patch defining lineups that will send reddit into ecstasy.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Captains_Hook: In waters as treacherous as those that surround the Trembling Isle, it is inevitable that even the most skilled captain sustain injury.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Carafe_2019_Autographed_b: This contains the same items as the Trove Carafe 2019 that will be autographed by your favorite Dota 2 caster.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Carapace_of_Bukivak_the_C: Far away beneath the Sunken Cities and through the Infernal Hollow, Buki'vak the Corrupted dwells in the depths forever expanding his corruption throughout the sea. Hearing of his power, Lion seeked to harvest his parts for a fresh demonoplasty. After a strenuous battle he defeated Buki'vak and gained the hand he desired as a reward, but it was not without cost. Just as his previous hand transformed him, so did this one. He became afflicted with the Malignant Corruption, causing unseemly shards of Obsidian to grow from his body and further disfigure him into something even more unrecognizeable from his original form.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Carapace_of_Gilded_Worshi: It has come to the attention of the Ultimyr Board of Overseers that a potential source of information on the so-called \"zealot scarab\" has been discovered in the unexplored lands beyond Ashkavor, six days upriver from the jungle ruins. Depart post-haste. Make contact at all costs. The board, and your reward, await response.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Carapace_of_Qaldin:
Required Level: 20

Passive: Acidic Regeneration - All mana and health gained are doubled, and a percentage of all damage taken is reflected back upon the attacker.

Bonus HP: 750
Bonus Mana: 750
Bonus Restore: 100%
Damage Returned: 33%
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Carapace_of_the_Chosen_La: Molted over the course of seven seasons by the slow administration of special alchemicals, this carapace is hardened against both blade and spell.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Carapace_of_the_Hidden_Hi: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Carapace of the Hidden Hive' set for Nyx Assassin:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Carry_TI10_Cavern_Crawl_S: This item can be used to unlock an alternate style for the Tellurian Trespass Divine Path item set for Slark.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Carved_Grin_of_the_Tricks: But does Yurnero ever smile beneath the mask?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Castors_Spaulder: The riverlands hero Castor Twin-Tusks challenged Verodicia's chosen prophet to an arcane duel. He lost.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Catalyst_Cap: The perfect accoutrement for when Lina wishes to \"Mix things up a bit.\" Which is almost always.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cauldron_of_Xahryx: Until at Sylla's paw the vile Xahryx fell asunder, the wildest power known was held within the cauldron's depths. In fear of what evil may seek such strength was the vessel taken, and put to heroic purpose.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cauldron_of_Xahryx_of_Emi: Claimed by Sylla from the horned Xahryx before The International 2013, this vile cauldron was given a new animation for Entangling Claws, and was the final indicator of the path that all future Immortals would follow.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cause_Gaming_Charity_Cup:
Cause Gaming brings you an open division charity tournament, showcasing some of South Africa's finest teams, who will battle for glory!
	
	Powered by Gigabyte and AORUS, casted by nAvTV. Proceeds benefit The Chaeli Campaign
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cause_Gaming_Spring_Seaso: Cause Gaming presents the Spring Seasonal DOTA 2 Tournament, powered by Gigabyte & Aorus. Teams compete for the grand prize in a double elimination format lasting over 2 days
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Caustic_Steel_Set: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Caustic Steel' set for Alchemist:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cavern_Crawl_2020_Slark_A: When the mother of all heists takes you into inhospitable environs en route to stealing the \"Dead God's Eye\" -- a cursed item long ago separated from its custodians and hidden by an exile of the Rumusque -- the wise thief's survival spares no expense.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cavern_Crawl_2020_Slark_H: When the mother of all heists takes you into inhospitable environs en route to stealing the \"Dead God's Eye\" -- a cursed item long ago separated from its custodians and hidden by an exile of the Rumusque -- the wise thief's survival spares no expense.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cavernite_Dire_Creeps: These custom creeps can be equipped in the World options of the Global Items loadout menu.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cavernite_Radiant_Creeps: These custom creeps can be equipped in the World options of the Global Items loadout menu.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Celestial_Observatory: This ancient ward has stood watch nearly as long as the stars themselves.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Censer_of_Gliss: When the mobs in pursuit at last grew too large to justify slaughter, and word of his frequent reprisals had attracted powerful foes, Rhasta ventured deep into the earth, guided by something he could not name. But even in the darkest caverns, he would find those covetous of his gifts. Where he sought kinship, strife would always follow. But a part of him seemed at home in the dark, and when a lordly serpent priest raised a cursed decanter to strike him down, Rhasta vowed to retreat no more.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cercus_of_Whirling_Death: Sandking uses these pincers as another set of hands, grappling onto prey as they scuttle above his sandy hideaway.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cerebral_Support: What ancient beast once wore this?  The Tidehunter cares not.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ceremonial_Carapace_of_Qa: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Ceremonial Carapace of Qaldin' set for Sand King:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ceremonial_Claws_of_Qaldi: Incised with the luminous runes of Qezh, the upraised claws of the Scintillant Supplicant summon the full attention of the Djinn of Qaldin.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ceremonial_Crawlers_of_Qa: All the rites of Qaldin are done as dance, with each step prescribed and enacted in precise detail. A misstep can mean an age of misfortune. But Sand King has never put one crawler wrong.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ceremonial_Horns: The avatar of Nature's Wrath may take whatever form he pleases. Choosing sometimes to appear as tree, other times as predator, or when it suits him as prey.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ceremonial_Pshent_of_Qald: The sentient sands of the Scintillant Waste don this glorious headpiece for only their most sacred rites.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ceremonial_Rapier: More a prize than a weapon, this rapier was looted from some unfortunate prince's treasure ship as it navigated the Narrow Channel.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ceremonial_Stinger_of_Qal: At the height of the ceremony of Qaz'hallaq, seven virtuous acolytes are stung to death with one swipe of this malevolent armored appendage.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ceremonial_Thorax_of_Qald: Behold! This ritual adornment celebrates the flawless power of the Djinn who first poured the Sentient Sand into a suit of magical armor. Flawless and mighty, like the Djinn itself, a thorax for only the most sacred of occasions.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chain_of_Enduring_Torment: She may be chained, but she is still in control.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chained_Chopper: Tangled in the links of Pudge's chains, a reminder of the shackles that bind us to life--and how easily Pudge may break them.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chained_Guard: A little armor can go a long way.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chained_Mistress_Set: Includes all of the items in the 'Chained Mistress' set for Queen of Pain:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chained_Slayers_Set: This bundle contains all of the items in 'Chained Slayers' for Pudge:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chained_Snatcher: Never give a meal the chance to be late for dinner.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chained_Spur: Delight in pain as they squeal with agony.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chained_Wings: Let her have you, and she will keep you.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chains_of_the_Summoned_Lo: Contains all of the items in the 'Chains of the Summoned Lord' set:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chalice_of_Ixyxa: The Nether Reaches teem with baleful life, none more fearsome than Ix'yxa the destroyer. Grown too corpulent from feasting to traverse known passages to our domain, Ix'yxa barters favors to those who might act as proxy in seeking a new path.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Champion_of_Discord: Contains all of the items in the 'Champion of Discord' set for Chaos Knight plus loading screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Champion_of_Emauracus: The wings symbolize the soaring heights of the cliffs of Emauracus, where it is said that the Omniscience itself may bless the pious with holy visions.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Champion_of_Nurgle: Contains the Champion of Nurgle set for Pudge, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Champions_Belly_Belt: Aggron says they won it in a game of chance.  Who are we to argue?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Champions_Chest: No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. This treasure contains full item sets.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Champions_Cup_Ticket: This ticket is proof that the owner has qualified for the Champions Cup.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Champions_Vs_Challengers_: A new Dota 2 league, where Champions and Challengers fight for glory. Who will survive? Will the challengers emerge as the new champions? Lets find out.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chaos_Chosen: Contains the Chaos Chosen set for Centaur Warrunner, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chaos_Fulcrum: Bound to purpose on the hunt for the pale rider, the Chaos Fulcrum strains even against the order of its own existence as it bends reality to devour rays from the first Light.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chaos_Knights_Armlet_of_M: From sacrifice comes power.  From power flows chaos.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chaos_of_the_Infernal_Maw:
While some amongst the Ultimyr faculty share concerns regarding the peculiar nature of Chief Curator Lannik's studies, none can deny that under his watch the Academy's archives of arcane knowledge have grown incomparably.

Contains the Chaos of the Infernal Maw set for Warlock, including the Loading Screen

Though depictions of his body and form differ in the telling, the crackle of the Lightning Revenant's whip is known to all of the blessed few who have returned to life from the Narrow Maze.

This item can be upgraded with the 'Compact of the Guardian Construct Style Unlock' granted to players who complete at least 40 stars on the Path of the Dominator.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chestplate_of_the_Hieroph: A Hierophant of the Omniscience must always sense the power that protects him.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chrome_Vial:
Auctioned from the estate of a brilliant but failed alchemist, these mystical vials have the power to transform liquid water into nearly any substance. However, a steady hand is required. The next item on the auction block was the chromed corpse of the sneezing thaumaturge himself. Vial art, indeed.

Stand in the river to reveal the vial interface. Pour the contents into the river to transform it for 3 minutes. Each vial can be used once per game.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chronite_Armor: The time-altering properties of chronite stabilizes the Faceless Void's presence in the material realm.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chronite_Bracers: A pair of chronite encrusted bracers that seem to warn the Faceless Void of his enemies' future attacks.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chronite_Scepter: A symbol of power within the infinite halls of Claszureme.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chronoptic_Crown: Heavy is the head that wears this crown.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_ChuangLeague_S3: This league is designed for college students to create cultural exchange platform. The tournament covers more than 1,000 colleges and universities. Our specific goal is to become the first nationwide  College tournament.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Chuangleague: The Chuangleague is a ShanghaiLanyou Cultural Communications Limited company held tournament. This league is a NewBee club competition for all Chinese College Students.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cicatrix_Regalia: Includes all items in the 'Cicatrix Regalia' set for Nyx Assassin and includes 4 different styles:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cinch_of_the_Mortal_Coil: A fine crimson cloth adorned by the Death Prophet.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cinder_Sensei: Contains the Cinder Sensei set for Ember Spirit
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Circlet_of_Forsaken_Beaut: A circlet of golden laurels holds the delicate veil that hid Medusa's once-beautiful face.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Circlet_of_the_Northern_W: Worn proudly wherever she goes, Lyralei reminds the world that it is her business to turn back the inevitable, and discover victory where others have foretold defeat.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Circlet_of_the_Purist_Cha: For Omniknight, no show of loyalty is too great.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Circuito_LVP_Dota_2: Some of the best teams in Spain compete for the 3,500 Euro prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Cudgel: After many years, Leviathan recently stumbled upon the sunken wreckage of his rival's fleet. He now wields the mast of their flagship as a cudgel, and woe betide any who get in his way.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Gauntlets: The only piece of equipment left on Kunkka after he washed up on a Keen shore.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Guard: A high collar keeps salty waters and harsh weather from marring Kunkka's visage, while heavy shoulder-plates have deflected many a tooth and claw belonging to such abominations as lurk in the murky waters.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Hightops: These steel toe-guards are effective at fending off sea monsters, as well as punishing booties of lazy Keen sailors.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Voyagers_Chestpl: Don't let the plate fool you; he'd much rather the jacket survived the battle unharmed.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Voyagers_Elegant: If you're going to travel, do it in style.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Voyagers_First_C: For when a sword won't do.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Voyagers_Gloves: The quality of an admiral's gloves is directly related to how well they can grip a sword.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Voyagers_Helm: The steel sweep and sprouting brush are said to be of Kunkka's own design.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Voyagers_Second_: For when both a sword and a pistol still won't do.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claddish_Voyagers_Treads: When you walk the deck, make sure they know who's in charge.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claive_of_Unyielding_Ston: When Sven stands his ground, this blade stands with him.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Clandestine_Trail: Includes all of the items in the 'Clandestine Trail' set for Templar Assassin plus a loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Clarity_of_the_Crystal_Pa: Contains the Clarity of the Crystal Path set for Oracle
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Clash_of_Pubs: A league for the causal pubers to show their competitive spirit.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Class_Zero_Moogle: The Military Operation Organization/Guidance Logistics Expert (or \"MOOGLE\") is an expert in the art of war, and wants nothing more than to ensure that heroes have a safe trip across the battlefield.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claw_Dota_League__The_Cha: The tournament brings together amateur and semi-professional teams for an amazing contest.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claw_Dota_League__Wekeend: An amateur championship Dota 2 for the South American scene.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claw_of_the_Ancient_Sover: In the fragmentary legends of the Ancient Sovereign, death by such claws was something greatly to be desired.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claw_of_the_Haruspex: Serpent Clan long held to the traditions of the haruspex, and so foresaw the ruin and war that would visit the ancient clans.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claw_of_the_Umizar_Crawle: For those with a taste for gambling and excess treasure to spend, the hidden grottos of Crey host all manner of speculative bloodsports.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claws_of_the_Blood_Moon: Banehallow often takes solace in the company of any fellow afflicted he might encounter in his wanderings. Not all, however, find the company of their own kind so agreeable.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claws_of_the_Chainbreaker: The cruelties devised by the nobles of Devarque and their progeny remained novel long after N'aix's mind could no longer fathom the meaning of punishment.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claws_of_the_Ferocious_He: Ambient particle effects can be unlocked on this item using the Tribute Upgrade Infuser - Fall Season 2015.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claws_of_the_Hidden_Hive: When the new Nyx Assassin is chosen, he is sent to the Hidden Hive for confirmation. These claws connote completion of the Assassin's first assignment.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Claws_of_the_Sangstrath_F: Rich in oral history, Ulfsaar's kin still celebrate the legends of the Sangstrath--ancient guardians of a fabled civilization and the first ancestors to settle the current lands of the ursine tribe after disaster befell their own.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cleaver_of_the_Hidden_Hun: An already heavy blade, made even heavier by the weighted ring looped through the top. This is not a weapon for finesse, but for taking the enemy's head in a single strike.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cleft_Hawks_Call: One among the many striders of Upland Druud, the timid Cleft Hawk makes its home within the many fissures dotting the plains.  The mating call of a Cleft Hawk is said to be as grating as it is unbelievably loud.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Clergy_Warhammer: When you are Omniknight's hammer, every opponent resembles a nail.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_ClickStorm_DOTA_2_League: Click-Storm DOTA 2 League is a league for those who want to play with friends, get positive emotions and become more experienced. Main partners of the league are hitbox.tv, Plantronics and VakeTV.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_Inscrutable_Zeal: To have a hope of examining the darkened wilds undetected requires clothing fit for subtlety.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Battleranger:
To some authorities, the line between ranger and ruffian is nearly nonexistent.

This item can be upgraded with the 'Bindings of the Battleranger Style Unlock' granted to players who complete all fifteen Three-Star objectives on the Path of the Spellbinder.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Bear:
There's no shortage of natural armor in the wild.

Required Level: 6

Aura: Rough Bearskin
Provides 10% bonus magic resistance to nearby allies.

SELF BONUS MAGIC RESIST: 25
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Boreal_Watch: Three layers of cloth and fur help to guard against the northern winds.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Dark_Wraith: Mortred's choice of garb is as mysterious as her choice of target.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Dawn: The Bear Clan taught that every rising sun was a gift, and so appointed one among them to greet the dawn each day.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Demonic_Vess: These items were created in partnership with Alliance, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Exact_Marksm: Created in partnership with YYF, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Haruspex: As Serpent Clan spread word of their coming doom, they granted their honored vestments to Sylla that he may remember their words.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Nimble_Edge: To guard against things unseen and unknown.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Northern_Win: In certain parts of certain worlds, the Northern wind blows warm, with a promise of eternal spring.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_One_True_Kin: In an age lost even to his own memory, Ostarion fed his lust for eternal life not with spectral essence, but a nigh-unending harvest of bone. The walls of his palace were formed of fired bone; the streets paved with bones of every sort of creature and every enemy. And those of the flesh who entered this domain took great care, for the King was first and foremost a collector, and nothing moved in the Empire of Bone without summoning the gaze of his unblinking eyes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloak_of_the_Stormcrow: A cloak crafted from the feathers and talons of the stormcrow.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Clock_Master: Includes all of the items in the 'Clock Master' set for Clockwerk:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Clockwerk_Announcer_Pack:
This pack replaces the Default announcer and Mega-Kills announcer with the metal moxie of Clockwerk. Includes the Telebolt Projektor cog item for Clockwerk!
	
	Announcer available in English, Chinese, and Korean languages. Killing Spree available in English and Korean languages.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Closed_Tournament_Season_: Closed Tournament for players on the gaming platform ProStage
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloth_of_Lucid_Torment:
The dreamer's eyes are opened to a world of anguish.

This item can be upgraded with the 'Lucid Torment Style Unlock' granted to players who complete at least 40 stars on the Path of the Protector.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloth_of_the_Clergy_Ascet: What clergy approved this lurid wrap and thought it suitable for an ascetic lifestyle? None survive to justify their decision.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloud_Forged_Battle_Gear_: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Cloud Forged Battle Gear Set' for Skywrath Mage:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloud_Forged_Great_Bracer: Solid bracers with a wide surace area designed to block a wide variety of attacks.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloud_Forged_Great_Girdle: Strips of cloth gilded with mithril and fastened to a sturdy girdle. The trail of this belt is spoken of among foot soldiers who gaze to the sky above to see Dragonus fly through the clouds.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloud_Forged_Great_Helm: This ornate helm was once seen worn by royal guards of the nest.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cloud_Forged_Great_Mantle: This mantle dons a masterful shape to deflect blades but its deeper enchantments protect from sorcery as well.

No longer shall a heroes thirst go unquenched! The call for brew is sacred and by oath it must be upheld! The brew must flow.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Compass_of_the_Rising_Gal: The mysteries of her birth had always enchanted Lyralei and her adopted family. But as she grew, and her strange connection with the guardian wind became ever stronger, an unease about her origins began to take hold. And though she thought to run from it, her headlong path led only to the discovery of a difficult truth — that her village and blood kin had been destroyed by wind elementals on a night of righteous reckoning, and that such destruction was necessary to reclaim her as one of their own.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Copy_of_Dolfrat_and_Roshi: \"How did I get here?\" Such words of power are commonly heard from Dolfrat the Wizard, whose magic is so great that even he cannot grasp it. Indeed, his enemies accuse him of having no magical training whatsoever, pointing to the evidence of his most frequent incantation: \"Did I do that?\" And should you ever spy the mighty Dolfrat flat on his back in the road, you can be sure his trusty steed Roshinante is somewhere nearby--probably galloping at top speed away from a creaky tree or shadow that resembled a demon of nightmarish power.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Covenant_of_the_Depths: Contains the Covenant of the Depths set for Invoker, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Covert_Saboteur: Contains all items from the Covert Saboteur set, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Coveted_Arms_Cache: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Coveted Arms Cache':
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cowl_of_Ice: In the frigid north, that which is lost to myth may still be found within the ice. In an age now lost to time, the Frozen Witch Yulsaria ruled the whitelands, summoning blizzards and hail storms upon those who displeased her, while an army of ice golems roamed the lands to snuff out all warmth. In time, her southward expansion angered the Eldwurm Slyrak who, in his terrible rage, melted Yulsaria's armies with his endless flame before conquering the Frozen Witch herself. Now, centuries later, shifts in the ice have heaved up the last remaining shard of her empire: her glacial crown.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cowl_of_the_Blood_Covenan: He needs not eyes, who is guided by the sight of the Flayed ones.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cowl_of_the_Blood_Stained: The hunter hides his face for various reasons, but in the desert wastes the sun is enemy enough.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cowl_of_the_Boreal_Watch: For those who wish their face never to be seen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cowl_of_the_Gluttons_Lard: Though the endless march of adventuring fools certainly disturbed the safety of her spiderlings, the constant supply of fresh treasure hunters did wonders for Arachnia's figure.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cowl_of_the_Malignant_Cor: Far away beneath the Sunken Cities and through the Infernal Hollow, Buki'vak the Corrupted dwells in the depths forever expanding his corruption throughout the sea. Hearing of his power, Lion seeked to harvest his parts for a fresh demonoplasty. After a strenuous battle he defeated Buki'vak and gained the hand he desired as a reward, but it was not without cost. Just as his previous hand transformed him, so did this one. He became afflicted with the Malignant Corruption, causing unseemly shards of Obsidian to grow from his body and further disfigure him into something even more unrecognizeable from his original form.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Craggy_Coat:
Required Level: 13

When the wearer takes damage, there is a 25% chance to retaliate with a thrown boulder, which deals 125 damage and stuns for 0.6 seconds.

BONUS STRENGTH: 20
BONUS ARMOR: 10
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cranial_Clap_Trap: Skulls, it turns out, are a hindrance when one is attempting to chemically manipulate one's ogre.  Razzil has eliminated that obstruction.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Craniomancer: A round head is an abomination.  So too, a round back.  Dark Seer now sports the cranium most ideal in all the universe.  In a battle of wits and wills, the pointiest head will often prevaile.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crashgame_League: 16 Iranian teams will clash over the Price of $400 in the first Crashgame Tournament!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crawlers_of_the_Ancient_S: Sandking pays tribute to the Ancient Sovereign with every step.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crazy_Cup_#1: CIS teams compete in a tournament which features two unique modes: Ability Draft and Reverse Draft! Teams will fight for a prize pool of 6000 Rubles!

Required Level: 3

Passive: Grants 15% bonus XP
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Creepers_Cruel_Hook: Gold is only one reason why Gondar hunts.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Creepers_Cruel_Painsaw: None would say that Gondar the Bounty Hunter does not take pleasure in his work.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crescent: Contains all of the items in the 'Crescent' item set for Mirana plus loading screen and custom Sacred Arrow.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crescent_Sickle_of_the_Dr: This sickle is a symbol and ritualistic tool of the Bear Clan, a forgotten druidic order that sought to restore the world.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crest_of_the_Burning_Caba: The war-crest of the Burning Cabal. This identifies the invoker as a specialist in fire manipulation.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crest_of_the_Fatal_Bloom: Unseen by Lesale in his urgent compounding, the orchid of his salvation was also host to the pulsing cocoon of a Fradjan moth.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crest_of_the_Flowering_Sh:
Ambient particle effects can be unlocked on this item using the Tribute Upgrade Infuser - Fall Season 2015.

Created in partnership with Hao, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crest_of_the_Magus_Magnus: A crest that crackles with the arcane might of Wex.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crest_of_the_Shifting_Sor:
A skilled shifter and sorcerer, Throsho often took a demon's form to intimidate those who lived within his realm. Those frightened by his appearance grew in time to worship him, often bringing him ornamental tithes.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crest_of_the_Vermillion_C:
'Neath vermillion plates
The shifting form
Of the star
Reborn.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crest_of_the_Wyrm_Lords: The dragon comes for war.  He also comes with a big, heavy shield of dragon-forged steel on his arm.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crests_of_Polymorphia: The power of Polymorphia is but barely contained between these splendid crests, and takes its most awe-inspiring form in the shape of their devoted wearer, Morphling.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crests_of_the_Falling_Com: As the comet fell, the power of Morphling crested. Perfect for slicing through enemies as you shoulder them aside.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crimson_Beast: Contains the Crmison Beast set for Earthshaker, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crimson_Cyrridae: The skill of a master Weaver is plainly seen in the spread of its antennae, each tendril allowing added complexity to the Weaver's astral loom.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crimson_Parcel_2016: A prize for completing a quest along the Path of the Blossom. Open it to claim your gift!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crimson_Pique: With eyes upon threads of strife, the exiled Skitskurr conjures patterns yet unseen in the fabric of the cosmic tapestry. Soon he will see these imagined swatches realized, woven from the tatters of the conflict to come.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crimson_Riptide: Let this blade drink deep of your foe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crimson_Wyvern_Bracers: Made from the interlocking scales that sit above the wyvern's spine, this crimson bracer is a perfect fit for knight's forearm.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crimson_Wyvern_Helm: A helm forged in the likeness of the ancient Crimson Wyvern.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crimson_Wyvern_Shield: Is that the eyes of the Crimson Wyvern that peer out from this ancient shield?  I think it is.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crimson_Wyvern_Shoulders: Constructed from the scales of a fallen wyvern, this shoulder armor is a mark of distinction for any knight.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crimson_Wyvern_Skirt: Protect your legs with the skirt of the Crimson Wyvern.  You are manly enough to pull it off; you're a knight after all.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crimson_Wyvern_Sword_: A sword made from the talons of a fallen wyvern.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Critter_Egg: A magical egg used to unlock new Smeevil styles.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crown_of_Black_Nihility: Those among the prey of the creatures of primordial night grew to worship their masters, and fashioned arms to honor their magnificence. Upon the head of the greatest of their kind was placed the Crown of Black Nihility, a symbol of terrible darkness.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crown_of_Gilded_Worship: It has come to the attention of the Ultimyr Board of Overseers that a potential source of information on the so-called \"zealot scarab\" has been discovered in the unexplored lands beyond Ashkavor, six days upriver from the jungle ruins. Depart post-haste. Make contact at all costs. The board, and your reward, await response.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crown_of_Hells:
Upon my crown, I'll gore thee.

These items commemorate the release of Valve's documentary, Free to Play, and were created in partnership with hyhy, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crown_of_Sacred_Light: Some brethren proselytize without speaking a word; their sermons may be heard only in the ringing blows of the hammer.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crown_of_Shifting_Forms: Morphling emulates the eternal patterns of Polymorphia in all he does. And by this crown, he marks himself a master of the art.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crown_of_Tears: As his birthing battle's curtain fell, the Morphling gathered to him the scant debris expelled in the melting flash of his earthly plunge. If war was the way of this world, he would fashion his own set of martial regalia.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crown_of_Vincere: The Queen wears her nightmare crown.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crown_of_the_Brood_Queen: With shaking hands, the doomed blacksmith laid a crown upon the spider's head, saying, \"A crown fit for a queen.\"
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crown_of_the_Comets_Tail: Although unknown to the land-based historians of terrestrial empires, the mythologies of sea-dwelling creatures oft look to the moon and stars for wisdom and guidance.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crown_of_the_Death_Priest: Death Prophet consecrates her union with death by donning this regal headdress. She only takes it off again with deep regret.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crown_of_the_Eminence_of_: Content for so long exploring the playground of the mortal realm, Akasha returns now to the dangerous Court of Ristul, where her star has fallen in her time away. But the Queen above intends to claim as well the throne below. Striking a bargain with an exiled demon prince, Akasha has seized a new measure of power, and her fiendish plans are at last set to begin.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crown_of_the_Ethereal_Mon: The royal regalia of Undertree? A juvenile dragon's nameday finery? Only Puck knows, and it's not telling.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crown_of_the_Falling_Come: From darkness, the comet came carrying the wotery essence of Morphling. As it fell, a searing crown marked its encounter with the atmosphere. Morphling wears it now.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crown_of_the_Gluttons_Lar: Though the endless march of adventuring fools certainly disturbed the safety of her spiderlings, the constant supply of fresh treasure hunters did wonders for Arachnia's figure.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crown_of_the_One_True_Kin: In an age lost even to his own memory, Ostarion fed his lust for eternal life not with spectral essence, but a nigh-unending harvest of bone. The walls of his palace were formed of fired bone; the streets paved with bones of every sort of creature and every enemy. And those of the flesh who entered this domain took great care, for the King was first and foremost a collector, and nothing moved in the Empire of Bone without summoning the gaze of his unblinking eyes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crown_of_the_Truebark_Adh: When Virga Truebark defied the Iron Princeling and sounded the Oakfall Horn, let it be known that Verodicia's favored son stood with her, fighting loyally by her side.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crucible_of_Light: Includes all of the items in the 'Crucible of Light' set for Keeper of the Light plus a loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Crucible_of_Rile: The Crucible of Rile both feeds upon and fuels the anger of any who don it. Always found upon a melted husk surrounded by a mess of corpses and viscera, it has never once passed between two pair of living hands.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cruelties_of_the_Spiral_B: Contains the Cruelties of the Spiral Bore set for Magnus, including the Loading Screen

This pass activates premium content in the Crumbling Island Arena custom game and supports the creators of this custom game.
Owning a Crumbling Island Arena Custom Game Pass will Unlock:
3 cosmetic items, 3 hero voice emotes, 3 taunts.

Gold text color in chat.
Expires 30 days after purchase.

For when carried in a fist of stone, Aghanim's scepter unleashes the spirit of the Crystal Dryad, and no foe is safe.

With fee 100 RUB with the team.1st place will receive 50%, 2nd place 30%, and 3rd place 20%.The tournament will be broadcast in Dota 2 TV

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cuffs_of_Oak_and_Yew: \"Below me trees unnumber'd rise, beautiful in various dyes; the gloomy pine, the poplar blue, the yellow beech, the sable-yew, the slender fir, that taper grows, the sturdy oak with broad-spread boughs...\"
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cuffs_of_the_Iron_Will: From planes beyond and essence untold charges a force to end all.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cult_Mask_of_the_Mage_Sla: The elements used in this mask's construction are able to deflect most spells, just as its shape may divert a blade.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Cult_of_Aktok: Following a particularly injurious victory, the Venomancer slithered into a crack in the earth, to coil around himself and focus on regaining full strength. But his chosen place of rest had a much older purpose. It was there that the worshippers of Aktok, an ancient serpent god destined to swallow the world, would gather once each season to offer sacrifice in Aktok's name. Mistaken for a herald of their lord, Venomancer was content to receive the offerings directly...until his strength returned, and he could trail the shamans back to their village for a much larger meal.

Rare though is the stormcrafter who dares try and control the pugnacious steambear.  That the young bear Maximilian now travels unaccompanied is proof that the domestication process did not go well.  For the stormcrafter.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dark_Artistry_Throwback: Amongst the varied and complicated array of uniforms worn by students of the world's most renowned academy for the mystic arts, none are more coveted by pupils than the school's formal battle dress. Issued only in times of great calamity or sorrow, no student had worn such a suit in living memory. That is, until a gifted young mage decided to liberate one on his self-chosen day of graduation...
