Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dark_Generals_Mantle: A golden mantle from Dark Seer's days as one of god-king Damathryx's great generals.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dark_Maw_Inhibitor: Though the craftsmanship and melding of his design seemed flawless, it was only too late that the erstwhile enchanter's apprentice realized the intended controlling agent of his muzzle hadn't bound itself to the device during his ritual -- not at all.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dark_Moon_Baby_Roshan: Don't let looks deceive. This little guy knows exactly what he's doing.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dark_Moon_Emoticon: Unlocks the Dark Moon Chicken emoticon, awarded for averting Dark Moon
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dark_Moon_Stalker: The Dark Moon faithful consist of former scholars, laborers, orphans, and thieves. One may have served as magistrate of a city, another spilled blood as a warlord in the wilds. They have walked all imaginable paths to find Selemene. In her service, the trials and tragedies of the past matter not. They worship the Goddess together, guardians of the Nightsilver Woods.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dark_Pantheon: Though his powers may not be what they once were -- a temporary issue of course -- the god of thunder isn't keen to let his position in the pantheon slip so easily away.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dark_Quiver_of_the_Vandal: Endless arrows shall be pulled from the pouch over your shoulder.  Enemies will quiver at the sight.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dark_Ruin_Gaze: It is said the blind forgemasters of the Ruined Keep are haunted by visions of realms beyond mortal knowledge.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dark_Ruin_Helm: In the molten furnace of the Ruined Keep, the blind forgemasters craft their wares.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dark_Ruin_Mantle: Upon the shoulders of darkness sit the burdens of chaos.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dark_Ruin_Mount: Where rides the knight, only chaos remains.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Darkstar_the_Mistforged: This ancestral blade of House Avernus was cast into the Font, to be forged anew. What emerged was an amalgam of steel, and mist, that feasts upon the souls of its foes.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Daughters_of_Hydrophiinae: Though lost to Medusa in the physical realm, the ethereal presence of the Gorgon sisters charges this ancestral armor to watch over their youngest sibling.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Davions_Broken_Dragon_Hol: Swords forged without dragon magic are a poor match against even a young wurm's scales.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Davions_Dragon_Hold_Pauld: While billowing capes are certainly cool, when the battle gets heated, it's the first thing to go.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Davions_Dragon_Hold_Perso: Protect Davion's charming mug with a helmet featuring a custom Ability Icon for Dragon's Blood.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dawn_of_the_Moon: On the night of each new moon, rites are sung and offerings burned in honor of the goddess of the moon, Selemene, in the hope that her countenance may shine once more. To wear the garb customary to these rituals is considered a sacred honor.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dead_Winter_Set: Includes all of the items in the 'Dead Winter' set for Lich:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deadly_Gaming_Cup_Season_: 16 professional teams compete for the $10,000 prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deadwinter_Arms: After years of the frost stirring deep inside him it began to creep out, seeking to claim him as if it had a life of its own. Enchanted cloth on his arms are a last line of defense against the icy claws reaching towards Ethreain by the dangerous, otherworldly power within.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deadwinter_Back: Over time, the frost magic had birthed a powerful force within Ethreain. It began to florish and bloom, eventually maturing enough to manifest physically in the form of a dense crystal in his back. It continues to grow steadily and appears to reach, seeking to embrace the mage himself.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deadwinter_Belt: Mastery of certain magics come with a price. As Ethreain honed his skill and grew stronger he encased his legs in ice and gathered shards to shield him. His sash helps to balance the frost within so that it does not consume him.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deadwinter_Neck: His ascension to a new throne and reign of ice deserved fitting attire - Ethreain reclaimed his tattered cloak from the previous life and imbued it with a darkened frost-bound undead aura.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deaf_eSports_League_Copa_:
The Deaf Opening Cup will take place online with the game Dota 2.
	With four teams invited will face off for 2 months to win the first title of the Deaf e-Sports League.
	Our goal is to establish a regular, competitive league and as a basis and incentive for train times and beyond to seek good results, also have visibility on the national scene.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Death_Mask_of_the_Brave: In the face of the great beast, Juggernaut saw bravery.  In the mask made from the creature's skull, Juggernaut's foes see death.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Death_Mask_of_the_Conquer: Wear this mask, and it will be the last face your enemies ever see.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deep_Vault_Guardian_Spine: A guardian's spinal display serves as an identifier to his peers, and a warning to his foes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deep_Vault_Guardian_Tride: Few creatures of the deep are able to heft such a heavy weapon, let alone weild it.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deep_Warden_Cape: There's not a lot to a darkray, but you'll find what's there to be pretty durable.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deep_Warden_Scimitar: No weapon was more prized among the warden's private collection, nor more missed when it vanished.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deep_Wardens_Conch_Pauldr: They say a glow conch can fetch a pretty penny on the black market.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deep_Wardens_Impounded_Ho: They say the thief that used to own this hood killed eleven guards before he was finally sent up for air.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deep_Wardens_Tooth_Bracer: If you're going to go through all the trouble of breaking out of prison, you may as well take a few souvenirs!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deepest_Depths: Within the coldest depths one must be clever and adaptable, or become food for one that is.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deepshock_Destroyer: There is nothing the drylanders can prepare against the depths that the servants of Maelrawn cannot repurpose for their own.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Deepweed_Drowner: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Deepweed Drowner' set for Tidehunter plus loading screen. These items and were created in partnership with Yol, who receives a portion of every purchase.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Defense_2_Chest: A special reward for early subscribers to <font color='#9da1a9'>The Defense Season 2</font> tournament. Included with a key used to open this chest. Thank you for helping us test and improve our tournament features!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Defense_Grid_Announcer_Pa: This pack replaces the Default announcer and Mega-Kills announcer with the upbeat wisdom of Defense Grid's very own General Fletcher.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Defense_of_the_Arabians: The first Defense of the Arabians takes the top Middle Eastern teams to compete for a prize and to become champions!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Defense_of_the_Australian: Defense of the Australians brings you its second Dota 2 Tournament for Spring 2013 with players from all around Melbourne, Australia coming together to compete.

The Autumn season arrives! Open qualifiers of 64 teams around Australia competing against each other until only 8 teams remain! Those teams will then battle against our top 8 teams of Summer 2014 and be crowned AustraliaÃ¢ÂÂs #1 team. Finals will take place at the Defense HQ in Melbourne.
Defense of the Australians brings you its summer 2014 tournament. Professional teams throughout Australia will compete Australia wide online and in a Melbourne LAN event finals.

This ticket gives you access to view games from the Defense of the Australians Season 3 Leagu and the Hobbly Cape for Sniper.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Delicacies_of_Butchery_Se: Includes all of the items in the 'Delicacies of Butchery' set for Pudge plus loading screen:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Delightful_Affliction: Contains the Delightful Affliction set for Queen of Pain, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Delights_of_Petaluna: Though the priests of Dezun believe they alone possess the secrets of the ethereal shade, Dazzle's discovery of a race of insects in the lost jungles of Fellstrath capable of suckling energy directly from the Nothl Realm puts that claim to rest. But these creatures are inefficient with their feeding, and each puncture they create allows a bit of influence from the Nothl Realm to bleed into our own.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Delights_of_Petaluna__Sty: This International 2019 Battle Pass reward enables an upgraded style to be unlocked on the Delights of Petaluna set for Dazzle through the style menu. You can use this item multiple times to unlock styles on all of the items in the set.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Blade_of_Apocalypti: A cursed blade forged to slice through the membrane that separates the seven hells.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Blood_Armor: Heavy platemail forged in the blood of the Tarnsmen's dead gods.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Blood_Guard: When the Red Mist consumed the Thousand Tarns, the lakes turned red with the blood of the slain. Many demons masquerading as the lawmakers and priests of that doomed civilization were also destroyed, their blood mixing with that of the mortals they once ruled.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Blood_Helm: A helm bearing the cyclopean visage of the Tarnsmen's demonic war god. It is said the Red Mist destroyed the god and took its symbols for their own.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Claive: Sven seemed overcome with nostalgia at the sight of this sword, though he would not say why.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Eater: Shadow Fiend has long collected the souls of his enemies. As is the case with any collector, some prizes have stood above others, to be sought out at any cost. However, there are certain souls that should not be tried, and forces so dark and filled with rage that no being could hope to contain them. Thus did Shadow Fiend learn the price, and gift, that comes with stealing the souls of demons, and he was changed evermore.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Guise_of_the_Vandal: For a hundred years, a blind smeevil hammered and honed his masterpiece, until the great work was done.  None shall see your face behind the iron mask of the Demon Guise.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Quiver_of_the_Crypt: He's got eyes in the back of his back.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Shard: Shattered during the cataclysmic battle of Heaven's Gate, the Blade of Worlds fell as a thousand pieces. Smuggled back into the foundries of Hell, the largest fragment was later reformed, the runes upon its surface shifting to denote a new name, Demon Shard.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Skull_Staff: Witch Doctor clearly has a thing for skulls.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Demon_Spine_Recurve_Bow: Made from the vertebrae of the fallen damned, this bow is crooked as the spine of any demon.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dolfrat_and_Roshinante: \"How did I get here?\" Such words of power are commonly heard from Dolfrat the Wizard, whose magic is so great that even he cannot grasp it. Indeed, his enemies accuse him of having no magical training whatsoever, pointing to the evidence of his most frequent incantation: \"Did I do that?\" And should you ever spy the mighty Dolfrat flat on his back in the road, you can be sure his trusty steed Roshinante is somewhere nearby--probably galloping at top speed away from a creaky tree or shadow that resembled a demon of nightmarish power.

No weapon is more feared by the involuntary inhabitants of the Underscape.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dota_2_Professional_Leagu: The Dota 2 Professional League (DPL) is the most prestigious league in China, and will feature a prize-pool of USD$1 million over two seasons. DPL: Sponsored by the General Administration of Sport in collaboration with Perfect World, MarsTV is hosting China's premiere league, DPL China DOTA 2 Professional League. Fall season officially begins in September with 3 months of exciting tournaments. This tournament will be divided into two types of leagues, and 20 top Chinese DOTA 2 professional teams participating to determine China's DOTA 2 kings!
	
	Notes: Altogether, a total of 20 Chinese teams will compete in the the two leagues.

The Dota 2 Professional League - Amateur is hosted by the Sports Information Center of National Sports General Administration, organized by MarsTV and officially supported by Perfect World, and aims at giving a chance to amateur players without a team to prove themselves, and hopefully catch the attention of teams playing at a higher level.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Double_Vision: This mascot of the powerful Pyrexae has two heads with which to scout for trouble!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Doubly_Braided_Beard: A force as mighty as nature itself should not be content with merely one beard.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Draca_Maw: When he first heard rumors of the \"unkillable\" draca eels that swim the magma rivers of Krulcsar, Huskar paid no mind. It was only in the midst of a firelodge vision quest that the eels' true potential became clear.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dragon_Forged_Armor: Forged in the plasmic residue of a star called Dragon, this armor protects as no mere dragon hide ever could.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dragon_Forged_Set: Contains all of the items in the 'Dragon Forged' set for Outworld Devourer:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dragon_Forged_Staff: Small minds are quickly broken.  With this mace, small bodies, even quicker.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dragon_Forged_Stare: Their sanity I'll shatter.  Their dreams of conquest I'll destroy.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dragon_Forged_Wings: The Harbinger bears dark tidings on swift wings.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dragon_Knight_Persona_Dav: The knights of Dragon Hold know firsthand the suffering and hardships that await those left orphaned by dragon-strike. But only one amongst them has glimpsed the thunderous truths of the universe through the eyes of an eldwurm. Now he fights for a greater purpose than vengeance or glory. Even as he fears the loss of a soul.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dragon_Sword: A blade inspired by a dragon's fire. Warning: May contain actual soul of dragon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dragon_Wall_Totem: That which the strength of earth may create, the strength of earth may destroy, chewed into dust by shifting rock. Where once, in a time before knowledge of time, great stone giants built their cities, now lies an endless sea of pebbles. At its center yawns a great fissure, filled with the gravel remains of the countless many. Only a single segment of a single pillar remains to mark a grave for this ancient civilization.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dragonblood_Ravager: Constructed from the scales and teeth of grand dragon Vyxia, her fiery blood still stains and heats the edge.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dragonbone_Helm_of_Sir_Da: Successful dragon knights boast few scars. The ones that get hit rarely live long.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dragonclaw_Hook: The claw from a black dragon's left toe. The only piece of the beast that survived an encounter with Pudge's voracious hunger.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dragonfire: Contains all of the items in the 'Dragonfire' set for Lina plus a loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dragonmaw: Dragonmaw is mighty even among the Named Swords. It's jagged teeth rip at even the strongest hides, laying bear the vulnerable flesh beneath.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dragons_Ascension: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Dragon's Ascension' set for Dragon Knight plus a loading screen:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dragonterror: Contains all of the items in the 'Dragonterror' set for Phantom Assassin plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Draining_Wight: A ward of uncommon origin, the Draining Wight draws its eerie power from the Nether Reaches, taking advantage of the imbalance that exists between different worlds. Part bone, part spirit, this ward has one foot in the corporeal realm, and one among the wights. It drains the lifeforce of its victim, leaving their corporeal bodies empty and vulnerable.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Drape_of_Foliate_Magery: While lesser druids draw upon blood and mana to work their arts, Nature's Prophet taps directly the heart of Verodicia's wrathsome will.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Drape_of_the_Flowering_Sh: Created in partnership with Hao, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dread_Ascendance: Contains the Dread Ascendance set for Doom, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dread_Requisition: Only an enchanter's forge can bring about such vile augmentations, but no sane enchanter would aid or trust a creature beholden to N'aix's awful desires. It was only with great difficulty N'aix was able to locate a disgraced enchanter's apprentice who held a useful interest in darker arts.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dread_Retribution: Through the eyes of the mad mask, Traxex glimpsed forgotten memories of her youth. But in addition to her own repressed terrors, the mask revealed much more--horrors glimpsed by different eyes in other times. Memories of brutality stretching into ages uncountable, mystically imprinting a murderous landscape across every corner of her mind. Now, even as she casts the mask aside, she must fight to overcome the most self-destructive impulses unleashed by the evils burned behind her eyes. In this maelstrom of loathing, her only recourse is vengeance... against any worthy victims that cross her path.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dreaded_Bravos_Cape: The sands of Halgalareh are all that remain of a vast empire of prismatic towers. To inhale them is to breathe fine shards of glass. So it is not secrecy alone that dictates the wearing of this colorful veil.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dreaded_Bravos_Guise: At night, the moon above Halgalreh's ruins casts an hallucinatory light that curdles the mind as surely as the blazing sun broils an uncovered skull throughout the day.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dreaded_Bravos_Scarf: When pursuing arcane leads in the desert ruins of Halgalareh, even an assassin can justify adopting a bit of the local color.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dreaded_Dreads: The braided nature of this hairstyle is said to symbolize one's tightly woven link to the ancestors.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dreadknight_Blade: The sword and spine of the Dreadknight were fused and displayed in order to set an example for those that would dare challenge Ostarion.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dreadknight_Cloak: The sigils lining this cloak were said to render the Dreadknight invincible.  Ostarion proved otherwise.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dreadknight_Crown: From what little remained of the Dreadknight's shattered form was made this crown, a fearsome symbol of Ostarion's reign.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dreadknight_Gauntlet: Carved from obsidian, lined in gold, and adorned with the skull of the Deadknight himself; Ostarion loves nothing more than to display his former rivals.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Dreadknight_Pauldron: Aided by a fierce magnosceros, the Dreadknight set upon Ostarion's kingdom intent on conquest.  Now their bones do little more than decorate his unliving foe.

Access to Player Profiles, Friend Leaderboards, Lifetime stats, Match History and Ranking Achievements

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Expired_Treasure_of_Vermi: You will need a <font color='#9da1a9'>Seal of Vermilion Renewal</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Expired_Treasure_of_the_C: A gnarled chest formed of a dark, still-living wood. The lock glows with cursed runes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Expired_Treasure_of_the_F: A strange and fragrant chest. The lock is of an unknown design and the contents are currently a mystery.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Expired_Treasure_of_the_M: A chest that seems mildly poisonous to the touch. The contents are unknown.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Expired_Treasure_of_the_S: A chest of magical items created by the community contributor Anuxi.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Exponent_of_the_Endless_S: Contains the Exponent of the Endless Stars set for Enigma, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Exquisite_Doubled_Axe_of_: Occasionally a target will be well-armored against more conventional blades.  Or they may be hiding behind a large door.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Eye_of_Avernus: The Font of Avernus can see through the mist.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Eye_of_Ixyxa: Distrustful especially of those he allows a measure of power or other favor, Ix'yxa sends an aspect of himself to watch over each cunning investment.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Eye_of_Lyralei: Created by the elements of nature to assist a hero in battle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Eye_of_Niuhi: Engrained within the beaten blade of the fisherman who first slew him lies the eye of Niuhi, a monster from the deep, long defeated but not forgotten.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Eye_of_Omoz: In the burning pits of the stygian waste, the sword sees all.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Eye_of_Skadi_Shell_Style_: This International 2017 reward enables an upgraded shell to be unlocked for Hermes the Hermit Crab in the style menu.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Eye_of_Thunderkeg: A handy creation of the Thunderkeg spirit to give vision to allies in the thick fog which surrounds them.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Eye_of_the_Beholder: Contains the Eye of the Beholder set for Medusa, including the loading screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Eye_of_the_Eyrie: A wizardly staff bearing the Skywrath symbol of clairvoyance.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Eye_of_the_Lost_Star: Created in partnership with Era, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Eye_of_the_Ozkavosh: Until its fall, none could escape the spying gaze of the First Dominion.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Eyes_of_Ardenok: Many magnoceroi believe the spirit of Ardenok, consort of the First Matriarch, refused passage through the Narrow Maze, and that for some unknown, terrible price, he can still be summoned to lend his strength from beyond the grave.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Eyes_of_Lucid_Torment:
The dreamer's eyes are opened to a world of anguish.

This item can be upgraded with the 'Lucid Torment Style Unlock' granted to players who complete at least 40 stars on the Path of the Protector.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Eztzhok_Blade: Bloodseeker invites cosmic disapproval, wielding demonic blades in the sight of his Twin Masters. Yet demons are no strangers to a gory thirst, and where skin is flayed from flesh, there is plenty of blood to go around.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Eztzhok_Blade_Bundle: Contains the Eztzhok Blades for Bloodseeker
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Eztzhok_Blade__OffHand: Bloodseeker invites cosmic disapproval, wielding demonic blades in the sight of his Twin Masters. Yet demons are no strangers to a gory thirst, and where skin is flayed from flesh, there is plenty of blood to go around.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FACEIT_League: FACEIT.com is an online platform for gamers which allows them to compete in completely automatized Dota2 tournaments, matchmaking and ladders every day for Dota2 Item & Hardware prizes! The best players from FACEIT can qualify for FPL and play with the best players in the world.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FACEIT_Pro_League: FACEIT Pro League is an elite community created by professional Dota2 players from Europe. Watch hundreds of games per month for free and witness the best players of Europe fight for a monthly prizepool. You can aswell qualify for FPL by playing at FACEIT Master League.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FACEIT_Pro_League_Europe: FACEIT Pro League Europe is an elite community created by professional Dota2 players from EU. FPL is also a development centre for young talented players and future champions. You can qualify for FPL by playing on Master and Diamond League on FACEIT every month.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FACEIT_Pro_League_North_A: FACEIT Pro League North America is an elite community created by professional Dota2 players from NA. FPL is also a development centre for young talented players and future champions. You can qualify for FPL by playing on Master and Diamond League on FACEIT every month.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FACTME_Dota_2_Online_Tour: The FACTME Dota 2 Online Tournaments is a round-robin competition where the top 4 teams will advance to the playoffs. Teams are competing for a prize pool of 1,000 Pesos!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FES_League_Championship_K: The top 16 teams from around the United Kingdom will compete in this new UK Dota 2 League to become champions!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FGCL_CIS_Open_Cup: Open tournament where over 500 teams will fight for the championship and a prize of $1000.  Bundle includes ticket and the Sovereign of the Woodlands set!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FGCL_CIS_Open_Cup_Ticket: Open tournament where over 500 teams will fight for the championship and a prize of $1000.  This ticket only gives you access to view games in the WPL CIS: Open Cup.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FGCL_CIS_Open_Cup_Ticket_: Open tournament where over 500 teams will fight for the championship and a prize of $1000.  This ticket only gives you access to view games in the WPL: CIS Open Cup.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FGCL_Championship_League: Top 32 winners in the group stages will be competing for a prize pool of $1000! The winners get a place in FGCL StarSeries. Includes an exclusive in-game HUD Skin: Reign of Maelrawn!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FGCL_Fight_Club_Promote_S: Eight invited professional teams and eight qualifying teams compete in Promote Season of Fight Club for $1,000!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FJBEG_Dota_2_Tournament: 32 Teams in Indonesia will play in this tournament for 500$ ! and Sponsored by Biggest Online Casino In Indonesia.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FJBEG_Online_Tournament_#: 64 Teams in Indonesia will play in online tournament for Rp 10.000.000 prize pool. Presented by biggest transaction gaming equipment facebook forum in Indonesia and powered by 9nagabet.com (sports & live casino) !
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Faceit_League_B: The second part of famous faceit league!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Faceless_Rex: In another time, in another place, perhaps Faceless Void would have rather carried items for heroes rather than become a hero himself. In another time, in another place, he might also have been a time-disrupting dinosaur. Who can say what other paths Faceless Void may have taken if given the chance...
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Faithful_Followers:
A joint effort between oft-rival factions, this pair of creatures was created to do exactly as they're told.
	This item will never be tradeable or purchasable on the marketplace.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Falconers_Design_Set: Includes all of the items in the 'Falconer's Design' set for Windranger:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Falcons_Rise: The Skywrath revere all avian species, and hold the falcon in particularly high esteem.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Falconside_Armor: Contains the Falconside Armor set for Windranger, including the loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fall_2016_Battle_Pass:
The Fall 2016 Battle Pass includes the Boston Major Compendium and gives you access to quests, exclusive treasures, token wagering, and more. The higher your Battle Level, the more rewards you'll earn.
	
	The pass and all treasure items will become tradeable after the standard Steam seven day cooldown after purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fall_2016_Battle_Pass_Emo: Unlocks The Fall 2016 Battle Pass emoticons
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fall_2016_Battle_Pass_Loa: Available only to Fall 2016 Battle Pass owners.
Available only to Fall 2016 Battle Pass owners.
Available only to Fall 2016 Battle Pass owners.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fall_2016_Champions_Cup_T: This ticket is proof that the owner has qualified for the Champions Cup.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fall_2016_Treasure_I: This treasure is only available to Fall 2016 Battle Pass owners.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fall_2016_Treasure_II: This treasure is only available to Fall 2016 Battle Pass owners.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fall_2016_Treasure_III__U: This treasure is only available to Fall 2016 Battle Pass owners.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fall_2016_Treasure_IV: This treasure is only available to Fall 2016 Battle Pass owners.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fallen_Sword: The sword that burns and is not consumed.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fallout_4_Announcer_Pack:
This pack replaces the Default announcer and the Mega-Kills announcer with the dry wit of everyone's favorite robotic butler, Mister Handy.
	
	Credits: Bethesda Softworks/Bethesda Game Studios/Stephen Russell
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Familiar_Woods: A trusted friend on a well-worn path.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Familiar_of_the_Great_Gre: As vicious as it is loyal, the familiar of the great grey is a powerful ally in any battle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Familiar_of_the_Soul_Keep: There are those who view the servitude of Necro'lic as worse than any fate faced by those that fall under its ruthless gaze.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Familiars_of_Glorious_Ins: Includes the Glorious Inspiration forge spirit ability icon
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fan_of_the_Royal_Butcher: Though the carnage may go on without end, there are those alive still who can recall when it began. Ah, to be young and in the employ of the bloody King Brandalon once more.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fancy_Kunkka_Shoes: You've never seen shoes like these before. Hand cobbled from a stock of long-forgotten quillboar leather, chic but practical for every-day wear, offered in men's and women's whole and half sizes. The price? Your blood.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fantasy_S2_Bronze_Telepor: A custom teleport effect given as a reward for placing third in a Fantasy Season 2 league.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fantasy_S2_Gold_Teleport: A custom teleport effect given as a reward for placing first in a Fantasy Season 2 league.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fantasy_S2_Silver_Telepor: A custom teleport effect given as a reward for placing second in a Fantasy Season 2 league.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fantasy_Season_1_Bronze_T: Prize for third place in a Fantasy Season 1 League
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fantasy_Season_1_Gold_Tro: Prize for winning a Fantasy Season 1 League
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fantasy_Season_1_Silver_T: Prize for second place in a Fantasy Season 1 League
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fantasy_Ticket_Season_1: This ticket will allow you to create a new Fantasy League or join an existing one in Fantasy Season 1.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fantasy_Ticket_Season_2: This ticket will allow you to create a new Fantasy League or join an existing one in Fantasy Season 2.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fantoccinis_Dilemma: Includes all of the items in the 'Fantoccini's Dilema' set for Rubick plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Faringame_League_Season_1: Best russian Far East teams compete for a 50000 ruble prize pool!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fashion_of_Yoskreth: The fashions of Yoskreth are not common in much of the rest of the world.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fashion_of_the_Scorching_: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Fashion of the Scorching Princess' set for Lina:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fatal_Bloom:
Unseen by Lesale in his urgent compounding, the orchid of his salvation was also host to the pulsing cocoon of a Fradjan moth.

Contains the Fatal Bloom set for Venomancer, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fatal_Blossom: Contains all of the items in the 'Fatal Blossom' item set for Death Prophet plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Father_of_the_Forest: Includes all of the items in the 'Father of the Forest' set for Nature's Prophet plus loading screen. The weapon includes an ambient particle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fathomless_Ravager: Contains the Fathomless Ravager set for Shadow Fiend.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Faulds_of_the_Gwimyeon_Wa: Speed is always the warrior's ally.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Favor_of_the_Shades: A gift from the shades of fortune! Will something valuable be inside?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Favors_of_the_Shamanic_Li: He that speaketh for the Shades casts his own light.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fearless_Impactor:
Though others may wear the ring and share in the service to his master's will, Barathrum alone answers only to the one who named him Imperator.

Contains the Elemental Imperator set for Spirit Breaker, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fearless_Impactor_Arms: Though others may wear the ring and share in the service to his master's will, Barathrum alone answers only to the one who named him Imperator.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fearless_Impactor_Belt: Though others may wear the ring and share in the service to his master's will, Barathrum alone answers only to the one who named him Imperator.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fearless_Impactor_Weapon: Though others may wear the ring and share in the service to his master's will, Barathrum alone answers only to the one who named him Imperator.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Feast_of_Abscession: Centuries ago, the Rumusque priestess Crella forged unbreakable links of hook and chain to bind the most powerful servants of the Dead God. But the Dead God's corruption grew too strong even for Crella's revered enchantments. Taken up with the rhythm of the Dirge, her chains abandoned their charge, turning instead to carry out the destruction of Crella's homeland at the Dead God's command. Now, their vile purpose long since served, the Chains of Abscession have sworn service to a new master... and the delights of butchery.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Feast_of_Abscession_Bundl:
Contains the 'Feast of Abscession' Arcana and the 'Skip to the Good Stuff!' Taunt for Pudge.

But the Dead God's corruption grew too strong even for Crella's revered enchantments. Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Feast_of_the_Gluttons_Lar:
Though the endless march of adventuring fools certainly disturbed the safety of her spiderlings, the constant supply of fresh treasure hunters did wonders for Arachnia's figure.

Contains the Feast of the Glutton's Larder set for Broodmother, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Feathered_Mantle_of_the_A: There is power yet in these old bones.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Feathered_Naginata: A light spear, balanced for quick slashes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Featherfall: Arrows of a feather flock together. Constructed from strong and resilient harpy feathers, this set of Featherfall is a fine upgrade to Windranger's look.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Featherfall_Bow: A colorful bow adorned with tough harpy feathers is just what a feisty girl like Lyralei needs for fabulous mega-kills!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Featherfall_Cloak: A breezy, flowing cloak is just what one needs to look good on a hunting trip.  Particularly if your prey might be hunting you right back.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Featherfall_Locks: Hair tied up and out of the way, she tops it off with a feathery headscarf for a breezy, carefree, I-just-shot-you-in-the-face look.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Featherfall_Quiver: Made of finest rumble-hide, this low-hanging quiver of feathery arrows is ready for action!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Featherfall_Spaulders: Designed to camouflage her outline and confuse attackers, these shoulders of tough harpy feathers offer protection against whirling blades.  This is sure to turn some heads.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Featherhutch: Having grown tired of her dilapidated chicken hutch, Babka the Bewitcher cast an enchantment to spruce it up and give it some life. She should have made sure there wasn't a chicken inside before she cast the spell.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Feathers_of_the_Vermillio:
'Neath vermillion plates
The shifting form
Of the star
Reborn.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Featherswing: Includes all of the items in the 'Featherswing' set for Windranger plus a loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Federal_League_Season_1: The first season of the Federal League allows teams in Europe to compete in different divisions to become champions!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Female_Dota_2_Southeast_A: A three month long league with a single-elimination BO3 playoffs for the top 4 teams. FSL is open to female Dota 2 teams that play on the Southeast Asian server.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Femur_Thrasher: A sharp, cracked femur of some unidentifiable sea-beast.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fengyun_Tournament: This year's Fengyun Tournament features grassroots teams competing against top Asian Dota 2 powerhouses for a prize pool of 100,000 RMB.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fengyun_Tournament__ADMIN: This year's Fengyun Tournament features grassroots teams competing against top Asian Dota 2 powerhouses for a prize pool of 100,000 RMB.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ferocious_Heart: Includes all of the items in the 'Ferocious Heart' set for Ursa plus a loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ferocious_Toxicant: Includes all of the items in the 'Ferocious Toxicant' set for Venomancer plus a loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ferrum_Chiroptera_Head: Long past time evil takes its fill, the feast goes on forevermore.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fervent_Conscript:
As the young orphan outgrew adolescence and his mastery of the Turstarkuri scrolls improved, he became eager to test his blades and begin his longed-for crusade to rid the world of magic, ultimately finding first opportunity as a volunteer in the failed defense of Bakhwarren.

Contains the Fervent Conscript set for Anti-Mage, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fervent_Conscript_Style_U: This Winter 2017 Battle Pass reward enables an upgraded style to be unlocked on the 'Fervent Conscript' set for Anti-Mage through the style menu. You can use this item multiple times to unlock styles on all of the items in the set.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Festive_Fireworks: There's nothing more festive than explosions!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fetish_of_the_Father_Spir: When it comes to dazzling fetishes, the Father Spirit knows best.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fetters_of_Omniscience: Fate knows its true course. None can struggle against it without provoking a commensurate response.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Feudal_Mace_of_Chivalry: Prove your chivalry by smashing enemies in the face with this powerful weapon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FezzleFeez_the_Magic_Carp: Fezzle-Feez, like most smeevils, has no floor on which to spread his magic carpet, therefore he unrolls it in mid-air.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fiery_Soul_of_the_Slayer: It has often been said that Lina's hair was touched by fire, though few know the truth of this claim.  In Lina's youth, as her natural talents first began to smoke and smolder it was her fiery hair that told the tale of the storm to come.  With time and training, her skill and control of the flame was enough to suppress the searing display.  Yet on occasion, when her ire grows and tempers flare, the full measure of Lina's burning spirit threatens to unleash its wrath.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fiery_Ward_of_Eki_Bukaw: With this fiery ward, no secrets are safe, no location hidden, no weakness unexposed.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fin_Kings_Charm: Though once used by the Fin King's arcanists to dispatch his foes to the underwater realm, the core technique of the charm has since been lost, and much of its potency along with it.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fin_Kings_Charm_of_Eminen: Brought into battle by the Demon Witch for the first time during The International 2014, this curious weapon introduced the first custom Hex effect, changing the form inflicted upon Lion's victims from jumping frog to flopping fish.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fin_of_the_First_Spear: For centuries, attempting to don this helm was a rite of passage to all who became First Spear of the Flood. In most cases, it was a short lesson in humility. In others, however, it meant a trip to the healer or even the grave. For one to wear the helm in battle like legends of old signals to Slithereen everywhere that a new age of strength is now upon them.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Final_Fantasy_Type0_HD_bu: Contains Chocobo courier, Watching Moogle ward and loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Finblade: Kunkka's ship cleaves the waves as easily as Finblade cleaves his enemies. Kunkka revels in the iridescent play of light given off by dashing spray and liberated souls alike.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fine_Bone_Bracers: Bracers crafted from the fine bone of some alien beast.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Finnish_Dota_League: The first season of the Finnish Dota 2 League provides Finnish teams a platform to develop Finnish eSports to the next level!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fintail_Reef_Kyte: Astride a fintail reef kyte and protected against the crush by an enchanted helm, the moon rider serves as Selemene's champion and emissary in forging undersea alliances and keeping creatures of the deep at bay.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FireBlessed_Mail_of_the_D: Includes all of the items in the 'Fire-Blessed Mail of the Drake' set for Dragon Knight:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fire_Dragon_of_Doom: Includes all of the items in the 'Fire Dragon of Doom' set for Dragon Knight:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fire_of_the_Exiled_Ronin: The flames of the Ronin burn hot against all who oppose him.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fireborn_Odachi: Forged in the fires that bubbled up from the sea on the night your homeland sank beneath the waves!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Firebreather_of_the_Voyag: Carried mainly for show, Kunkka does find Firebreather's flintlock a reliable means of lighting his pipe in inclement weather.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fireflight_Scion:
From the ashes, she rises.

Contains the Fireflight Scion set for Lina, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fires_of_Vashundol: Contains all of the items in the 'Fires of Vashundol' set for Doom plus ambient particles and loading screen. Created in partnership with Evil Geniuses, who receive a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fires_of_the_Volcanic_Gua: Contains the Fires of the Volcanic Guard set for Ember Spirit, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Firestarter: Contains all of the items in the 'Firestarter' set for Batrider plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FirstGameTV_Dota_2_Cup_To: Contains the FirstGame Dota 2 Cup Ticket and the Rhinoceros Order set for Sven
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_First_Arrival_Dota_2_Tour: A double elimination tournament where teams will compete for treasure keys in Dota 2!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_First_Night_of_the_Summer: Contains the First Night of the Summer Child set for Enchantress, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_First_of_the_Flood: Even for those Slithereen Guard skilled enough to be counted amongst the Centurion elite, few could hope to be called for induction into the ranks of the Flood. Slardar's initiation at a young age and his rapid rise to position of First Spear suggest he has barely skimmed the surface of his true depth.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fishing_Halberd: Off the coast near the village of Pole are fish large enough to eat a man in a single bite.  Against such a beast, a spear simply will not do.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fishy_Frillhawk: In Dark Reef Prison, Slark kept too low a profile to ever be called a trendsetter. He figured nobody noticed his radical look. But as soon as he had broken out, the remaining inmates began to imitate this finny style.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fistful_of_Snowballs: Just when they least expect it... Snowball fight!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fists_of_Axe_Unleashed: Lost, alone, and without his precious namesake in a strange land... Axe is exactly where he wants to be!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flail_Sleek: Many lives has this mighty flail ended.  Many skulls has this mighty flail pulped.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flail_of_the_Death_Charge:
Your iron flail shall break them.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flail_of_the_Great_Elder: The title of Brewmaster is won in combat. This ancient weapon is also passed with the title.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flail_of_the_Iron_Will: Shimmering with an elder power, one swing is enough to dim even the stoutest heart.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flail_of_the_Violent_Prec: And here Rigwarl thought \"Crystalback\" had a nice ring to it...
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flame_Bat: The Flame Bat's blood is as thick as tar and burns just as hot.The rider taps the creature's blood, harvesting it for his own fiery needs.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flamestitched_Suitings_Ba: Do you know how hard it is to find a fireproof bandanna?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flamestitched_Suitings_Se: Includes all of the items in the 'Flamestitched Suitings' set for Batrider:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flamestitched_Suitings_Wr: You mix it right, the world burns.  You mix it wrong, it burns a bit brighter!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flaming_Scepter_of_Ancest: By rights it came to Aggron, and by luck it happened to be on fire!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flare_of_the_Mechanised_P: Created in partnership with June, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flared_Wooden_Crest: A simple, but decorative crest of wood. Designed to provide protection from the hated axe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flares_of_the_Solar_Divin: The heat of the eastern wastes is said to be extraordinary.  One must dress appropriately.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flight_of_Epiphany: Only tentatively could Dragonus send tendrils of mystic thought out in search of the boundaries of his power's connection to the Skywrath scion, for a single false step would expose him and doom his efforts forever. It was with a careful, quiet joy that Dragonus discovered there are grey areas in his oath to the Nest of Thorns, and much like the emotions behind the creation of Scree'auk's Talon, loyalty to the progenitors is powerful haven for certain actions of ambiguous intent.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flight_of_the_Marauding_P: Contains the Flight of the Marauding Pyro set for Batrider, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flight_of_the_Sparrowhawk: Includes all of the items in the 'Flight of the Sparrowhawk' set for Windranger:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flight_of_the_Valkyrie: This bundle contains all of the items for the 'Flight of the Valkyrie' set for Legion Commander.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flightless_Dod: Fleet of foot and fast of feather, it's Flightless Dod (and friends)!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flightless_Fury: Includes all of the items in the 'Flightless Fury' set for Vengeful Spirit plus a loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Floathide_Bands_of_the_Sh: Never coordinated well enough to swim with any stealth or grace, Ogre Magi relied on pilfered shipwright's tools and a bit of luck to survive a failed raid on Deshom Bay.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Floathide_Belt_of_the_Sho: Never coordinated well enough to swim with any stealth or grace, Ogre Magi relied on pilfered shipwright's tools and a bit of luck to survive a failed raid on Deshom Bay.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flockhearts_Gamble: Lost, separated from her family, and saddled with the impossibly-stupid ogre responsible for it all, Flockheart the Firelark has no choice but to trust that the Goddess of Luck will help her survive the trials standing between her and a reunion with her flock. After all, it was the Goddess herself who tasked the Ogre Magi with standing watch over said flock in the first place. What the cluck was she thinking?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flockhearts_Gamble_Bundle:
Lost, separated from her family, and saddled with the impossibly-stupid ogre responsible for it all, Flockheart the Firelark has no choice but to trust that the Goddess of Luck will help her survive the trials standing between her and a reunion with her flock. After all, it was the Goddess herself who tasked the Ogre Magi with standing watch over said flock in the first place. What the cluck was she thinking?
	
	This bundle contains the Flockheart's Gamble Arcana for Ogre Magi, as well as arcana Voice Pack.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Floodmask: The unimaginable pressure of the ocean's deepest chasms is pent up in this sturdy bit of salvage. Open the hatch and stand aside!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flopjaw: Splish-splash! Plip-plop! There's nothing like the splattery patter of finny feet to let you know your treasure is secure inside a Boxhound, and safely on its way.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flourishing_Lodestar: In the shade of the first trees, water runs clear, and the earth radiates a gentle warmth. The spirits of the verdant wild coil about, endlessly mending, and eternally twisting old life into new. From the boughs of these elder saplings was carved the Lodestar, a tool to aid nature's benevolent servants so that they may guide, heal, and preserve all that must be held dear.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flow_of_the_Flowering_Sha: Created in partnership with Hao, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flower_Staff_of_the_Peace: A Candral-Flower plucked from the heart of the Endless Copse.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flowering_Shade: Includes all of the items in the \"Flowering Shade\" set for Spectre plus a loading screen. Created in partnership with Hao, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flowering_Shade_Loading_S: Created in partnership with Hao, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flowering_Treant: What appears to be a beautiful blossom is in fact the motile form of a cordyceps fungus which has infested the poor plant. It is still under the control of Nature's Prophet, but the ultimate outcome for the infected treant is far from pleasant.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flowersong_Tempest: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Flowersong Tempest' set for Windranger plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flowing_Entropy: Contains all of the items in the 'Flowing Entropy' set for Spectre plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fluted_Guard_of_the_Moon_: An emblem of honor, worn with grace but never lightly.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fluted_Guard_of_the_Sword: The sheer size and weight of this piece were scoffed at until Sven used the shoulder spikes to impale an attacking ogre along the Feral Road.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fluttering_Cache: This treasure is only available to Fall 2015 Compendium owners.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fluttering_Staff: So gentle was the prophet that when he pulled the branch to make this staff, the butterflies upon the leaves remained. Includes ambient particle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fluttering__Bonus_Cache: This special cache contains rare items from the Fluttering Cache, as well as additional levels for the Fall Season 2015 Compendium.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Flux_Dota_2_Tournament: Flux Dota 2 Tournament is a Dota 2 Competition consisting of 64 teams competing for a prize pool of over $950!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Focal_Resonance: Within the Violet Archives are blueprints for weapons that many would say should remain forgotten. Such a weapon is the Focal, which resonates with, and channels the wearer's psyche into a blast of piercing power.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Focus_of_Resonant_Vibranc: To focus and bend the wild, unseen energies to one's whim is a skill few possess!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Forbidden_Knowledge:
As Ethreain's rebellious subjects bound him, they shackled his magic tome upon his back and a blinding crown upon his head to ensure he could never again read from those dark pages.

Contains the Forbidden Knowledge set for Lich, including the Loading Screen.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Force_Staff: Sometimes a little push is all you need.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Force_of_the_Magus: Captured in this staff is a puzzle that not even Rubick has solved. He passes idle moments attempting to unlock its mysteries. From time to time, hoping for insight, he casts it upon an enemy, and lets them hang enthralled in its enigmas.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Forest_Hermit_Set: Includes all the items in the \"Forest Hermit\" set for Earthshaker.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Foretellers_Oath: Contains the Foreteller's Oath set for Witch Doctor, including the Loading Screen

An iron mask for an iron will.

These items commemorate the release of Valve's documentary, Free to Play, and were created in partnership with Fear, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Forgemasters_Hammer: The only day Axe declared defeat was the day he tried to forge a weapon with an axe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Forgemasters_Mask: The warriors of the Red Mist are not only superb fighters, but also master smiths. Each grunt is expected to craft his own sword and his own shield. Should his war tools fail him on the battlefield, the grunt has only his own hands to blame.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Forgotten_Tactician: Contains the Forgotten Tactician set for Dark Seer, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Forlorn_Descent: Contains the Forlorn Descent item set and Loading Screen for Undying
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Form_of_the_Atniw: No foe shall stand against the true form!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Form_of_the_Blood_Moon: Banehallow often takes solace in the company of any fellow afflicted he might encounter in his wanderings. Not all, however, find the company of their own kind so agreeable.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Form_of_the_Great_Grey: A form out of your worst nightmares.  The wolf is at your door.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Form_of_the_Great_Grey_Se: A wolf in warrior's clothing.  This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Form of the Great Grey' set for Lycan:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Form_of_the_Onyx_Grove: Among the northern pine did Sylla discover the darkness of the Onyx Grove, where creatures both fierce and strange gather to quarrel.  In time, the lone druid adapted his own form to join in the fray.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Formed_Alloy_Apron:
If you're going bring in a dragon to help you mix alloys you'd best become fireproof!

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.

Invaluable and nigh indestructible, it can take up to fourteen months to mix materials to concoct just one pound of shadeglass.

Keeping a splash of dragon drool on hand is never a bad idea, assuming you can find the right mix of alloys to store it!

A shadeglass eyepiece is a perfect addition to any laboratory.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fortune_of_Three_Spirits_: Contains all of the items in the 'Strength of the Demon Stone', 'Flames of Prosperity', and the 'Gifts of Fortune' for the Three Spirits. Also includes a bonus loading screen and HUD.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fortune_of_the_Five_House: Once he had gained mastery over his spectral kin and returned to Ashkavor, Grimstroke claimed as final prize a brush imbued with magic from the most ancient and venerated bloodlines of his people, forged in the early days of the city before the advent of the Ascended Ones.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fortunes_Tout: Few can resist the call of this purry peddler.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Forward_to_victory: 32 teams from the CIS Region will compete for the $10 prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Forward_to_victory_cup#2: 32 teams from the CIS will battle for a prize of 100$
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Foulfell_Corruptor: Contains the Foulfell Corruptor set for Terrorblade, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Foulfell_Shard: A fragment of black crystal that radiates corrupting, abyssal energy. It throbs with the voiceless hatred of demons imprisoned within.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FourFangs_the_Swordbreake: The fangs of this fierce blade bite deep into your foe's bared weapon!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fowl_Omen: Contains the Fowl Omen set for Necrophos
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fowl_of_the_Stormcharge_D: Astride the focused storm, Disruptor stalks the boundaries of battle, ready to strike down his enemies and lead his tribe's return to a place of distinction and honor.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FoxBox_Open: FoxBox Open is the first open online tournament from FoxBox, where 32 teams will compete for a prize pool of 15000 rubles.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fractal_Shard_of_Inner_Ab: Deep in the hell of Hell, Terrorblade lay bound behind fractal walls, sentenced to an eternity of twisted contemplation. He stared long into the reflection of his own worst self. And long did his worst self stare into him. Now they rise together, a single entity more powerful than ever before.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fractured_Envoy: Contains all of the items in the 'Fractured Envoy' item set for Arc Warden plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fragbite_Masters: 32 teams compete in the Fragbite Masters which is an online tournament with a $30,900 prize pool for Dota 2.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fragbite_Masters_2014: Fragbite Masters 2014 consists of twelve professional teams competing alongside a bracket open to amateur teams for a prize pool of over 200,000 SEK.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fragment_of_Radiant_Ore: No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. This treasure contains full item sets.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fraidy_Jack:
Fraidy Jack is full of fright
	Stealing treats all through the night
	Always waiting, always there,
	You cannot escape his stare.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frankfurt_Major_2015: Who will emerge victorious? Witness the world's top teams battle at The Frankfurt Major 2015.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frankfurt_Major_2015_Open: Witness teams from all around the world compete for a place at The Frankfurt Major 2015.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Free_Treasure_Redemption: Right click and redeem this item to exchange it for a free treasure of your choice.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Free_to_Play_Collectors_P:
These items commemorate the release of Valve's 'Free to Play' documentary. A portion of the purchase will go toward the players featured in the film - Danil 'Dendi' Ishutin, Clinton 'Fear' Loomis and Benedict 'hyhy' Lim.

The bundle includes all of the items in the 'Forge of Iron Will' set for Sven, the 'Murder of Crows' set for Pudge, the 'Crown of Hells' set for Doom and the exclusive 'Wide Angle' Ward, 'Filmtail' Courier and 'Depth of Field' HUD:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Free_to_Play_Courier: This courier commemorates the release of Valve's documentary 'Free to Play'.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Free_to_Play_HUD: This HUD commemorates the release of Valve's documentary 'Free to Play'.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Free_to_Play_Ward: This ward commemorates the release of Valve's documentary 'Free to Play'.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Freestyle_Dota_1x1: Players from Kramatorsk will fight for a prize.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Friend_of_the_West: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Friend of the West' set for Beastmaster:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Friendly_Hardcore_Gaming_: Friendly Gaming Community. Open Registration Amateurs Only
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FroggedTV_Cup: French tournament organized by the FroggedTV and going on all the year with Major System.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frost_Avalanche: Some say the garment began as the wedding gown of an ancient queen.  Others say it was once a battle cloak of a frost ogre. In truth, the enchanted fabric is as malleable as an avalanche, and can mold itself into various forms. This form has attracted a lone wolf pup, who has now become a hardy and loyal companion.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frost_Avalanche_Bundle: Contains the 'Frost Avalanche' arcana for Crystal Maiden.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frost_Owls_Beacon: Little hope remains to those lost in the frozen north, yet it is said that those able to summon an elusive Frost Owl will always find their way to safety.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frost_Shard_Armlets: Coming through! Even Juggernaut will leap to avoid the icy edges of these lethal armlets.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frost_Shard_Crown: Morphling spent eternities travelling space in the form of ice. Morphling knows ice. You know that if Morphling wears a crown of ice, it is a serious crown.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frost_Shard_Pauldrons: The glitter of the interstellar ice that once bedizened Morphling, decks his shoulders now as he surges to and fro across the field of battle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frost_Spikes: A playful crop of spikes that says 'I'm killing you and having fun doing it.' Includes a frost-tinged cloak to complete the image.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frost_Spikes_FIXUP_BUNDLE: Use this bundle to unpack the Frost Spikes and Ice Burst Cloak items. These were previously one item, but have been broken into two.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frost_Touched_Cleaver: A deep winter chill touches this cleaver for Tusk!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostbitten_Cloak_of_the_: Ice is nice!  Except in cases of frostbite, so stay warm in this downy cape.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frosthaven_Consumables_Bu: Contains a full set of consumables for both normal Dota and the Frosthaven special event.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frosthaven_Emoticon: Unlocks the Frosthaven Emoticon for winning the game mode.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frosthaven_Loading_Screen: The Grand Magus and his fanatical mob advance on Frosthaven, intent on uprooting the original Frostivus tree and snatching the source of arcane power from which all the world's holiday presents originate. To stop the mad magus, five heroes must rise to the defense of the ancient tree—and fight to save the very spirit of Frostivus itself.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frosthaven__Festive_Firew: There's nothing more festive than explosions!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frosthaven__Pile_of_Snowb: Enjoy a bold, rocky center with a packed-ice crust!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frosthaven__Tree_Decorati: Who knew a few twinkling lights could be so deadly?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostheart_Wyvern: Contains the Frostheart set for Winter Wyvern, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Raider_Axe: The blacksmithing skill of the Frostiron Tribe has kept many a foe at bay.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Raider_Cape: As Ymir wandered the great northern wilderness, he spent time among the Frostiron Tribe.  Upon his departure, he was given gifts to remember them by.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Raider_Fist: Deceptively light yet incredibly durable, this glove was gifted to Tusk with the hope that it might ensure Ymir's safe return.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Raider_Helm: Denizens of the northern sea, the Frostiron Tribe are a proud people with a rich history.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Raider_Set: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Frostiron Raider' set for Tusk:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Raider_Shield: During his stay with the Frostiron Tribe, Ymir tried his hand at crafting armor.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Raider_Tusks: Masters of metals, the artisans of the Frostiron Tribe crafted steel tusks for Ymir as a symbol of his bravery.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Sorceress_Brooc: The brooch is made of glacial sapphire carved by the artisans of the Frostiron tribe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Sorceress_Cape: A tribe unknown to much of the world, the Frostiron are able to weave fabrics of incredible durability and warmth.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Sorceress_Cuffs: As fleeting spring came to the icy north, Ymir set off into the wilderness.  The warm seasons passed, and when winter returned so did he, bringing with him gifts and tales of a hidden tribe living near the coast.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Sorceress_Pads: The pads are deceptively durable, able to deflect even the strongest blow.  Such is the skill of the Frostiron Tribe that they remain as light as a snowflake.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Sorceress_Set: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Frostiron Sorceress' set for Crystal Maiden:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostiron_Sorceress_Staff: The cool glow of an uncut glacial sapphire symbolizes the icy resolve of the Frostiron Tribe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostivus_2017_Treasure: No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. This treasure is full of unique Frostivus sets for your favorite heroes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostivus_2018_Baby_Rosha: He may look fearsome, but this little guy is sweet as can be.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostivus_2018_Treasure_I: The first of two Frostivus-themed treasures coming this winter. This treasure is full of unique Frostivus sets for your favorite heroes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostivus_2019_Treasure: No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. This treasure is full of unique Frostivus sets for your favorite heroes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostivus_Consumables_Bun: Contains a full set of Frostivus consumables for Dota.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostivus_Gift__Naughty: A gift for saving Frostivus from the Greevils! What could be inside? It is a mystery. This gift looks like a Greevil sat on it or maybe chewed it up.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostivus_Gift__Nice: A gift for saving Frostivus from the Greevils! What could be inside? It is a mystery. This particular gift looks to be in excellent condition.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostivus_HUD_Skin: A chill fills the air as the snows blanket the cold ground.  The time of Frostivus comes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frostivus_Treasure_Key: Used to open locked <font color='#9da1a9'>Treasure Chests</font>. Double click or right-click the key in your backpack and select the chest you want to open.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frosty_Treasure_of_Frosti: You will need <font color='#9da1a9'>Frostivus 2013 Treasure Key</font> to open this chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Beware! At the end of <font color='#9da1a9'>January 12, 2014</font> this chest will crumble into useless snowflakes. This chest contains one of several mysterious new items:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frozen_Feather_Set: Includes all of the items in 'Frozen Feather' set for Crystal Maiden:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frozen_Formation: If you're spotted, it would be in your best interest not to freeze!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frozen_Star: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Frozen Star' set for Lich:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frozen_Stein_of_the_Bar_B: There's always time for a frosty mug!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frozen_Touch: There is cold wisdom in the core of winter.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Frull: What strange beast is this? Why, it's Frull--faithful four- footed freighter of mercantile wares. She may be a beast but she's also a lady, and your goods are never a burden to her!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_FullBore_Bonanza:
Of all the memories from his homeland that Kardel Sharpeye revels in during rare quiet nights, tales from the midsummer carnivals and their requisite target galleries are first to pass his lips. At least, they would be, were any of his folk around with which he might share the tale.

Immortal items cannot be traded or marketed through The International 2018, but can still be gifted once.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fundeavour_Christmas_Tour: 32 team will fight each other in a fun environment to celebrate Christmas together. Visit our website to know more.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Funereal_Dress_of_the_Bon: Far-seeing prophets who see anything other than Death are merely fooling themselves. Death Prophet knows how every occasion ends, and thus her attire is always appropriate.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fungal_Lord_Set: Includes all of the items in the 'Fungal Lord' set for Nature's Prophet:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Furious_Rune: When is a rune a sword, and a sword a rune?  This is not a question you worry about when Sven swings this at your head.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Furstole_of_the_Shadowcat: A stole created from the skin and pelt of the shadowcat.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Fury_of_the_Bloodforge: Contains the Fury of the Bloodforge set for Bloodseeker
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Furyblade: A thousand lives it claimed before it shattered, and a thousand more it shall claim after!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Furyblade__OffHand: A thousand lives it claimed before it shattered, and a thousand more it shall claim after!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Furyblades__Pair: Pack includes both the main and off-hand Furyblade.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_G1_Champions_League_Seaso: The 5th G-1 Championship will feature an online qualifier to select the top Western team for a paid flight to the LAN finals in China to face teams like iG, LGD, DK and Orange. The Asia qualifiers will also use a prelim system to compete for spots at the LAN finals. The prize pool exceeds $53,000.

The Fifth Season of the G-1 Championship league will feature an online qualifier to select the top Western team for a paid flight to the LAN finals in China to face teams like iG, LGD, DK and Orange. The Asia qualifiers will also use a prelim system to compete for spots at the LAN finals. The prize pool will exceed last season's $53,000.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_G1_Championship_League: The G-1 Championship League, hosted by 17173 Games, is the first Dota 2 tournament in China. Exciting matches await with teams like iG, LGD and DK competing for a prize pool of $50,000.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_G1_Championship_League__A: The G-1 Championship League, hosted by 17173 Games, is the first Dota 2 tournament in China. Exciting matches await with teams like iG, LGD and DK competing for a prize pool of $50,000.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_GBG_DOTA2_Madness: We organize weekly and monthly leagues in DOTA2. The platform that we use is a new platform that aims to automate the tournament process and help players focus on the most important thing, their game.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_GCCSL_Cup_Lan_#1: Twelve of the best teams in the Leningrad region compete for a grand prize of 16,000 Rubles!

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gift_of_the_Sea_Head: Crowned with ambition and innate knowledge of the depths, Morphling wears these shimmering scales with eldritch pride.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gift_of_the_Sea_Shoulders: Who can say no to such a glorious gift of strength and power?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gifted_Jester: Contains the Gifted Jester set for Rubick, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gifts_of_the_Heavenly_Gua: Includes all of the items in the 'Gifts of the Heavenly Guardian' set for Mirana plus the loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gifts_of_the_Shadowcat_Se: Includes all of the items in the 'Gifts of the Shadowcat' set for Drow Ranger:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gigabyte_Esports_Tourname: Watch the best Dota 2 teams from South-East Asia battle it out for the $2,000 prize pool and to earn their spot in the GEST Challenge.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gigabyte_Premier_League_S: Gigabyte in partnership with DotaTalk proudly brings you the Gigabyte Premier league. It features Southeast Asia's finest teams as they compete for a total prize pool of $1,500.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gigabyte_Windforce_Dota_2: The Gigabyte Windforce Cup features the best teams in South-East Asia competing for a total prize pool of $3,000.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gilded_Falcon_Bow: An ancient bow of oak and iron, gilded with the golden feathers of a sacred falcon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gilded_Falcon_Cloak: This beautiful emrald cloak is embroidered with the ancient sidgel of the gilded falcon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gilded_Falcon_Helm: A helm of great strength and beauty, this armor of the gilden falcon offers a special kind of security, protecting both the wearer's head and identity.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gilded_Falcon_Quiver: As the diving bird of prey has talons, so the archer has arrows.  And many are the arrows that can be held in the quiver of the gilded falcon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gilded_Falcon_Wings: Like the angvols of old legends, these golden falcon wings speed Windranger's flight into battle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gilded_Mark_of_the_Harusp: Upon the shoulder sits a coiled snake, wrought in gold. The seers of Serpent Clan often read the future in the entrails of their lowly kin.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gilded_Valor: Celebrate The International with a gilded, posed hero statue that can be equipped to customize your base.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gimlek_Decanter: If the forgemaster of Grod had known his greatest blending of the mystical and martial arts--presented as holy tribute to, and bearing the royal sigil of, the King of Grod himself--would one distant day fall into the hands of a filthy ogre... Well, he likely wouldn't have bothered at all.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Girdle_of_the_Dark_Wraith: In hushed voices, they whisper of lessons learned in a distant land known as Lordran. What can it mean?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Girdle_of_the_Nimble_Edge: An assassin must have speed and cunning, yes, but also a backup blade for when things do not go to plan.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Girdpiece_of_the_Acolyte_: To enter Claszureme, one must study the workings of Clasz...and such endeavors require one gird oneself well.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Girls_Wars_2: Girls Wars is an exclusively Dota 2 tournament for female players. 12 teams from CIS and Europe will compete for the title of best female team.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Girth_of_the_Swordmaster: Few would argue that keeping their thigh intact outweighs whatever discomfort this armor may cause.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Glacial_Magnolia: Contains the Glacial Magnolia set for Crystal Maiden, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Glacier_Duster_Set:
Strike a chill in your enemies!

These items were created in partnership with ixmike88, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Glacier_of_Eldritch_Ice: Drowned but not dead, deep in the Black Pool, the cold hatred in Lich's heart froze the water around him. These ice-shards, formed of evil, hold a hatred that will never melt.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gladiators_Revenge: Includes all of the items in the 'Gladiator's Revenge' set for Pudge:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gladius_Dota_2: South American teams compete in Gladius for $150!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gladius_TGD2: There are many players, but only one Champion of TGD2!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gladys_the_LightBearing_M: Ezalor keeps the Light; Gladys keeps Ezalor.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Glaive_of_Oscilla: Each orb on its own, when far removed from the other two, seemed nothing more than a mundane -- albeit perfectly shaped and polished -- stone sphere. Yet when the three stones were brought within proximity of one another, they began to vibrate so violently as to break the bones of anyone holding one. When a clever tinkerer devised mechanical means to bring the stones within a few paces of each other, the resulting shockwave left him and his hapless apprentice bleeding from the ears, and the stones nowhere to be found. It was only after they were much later recovered by the Aeol Drias that a more effective means of harnessing the power of the stones was discovered.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Glaive_of_the_Dark_Moon_S: The Dark Moon faithful consist of former scholars, laborers, orphans, and thieves. One may have served as magistrate of a city, another spilled blood as a warlord in the wilds. They have walked all imaginable paths to find Selemene. In her service, the trials and tragedies of the past matter not. They worship the Goddess together, guardians of the Nightsilver Woods.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Glaive_of_the_Hidden_Tale: With this three-bladed glaive, Nortrom ensures a silence that will never be broken.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Glaive_of_the_Mage_Slayer: Brutality defined many of the early weapons used by the Anti-Mage.
Brutality defined many of the early weapons used by the Anti-Mage.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Glaive_of_the_Reef_Kyte_R: Astride a fintail reef kyte and protected against the crush by an enchanted helm, the moon rider serves as Selemene's champion and emissary in forging undersea alliances and keeping creatures of the deep at bay.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Glaives_of_Final_Utteranc: Includes custom ability icons when equiped.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Glaives_of_the_Mage_Slaye: Pack includes both the main and off-hand Glaive of the Mage Slayer.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Glare_of_the_Tyrant: In seeking to further augment his already vast powers by consuming those of another such as himself, Ethreain learned well from Anhil's mistake--the head alone will do.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Glaves_of_the_Crescent_Mo: Glaves as sharp as moon beams cut swaths through her enemies. Ribboned by a pair of glossamar wings, they fly true and far.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Glazov_Cup: Players from Udmurtia and the CIS will play in house league
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Glimmer_of_the_Sacred_Hun: Contains the Glimmer of the Sacred Hunt set for Drow, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Glimmerdark_Shield:
This shield's first bearer thought he had gained immortality in battle. Until the second bearer's magic began to flow.

+20 Strength
+20 Agility
+20 Intelligence

Required Level: 21Active: Gleam
Gain Immunity to physical damage, but receive +100% magic damage. Lasts 6 seconds.

BONUS HEALTH REGEN: 80
BONUS ARMOR: 40
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Global_Amateur_tournament: 32 amateur teams will compete for a prize fund of 35,000 rubles. Unique group stage, teams worthy, worthy of the prize fund. Let there be war!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Global_Grand_Masters_by_P: 12 total teams will fight in this event to claim the $50.000 total prize pool. 8 team will be invited to the closed qualifier 4 will survive and face against the 4 directly invited team.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Global_eSports_Cup_LAN_Fi: Game Show Global eSports Cup is the first of three seasons with a prizepool of 1.000.000 USD. All regions battle in various stages until 8 teams meet eachother in the Game Show Studio LAN Vilnius. The best 4 will move on to fight on Dreamhack Moscow to enter the Grand Final for 250.000 USD
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gloom_Dota_Season_3: 16 semi-pro teams will participate in the third season of Gloom Dota for a total prize pool of 3000 Rubles!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gloomblade: Beware the gloom, for it is ever the friend an assassin's ally.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gloombob: \"Ok. Listen up, new guy. Jex says you can pull your weight while he's away. He better not be wrong. For your sake. And, no, I don't care what your real name is. I'm not gonna learn how to say it anyway.\"
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gloried_Horn_of_Druud: Encorselled by Elder Greyhoofs at the Clanfounding, a single note from this horn can call forth the great hordes of Druud to do battle at the end of all times. Bradwarden the Warrunner and vanguard of the Druud clans protects the horn and will, at the appointed hour, summon his brothers and sisters to make a final apocalyptic war.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gloves_of_Retribution: Those who stand against the Skywrath can expect no mercy when Dragonus has them in his grip.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gloves_of_the_Admirable_A: Fine white gloves of silk. Noble clothing like this serves to set the Captain above his crew and to also motivate them with the promise of hard-earned wealth.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gloves_of_the_Crested_Can:
A gauntlet for the sword hand, a mitt to grip the rum!

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Glowbat: Deep in the jungles of Jidi, evolution has taken a strange turn. The bioluminescent bats of the rainforest lure their prey with a comforting glow, only to incinerate their unsuspecting victims with a caustic venom.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Go2Olymp:
Go2Olymp is excited to announce our new tournament for experienced teams showing off their skills in real battles.
	
	ATTENTION: The number of teams is limited. Only the first 32 teams to sign up will play in this tournament.
	
	Tournament format: Single Elimination. A match is won when a team gets its first victory (best of 1). Final match will be played to 2 victories (best of 3).
	
	Winning team will get $250. Other participants who reach finals and semifinals will also get money prizes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Go2Olymp_Season_2:
Go2Olymp is excited to announce our new tournament for experienced teams showing off their skills in real battles.
	
	Tournament format: Single Elimination. A match is won when a team gets its first victory (best of 1).
	
	Winning team will get $250. Other participants who reach finals and semifinals will also get money prizes.
