Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_GoDOTA_BALI_Season_1: Tournament of Bali Dota 2 Community, with a total prize pool of Rp12.000.000 ++ for 6 winners, held and sponsored by Go-Kool.Net eSports Arena on December 19 and 20, 2015.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Godhorse: The Redhooves of the Western Wails were long thought a thing of myth.  The last survivors of an ancient army, their riders lost to sword and arrow, these hardy steeds returned to the wilds where they bred and grew more feral with each passing generation.   Caught young, this fiery Redhoof shows all the courage of its warsteed ancestors.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Godlike_Dota_2_Online_Tou: Indonesian Dota 2 Online Tournament Season 1. Presented by Godlike Dota. Supported by Unjedoto.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gods_Mercy: Trust not in the mercy of gods, for many find it more fearsome than mortal spite.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gold_2014_Compendium_Gem: Awarded for raising The International 2014 Compendium beyond level 50.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gold_Rush: Gold Rush is a series of tournaments with a monthly prize of 350 Euros for the winner!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gold_Spectator_Gem: Adding this gem to an item will enable that item to track games viewed for a league or team.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Atomic_Ray_Thruste: Seldom do the blacksmiths and wizards of Ultimyr University cooperate, and yet far more seldom do those who test the result of such a cooperation survive to tell the tale.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Awalebs_Trundlewee: As Awaleb's destructive powers grew, so too did the influence of his healing touch. Indeed, one only need look for flourishing lands and overgrown fauna to follow the path of his great atrocities.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Baby_Roshan: A rare and glittering trophy awarded to the fastest slayers of Sugar Rush Roshan.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Barb_of_Skadi: Deep in Dark Reef Prison, a sorcerer and a blacksmith combined their trades to create a unique weapon. Fashioned from found materials,  the blade can open prison walls as easily as it opens bellies.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Basher_Blades: The fabled blades that shattered the Anvil Magus Hroth. Its terrible weight dented and shattered his iron shell, just as its blades tore into the enchanted hide beneath.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Basher_of_Mage_Sku: The fabled blades that shattered the Anvil Magus Hroth. Its terrible weight dented and shattered his iron shell, just as its blades tore into the enchanted hide beneath.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Beetlejaws_the_Box: Call for Beetlejaws as often as you'd like. Once, twice, three thousand times, Beetlejaws'll come snicking faithfully along
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Bracers_of_Forlorn: Though he uses his powers in battle unflinchingly and without pause, Ish'Kafel silently yearns to do more than just grasp and manipulate the tendrils of his home. But he must balance his desire to explore the boundaries of his growing influence with the knowledge that such experiments have the potential to destroy his current world, or worse, unleash new terrors upon the land of his own kind.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Chaos_Fulcrum: Bound to purpose on the hunt for the pale rider, the Chaos Fulcrum strains even against the order of its own existence as it bends reality to devour rays from the first Light.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Cyrridae: The skill of a master Weaver is plainly seen in the spread of its antennae, each tendril allowing added complexity to the Weaver's astral loom.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Devourling: While very few tales of astral experience have earned a place in the Academy Library, each trusted account includes mention of a strange reflection of the self, an oddly-distorted quintessence, never far from hand...
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Draca_Maw: When he first heard rumors of the \"unkillable\" draca eels that swim the magma rivers of Krulcsar, Huskar paid no mind. It was only in the midst of a firelodge vision quest that the eels' true potential became clear.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Edge_of_the_Lost_O: Long before Yurnero's time, just before the apex of the Isle of Masks, a new school of Mastery emerged--one whose practitioners had learned to use their blades to pierce the very fabric of reality itself. But soon these blade masters found the repercussions of such actions could spread far beyond the field of battle. Fearing dire outcomes--the nature of which we know little about--the elders of the school burned every scrap of parchment in their libraries before turning their blades upon all of the school's adherents...and eventually themselves.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Edict_of_Shadows: In the midst of Riki's cloud, enemy spellcasters are beset by the whispers of Tahlin.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Effigy_Block_of_Th:
Use this item to carve your favorite hero into a Golden Heroic Effigy of The International! Choose your effigy's pose, give it an inscription, then equip it to have your customized monument appear in your team's base for all to see.

Available exclusively to purchasers of The International Compendium 2015.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Empyrean: 'Tis told among Skywrath kind the legend of Shaldera, a being of black wing who in hubris flew into the darker skies hoping to meet the heavenly lords above. She who returned did so upon golden feathers, bearing the divine spear Empyrean, a symbol of her flight. It is said her kingdom endured for a thousand years and one.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Esports_League_Sea: The first season of the Golden Esports League puts the best Swedish teams against each other over three months for 30.000SEK!
The top Swedish teams compete over 3 months for 30,000 SEK!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Fin_of_the_First_S: For centuries, attempting to don this helm was a rite of passage to all who became First Spear of the Flood. In most cases, it was a short lesson in humility. In others, however, it meant a trip to the healer or even the grave. For one to wear the helm in battle like legends of old signals to Slithereen everywhere that a new age of strength is now upon them.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Flight_of_Epiphany: Only tentatively could Dragonus send tendrils of mystic thought out in search of the boundaries of his power's connection to the Skywrath scion, for a single false step would expose him and doom his efforts forever. It was with a careful, quiet joy that Dragonus discovered there are grey areas in his oath to the Nest of Thorns, and much like the emotions behind the creation of Scree'auk's Talon, loyalty to the progenitors is powerful haven for certain actions of ambiguous intent.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Floodmask: The unimaginable pressure of the ocean's deepest chasms is pent up in this sturdy bit of salvage. Open the hatch and stand aside!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Flopjaw: Splish-splash! Plip-plop! There's nothing like the splattery patter of finny feet to let you know your treasure is secure inside a Boxhound, and safely on its way.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Fortunes_Tout: Few can resist the call of this purry peddler.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_FullBore_Bonanza: Of all the memories from his homeland that Kardel Sharpeye revels in during rare quiet nights, tales from the midsummer carnivals and their requisite target galleries are first to pass his lips. At least, they would be, were any of his folk around with which he might share the tale.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Grasping_Bludgeon: An immortal weapon may know many masters through the ages, but it is rare that both attempt to wield it at the same time, with neither willing to relinquish his grasp. Woe betide he who finds himself a third party to this indelible struggle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Greevil: A reward for slaying a rare loot greevil.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Huntling: Even the smallest shadow of the tiniest baby leaf is sufficient to hide the Huntling from spying eyes, as he slips through the wilds with your valuables.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Hydrakan_Latch: Many of Slark's old stashes and boltholes were plundered or fallen into ruin by the time of his exodus from Dark Reef. Yet, in the most secret places, a few dark trinkets do remain.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Infernal_Chieftain: Bradwarden's thunderous stomps reverberate into the pits of hell.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Latticean_Shards: The zealot assassin burrowed deeper than any of his predecessors had ever dared. Striking a rich seam of dense crystalline formation, he soon found the armored plates of his exoskeleton coated in the shimmering substance.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Mandate_of_the_Sto: There are some who believe the surge of power that comes to Raijin Thunderkeg's hands is a natural result of any expenditure of his power. But no power comes without struggle, even for a Celestial. Though his skill allows for an effortless appearance, it is through sheer will alone that Raijin is able to harness the excess forces that flow from each jolt of his abilities.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Mantle_of_Grim_Fac: When first reforming himself in the wake of Doom and Nevermore's umbral intervention, Shadow Demon gathered new parts to himself with little regard to form, so long as they were strong in function. Now, as his plans come ever closer to fruition and his strength nears its zenith, he chooses more deliberately a face fit to mete out the tragedies to come.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Mask_of_Metira: The enchanters of Metira could never abide human hands in possession of their artifacts. The few thieves who \"succeeded\" in liberating small baubles from their trove were hunted down and swiftly executed. For a Metiran master to gift a bespoke golden mask to Axia's ward Mirana -- an honor no other outsider had earned -- was a sign of gravest respect indeed.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Minnow_Ward_Upgrad: This International 2017 reward enables an upgraded color style to be unlocked for the Shifty Minnow ward in the style menu.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Moonfall: When Nightsilver Wood was yet but a thicket, a shard of stellar origin fell. Around this holy landing was built the Shrine of Selemene, and the shard itself fashioned into the most sacred of arms possessed of the order of the Dark Moon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Nothlic_Burden: That which encumbers in the Nothl Realm emboldens on the earthly plane.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Offhand_Basher_of_: The fabled blades that shattered the Anvil Magus Hroth. Its terrible weight dented and shattered his iron shell, just as its blades tore into the enchanted hide beneath.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Pale_Mausoleum: The dirge howls from the deep. Its call is irresistible, its song a melody of dark and cold. All will fall under the spell, be they tyrant or peasant, soldier or thief. The dirge shall claim.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Profane_Union:
Already an unnatural mingling of two separate minds inhabiting a single form, N'aix finds nothing distasteful in augmenting that form ever further to suit their twisted needs.

Immortal items cannot be traded or marketed through The International 2018, but can still be gifted once.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Rabid_Watchcog: As the full scale of his opposition's strength became clear, Clockwerk set about procuring whatever meagre enchantment help was available in order to augment the effectiveness of his arms and armor. Hopefully the second attempt turns out a bit more...stable.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Reel_Guardian_Set: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Golden Reel Guardian' set for Earthshaker.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Rippers_Reel:
The simple barbs of the ripper's hook find difficult purchase in the scales of the slippery folk who glide beneath the waves. To catch certain prey, a bit of ingenuity and engineering are required. Or, in Pudge's case, gold to pay the tinkerer

The animations for this item should take priority over most other animations or kinetic gems.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Riptide: Let this blade guard you from harm.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Seekling: Even the Hound of the Flayed Twins entered his calling as a mere pup, tending to his predecessor's needs. Now a new pup has arrived seeking to take on the mantle, ready to aid warriors in their time of need.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Shadow_Masquerade: While most family heirlooms were abandoned along with his former life, the last son of the Tahlin line still treasures the ancestral blades that adorned the sigil of his house.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Shards_of_Exile: The self-assembling crystals of the Outworld make a very good staff ... and an even better prison. Embodiments of the Void, the Shards offer a crash course in its essentials to Harbinger's opponents.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Silent_Wake: The midwinter drifts scatter in a silent gust from the passing ranger before settling gently back to earth, as if they were never disturbed at all.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Staff_of_Perplex: Captured in this staff is a puzzle that not even Rubick has solved. He passes idle moments attempting to unlock its mysteries. From time to time, hoping for insight, he casts it upon an enemy, and lets them hang enthralled in its enigmas.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Sullen_Hollow: Idly drumming phantom phalanges, Sullen Hollow barely restrains its impatience to lash out and administer tainted browbeatings to the foes of Necrophos.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Treasures: Riches are won on the battlefield.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Trove_Carafe_2015: No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. This treasure contains individual items.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Trove_Carafe_2017:
No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. 
	
	This treasure contains the rare golden versions of some of the items in the Trove Carafe 2017.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Venoling: Shortly after Lesale the Herbalist's disappearance in the Acid Jungles of Jidi, his bold yet diminutive nephew went looking for his uncle ... and found a similar fate.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Walrus_Whacker: If you ask Aggron, they won it in a dice game.  If you ask its former owner, you'll get the silence of the grave.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_Wyrmwrought_Flare: Only a fraction of the wyrm-kissed ever discover the true nature of their heritageÃ¢ÂÂor the full extent of their powers.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_eSports_League_Sea: Watch eight of the top Nordic teams compete in a three-month long season for a 30,000 SEK prize pool and merchandise from Plantronics and Razer. The LAN finals will be held on the 18th of April in Sundsvall, Sweden.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Golden_ns_ti10_immortal_a: Though long perished of form, some spiritual remnants of Balanar's lost brethren still haunt the edges of the void, drawn to the dark focus of their remaining One.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gombangdae_Dosa: Includes all of the items in the 'Gombangdae Dosa' set for Dark Seer:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_GoodGamingShop_Dota_2_Tou: 128 teams from Indonesia will compete for a  $1550 prize pool. GoodGamingShop Tournament is sponsored by Logitech - G SERIES.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_GoodGamingShop_Tournament: GoodGamingShop is one of the biggest gaming peripheral store in Indonesia. GGS are established from 2008 and committed to grow the eSports community in Indonesia. With sponsorship from Logitech G Series as our official gaming partner, GoodGamingShop presents the Dota 2 Tournament for Indonesia scene to take a good step to competitive scene.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Good_Play_SEA_Invitationa: Featuring 10 of the top teams in Southeast Asia battling it out in the Good Play SEA Invitational for a RM 20,000 prize pool. All games will be casted by Beyond the Summit.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_GosuLatam_Tournament: Gosulatam is a single elimination tournament for eight up-and-coming LATAM  teams
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_GosuLeague: GosuLeague delivers seasons on a monthly basis where teams of all skill levels play in different divisions. The top division is awarded with $5000 each month. Each team play two matches a week.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_GosuLeague__Admin: GosuLeague delivers seasons on a monthly basis where teams of all skill levels play in different divisions. The top division is awarded with $5000 each month. Each team play two matches a week.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gothic_Whisper: Contains the Gothic Whisper set for Phantom Assassin
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gown_of_the_Mortal_Coil: The beautiful flowing robes of Krobelus, the Death Prophet.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gown_of_the_Phoenix_Blood: The dress was made in an old style once popular among the nobles of western Misrule.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grace_of_the_Eminence_of_: Content for so long exploring the playground of the mortal realm, Akasha returns now to the dangerous Court of Ristul, where her star has fallen in her time away. But the Queen above intends to claim as well the throne below. Striking a bargain with an exiled demon prince, Akasha has seized a new measure of power, and her fiendish plans are at last set to begin.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gramma_Sharpies_Smokin_Ru: Gramma Sharpeye never touched a rifle in her life, but she rolled a fine cigar and packed a solid cartridge. Every fifth eve, after chores were done gramma would sit by the fire and puff her cigar and rock her chair and pack enough cartridges to serve the entire family's shooting. Wear her favorite smokin' rug on your back as a memento of those happy days.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grampa_Sharpies_Shin_Shoo: Brag 'Whistlecheeks' Sharpeye was once the finest gun in all the Knollen, able to knock the toes off a troll at one thousand feet. He left his favorite gun to his grandson in the hopes that one day young Kardel would continue to build its legend.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grand_Blade_of_the_Demigo: The name of the ancient kingdom that fell to this terrible blade has long been forgotten to history.  The blade itself, however, seems impossible to lose track of.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grand_Claive_of_the_Unsha: \"Ware the wanderer who walks with head held high, back unstooped, and arm held ready. The one that so boldly denies his disgrace has no such disgrace to deny! Surely that one is an assassin cloaked in contempt.\"
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grand_Crown_of_the_Gigas: Is there any beast more majestic than the mighty Gigas? Even Alces and Cameloides bow before it.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grand_Curls_of_the_Admira: Show them that you are a man of privledge.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grand_Mantle_of_the_Archi: Caring for a repository of singular, priceless, unreproducible volumes of wisdom and madness is a burden that, like this mantle, may be shouldered by only an Archivist of similarly singular power.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grand_Witch_Hunter_Templa: Contains the Grand Witch Hunter Templar set for Kunkka, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grandfathers_Ribs: Witch Doctor carries the ribs of his old grandfather, a shaman who held powerful magicks and spoke with influential spirits. Grandfather offers the Witch Doctor access to power in exchange for the opportunity to see blood spilled once more.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grapple_Gaming_Tournament: This Tournament Organized by Grapple Gaming and Supported by Dota Base Indonesia. 64 team will compete to get IDR 6.000.000 Prizepool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grasping_Bludgeon: An immortal weapon may know many masters through the ages, but it is rare that both attempt to wield it at the same time, with neither willing to relinquish his grasp. Woe betide he who finds himself a third party to this indelible struggle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Graveheart_Staff: At the edge of death, a spark of life remains to restart a faltering heart.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gravel_Foot:
Find sure footing on any terrain.

Required Level: 13

BONUS MOVEMENT SPEED: 50
DAMAGE BLOCK: 25
+8 ALL STATS
+8 HP REGEN
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Great_Grey_Owl_Bow: She dreamed in the night that the divine owl spirit called her name. When she woke, this bow lay beside her in a bed of leaves...grey feathers still drifting from the branch above.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Great_Moss_Cape_of_the_Fu: Infused with the essence of the Father Mushroom.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Great_Pipe_of_the_Father_: There are many ways to reach the Nothl realm, several of which involve hits from the Great Pipe. Some hits are less survivable than others.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Great_Sages_Reckoning:
Though his misdeeds have long been forgiven, the thrills of Sun Wukong's crimes live on. Relive three legendary trials from his earliest adventures with the Great Sage's Reckoning.
	
	This Monkey King Arcana item includes four dynamic styles unlocked by game state, altered voice effects, and new animations.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Great_Sages_Reckoning_Bun:
Though his misdeeds have long been forgiven, the thrills of Sun Wukong's crimes live on. Relive three legendary trials from his earliest adventures with the Great Sage's Reckoning.

This Monkey King Arcana bundle includes Great Sage's Reckoning Arcana head item with four dynamic styles that change depending on the level of his Ultimate ability, custom animations, Great Sage's Reckoning Loading Screen and Emoticon, and Taunt: Goin' Bananas.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Great_Sages_Reckoning_Emo:
Unlocks the Monkey King arcana emoticon: :mischief:

Watch out - he will hide in your emoticon gallery!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Great_Sages_Reckoning_Loa: Though his misdeeds have long been forgiven, the thrills of Sun Wukong's crimes live on.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Greathelm_of_the_Chiseled: Though what or who they once held safe has long since passed, the armor of the Chiseled Guard remains.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Green_Cup_by_Terrikon: 32 teams from CIS will fight for a prize pool of 3200 Hryvnia.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Green_Minnow_Ward_Upgrade: This International 2017 reward enables an upgraded color style to be unlocked for the Shifty Minnow ward in the style menu.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Green_Sleeves_of_the_Voya: For who else but my captain, Green Sleeves?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Greevil: A strange beast infused with magic. Its color, appearance, and abilities are determined by the types of magical essences it was exposed to while still an egg.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grievous_Grapnel: There's no time for grappling with your conscience when your dinner is getting away.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grim_Destiny: Contains the Grim Destiny set for Wraith King
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grimoire_The_Book_Wyrm: Grimoire is a long forgotten Book Wyrm, who literally lost himself studying the books in the great library of The Ultimyr Academy. Bound to the book, he does his master's bidding, forever hopeful he will find the incantation to set himself free once more.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grimsneer: The tools of death are no burden for Grimsneer.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grip_of_the_Lost_Star: Created in partnership with Era, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grip_of_the_Swordmaster: Carefully constructed to guide a foe's blade away from the shoulder, or to catch it mid-swing.  Many have fallen overlooking such a simple piece of armor.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grips_of_Eternal_Harvest: Long past time evil takes its fill, the feast goes on forevermore.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_GrossuCup_Season_1: Teams from South America will compete in the first  season of the GrossuCup for a prize pool of $450!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_GrossuCup_Season_2: Teams from South America compete in the primary season of the GrossuCup for the $450 prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gruesome_Embrace: This contains the 'Gruesome Embrace' set for Lion, including a loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grull_the_Grim_Walker: Disruptor had his eye on Grull from the moment he spotted the beast standing in the corner of the breeder's yard. \"Who's that one then?\" \"Grull. None can ride her. She's too disruptive.\" \"Perfect! I'll ride her home!\"
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Grunion_Battle: The first season of Grunion Battle will gather many players from Europe to compete for a mythical set.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guard_of_Anguish: A skull plucked from among the eager forsaken.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guard_of_the_Clergy_Ascet: The rightmost shoulder of Antimage: Righter by far than thou!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guard_of_the_Crescent_Moo: A shield made from pure MoonSilver and dusted with the wing scales of the Lunar Moth. Attacks that luna fails to evade are blocked effortlessly by this guard.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guard_of_the_Crimson_Cutt: The guard is built from the shield and straps taken from the corpse of the Crimson Cut-throat.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guard_of_the_Dark_Wraith: Wraithlike, she passes unseen. But should you espy her, you would appreciate the graceful lines of her garb.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guard_of_the_Deep_Tribes: The men of the deep forest are not like their milk-fed cousins. Primal, driven by instinct and a will to survive, they call upon nature's pantheon and know nothing of gentle gods.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guard_of_the_Drunken_Warl: Designed from the cast-off remnants of ancient brew casks, these bits of aged wood have been infused with the essence of the ancient order of the Oyo.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guard_of_the_First_Hunt:
A kit's first tools must come from the remains of its prey.

This item can be upgraded with the 'Kit of the First Hunt Style Unlock' granted to players who complete at least 40 stars on the Path of the Saboteur.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guard_of_the_Lost_Vigil: Were there any Vigil Knights still alive to tell the tale, they might share a favorite yarn of the \"Lost\" Vigil patrol, a mystery with endless variations. Though most believed the missing knights lost at sea, some insisted there had been sightings recorded by the elders of Ashkavor--that the knights had been seen in the mountains that guard the unforgiving jungle lands of Fellstrath--a region already feared long before the destruction of Ashkavor made any journey into those lands impossible.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guard_of_the_Red_Mist: Forged when the Red Mist were many and Mogul Khan was but a lowly grunt, the Guard is a rock among a sea of blows. As much a statement of intent as a shield, the cursed sigil of Battle Hunger lies emblazoned upon its face. Only death and slaughter may remedy its hex.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guard_of_the_Wandering_Fl: Seeking to restore the mantras of the Guardian Flame far beyond the embers of his ignition pyre in the Wailing Mountains, Xin loosed his remnants into the fury of a passing storm, casting them out in search of all who might still carry his spark.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guardian_Shell:
Required Level: 16

Passive: Unwavering - Movement Speed cannot be slowed and bearer cannot be rooted.

Bonus Armor: 15
Bonus Magic Resistance: 40%
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guardian_of_Silence_Set: Includes all of the items in the 'Guardian of Silence' set for Silencer:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guardian_of_the_Eternal_S: Includes all of the items in the 'Guardian of the Eternal Seasons' set for Nature's Prophet and a loading screen:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guardian_of_the_Red_Mount: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Guardian of the Red Mountain' set for Earthshaker:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guardians_of_Justice: This courier was created in partnership with KDL Season Three winners MVP Phoenix, who receive a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guardians_of_the_Lost_Pat: These custom towers from The International 2019 Battle Pass can be equipped in the World options of the Global Items loadout menu.
These custom towers from The International 2019 Battle Pass can be equipped in the World options of the Global Items loadout menu.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guards_of_Vincere: There will be pain.  There will be screaming.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guards_of_the_Burning_Dec: The unsleeping huntsman patrols all reaches of The Hoven, one anguished step after another.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guards_of_the_Wyrmforge_S: The demasted figurehead of the Wyrmforge is just one of many lost relics gathered by the One for safe keeping and occasional good use.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guf_Australia_Winter_Regi: The Guf Australia $1600 Winter Regional is a swiss format tournament played at Guf LAN Centres around Australia with a total prize pool of $1,600 AUD on the 22nd of June!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guilt_of_the_Survivor:
As even the faces of favored kin fade from recollection, the unholy forms of the Turstarkuri faithful rise perversely in the mind's eye.

Contains the Guilt of the Survivor set for Anti-Mage, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Guise_of_the_Winged_Bolt: Includes all of the items in the 'Guise of the Envious Archer' for Drow Ranger plus Loading Screen:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gunboat_Hegemon: Contains the Gunboat Hegemon set for Gyrocopter, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gunslinger_Set: Includes all of the items in the 'Gunslinger' set for Sniper:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gunslingers_Bracers: Any article of clothing worn upon the body should be capable to carrying ammunition.  Even stylish bracers.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gunslingers_Cape: By obscuring the profile, this cape has proven a useful countermeasure against long distance sniping.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gunslingers_Hat: The perfect hat for a shootest accused of having bullets on the brain.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gunslingers_Rifle: For the highland Keens, it is a matter of honor that each shootist construct his own weapon.  Thus a good shot is the product of both a sharp eye, and a keen mind for gun design.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gwanji_the_Thunder_Lizard: Long thought extinct, the deadly Gwanji is a living relic from a bygone age.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Gwimyeon_: The fiercest face often wins the fiercest battles.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_HCUP: Presents by IMBATV,every week is a single season,prizepool is 20,000RMB for each week,most chinese teams play this tournament to improve themselves.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_HEELYS_CUP_season_1: Some of the top Amateur teams compete for the $1,000 prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_HELL_League: 16 teams will compete for the championship in a best of one format.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_HSL_Summer_Academic_Showd: High school teams from US/Canada will compete to earn one of 13 qualifying spots in the Summer Academic Showdown. These teams will be pitted against 3 collegiate teams with the top four teams earning cash prizes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Habit_of_the_Seeker: The Flayed Ones cannot be destroyed nor can they be banished to some outer realm. Only through endless bloodshed can they be placated and their wrath stayed.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hair_of_the_Blood_Moon: Banehallow often takes solace in the company of any fellow afflicted he might encounter in his wanderings. Not all, however, find the company of their own kind so agreeable.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hair_of_the_Dark_Magic: Style and sorcery are said to go hand in hand.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hair_of_the_Imperious_Com: Given enough gold and exposure to civilization, a troll's haughty nature lends itself well to indulging in a bit of finery.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hair_of_the_Survivor: As even the faces of favored kin fade from recollection, the unholy forms of the Turstarkuri faithful rise perversely in the mind's eye.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hakama_of_a_Thousand_Face: A traditional hakama from Isle of Masks. It was given to Yurnero by his late swordmaster, long before his exile.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hakobi_and_Tenneko_Bundle: Contains the Hakobi and Tenneko courier and loading screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Halberd_Gaming_House_Tour:
Halberd Gaming House Tournament with prizepool
	2.500.000 idr
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Halberd_of_the_Steppe: A ceremonial halberd, blooded often in the ceremonial battles of Omexe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hammer_Time: The shark said it couldn't be touched. Tidehunter disagreed.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hammer_of_Enlightenment: It may not save their souls, but this hammer will surely send your enemies to their just reward.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hammer_of_Hope: For hope is brought to all who witness the hammer's fall and repent.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hammer_of_Light_Inexorabl: This strange, rune-scrawled hammer will ensure that all your enemies see the light.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hammer_of_Thunderwraths_C: A weapon capable of hammering the most unmalleable of unbelievers into shape.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hammer_of_the_Dingus: A nameless weapon, wrapped in holy scripture taken from the Book of the All Seeing.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hammer_of_the_Guarded_Wor: Contains the Hammer of the Guarded Word set for Tusk, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hammer_of_the_Mechanised_: Created in partnership with June, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hammer_of_the_Purist_Cham: When your best tool is a hammer, the world (and the head of the heretic) begins to look like a nail.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hammer_of_the_Radiant_Cru: Intended as an trophy for the most stalwart of the order's crusaders, the great smiths ensured it would be just as impressive above a hearth as it would be in combat.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hammer_of_the_Skygods: By stormcraft and steady arm is wrought the will of the skies.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hand_of_Glory_Staff: A week of incantations were spent to pierce beyond the mortal realm and consort with what lay beyond. Finally, a sliver of infernal light appeared and from depths unknown rumbled a distant wail of suffering and anger. The wretched sound grew and grew into a deafening roar before a hellborn claw reached through the burning tear into the world. Yet in its unseeing fury the invading appendage disrupted the ritual, and the vile mouth from whence it sprang suddenly closed shut, forever severing the vile hand from its unknowable owner.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hand_of_Hells_Ambassador: Enemies cower when he raises this horrific hand, but friends merely return the greeting.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Handful_of_Jade_Tokens: Unpack this gift to earn 50 Jade Tokens.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hans_Pro_Gaming_Series_To: More than 500 People will compete in this Tournament, will be held on Oct, 2016 to win over IDR 5.000.000 prize pool. Organized by Hans Pro Gaming
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Harbinger_of_War: Includes all of the items in the 'Harbinger of War' set for Axe plus a loading screen:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Harbinger_of_the_Inauspic: Contains all of the items in the 'Harbinger of the Inauspicious Abyss' set for Outworld Devourer:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Harborblossom: A shy but powerful band of wisps with gifts in the healing arts often seek shelter in the petals of a rare bloom whose whereabouts are known by very few.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hard_Core_Dota_2_Tourname: 64 Teams in Indonesia will play in LAN Tournament for the $500 prize pool!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hard_Dota_League_Season_1: This amateur league team where everyone can participate. The prize fund themselves make the team! When registering a team makes a small contribution!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hardened_Hunters_Armor: The value of a contract is measured not only in the bounty paid, but in the loot taken from the mark's cold corpse.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hardened_Hunters_Bracer: One might think that the bounty hunter thinks nothing of his victim. On the contrary, the bounty hunter understands his target's pain and fear. He simply does not care.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hardened_Hunters_Mask: It's not uncommon for bandits to wear leather gorgets to protect their throats from the knives of their 'allies.'
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hardway_League_Ticket: 24 semi-pro and professional teams from the CIS region will fight for a $600 prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hare_Hunt_Cape: A cape as golden as the autumn woods through which he stalks his tremulous prey.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hare_Hunt_Hat: A furry woodland pelt is a perfect pate protector.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hare_Hunt_Rifle: Overkill for a rabbit hunt? You haven't seen these particular rabbits.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hare_Hunt_Shoulders: What's that? I can't hear you. There's a lit fuse hissing in my ear.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hare_Hunt_Sleeves: Richly ornate protection for Sniper's forearms when he creeps through shady cover, as snipers do.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Harmony_League_Season_1: Harmony League Season 1 features 16 amateur teams from South Korea and Japan to clash in an epic two-days online series to decide the first glorious victor in the series. Co-hosted by the Genuine Factory of South Korea, and JapanDota of Japan.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Harness_of_the_Fissured_S: Contains the Harness of the Fissured Soul set for Elder Titan, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Harness_of_the_Forgotten_: Ambient particle effects can be unlocked on this item using the Treasure Upgrade Infuser - Winter 2016.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Harvester_of_the_Hidden_H: A curved scythe, used to capture men or cut them down like so much wheat.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hat_of_The_Howling_Wolf: A pelt hat made of the fur of the rare Triple-Tailed Howling Wolf. The spirit of the creature lives within!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hat_of_the_Jiang_Shis_Rev: Should the mob ever come for him a second time, Ethreain will be ready.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hat_of_the_Stormcharge_Dr: Astride the focused storm, Disruptor stalks the boundaries of battle, ready to strike down his enemies and lead his tribe's return to a place of distinction and honor.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hatchet_of_the_Shifting_S:
Besting a vicious sorcerer often requires a vicious tool.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.

Besting a vicious sorcerer often requires a vicious tool.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Haunted_Lord: Contains the Haunted Lord set for Wraith King, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Haven_of_the_Hinterheart_: This item can be used to unlock an alternate style for the Haven of the Hinterheart item set for Treant Protector.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Havoc_of_Dragon_Palace: Contains the Havoc of Dragon Palace set for Monkey King, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hazhadal_Magebreaker:
After besting the young mages of his order, Nortrom put his newfound skills to use suppressing the godless outlaws of the Hazhadall Barrens, routinely making short work of their vaunted enthrallers.

Contains the Hazhadal Magebreaker set for Silencer, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hazhadal_Magebreaker_Load: After besting the young mages of his order, Nortrom put his newfound skills to use suppressing the godless outlaws of the Hazhadall Barrens, routinely making short work of their vaunted enthrallers.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_HeadAche: A rare but useful mutation. The spikes are actually malformed teeth that grew out of place, and well out of hand.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Head_of_the_Ageless_Witne: As the lone Protector's path takes him ever further from his home soil, the fresh growth of bark keeps record of the wonders he has seen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Head_of_the_Forest_Hermit: This humble cap is a reminder that he wishes to be left alone with his thoughts.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Head_of_the_Lucent_Gate: Includes 2 head styles and an ability icon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Head_of_the_Sea_Djinn: Includes an alternate style with an open mask.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Headdress_of_the_Arkturan: There is power yet in these old bones.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Headdress_of_the_Father_S: Fashioned from the feathers of the violet shryll, a bird that flies with its wingtips trailing through the Nothl realm, while the rest of its body sails in the light of this world.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Headdress_of_the_Seeker: Adorned in tusks of great beasts slain in the high peaks of Xhacatocatl, the priests of the Flayed Twins seek blood to keep their greedy gods appeased.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Headdress_of_the_Slithere: It has been long since this apparel has been seen in the great halls of the Slithereen, but few have forgotten it.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Headdress_of_the_Wildwing: Enchantress passes unchallenged through Wildwing territories when she wears this headdress.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Headgear_of_the_: Never coordinated well enough to swim with any stealth or grace, Ogre Magi relied on pilfered shipwright's tools and a bit of luck to survive a failed raid on Deshom Bay.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Headhunter: This weapon once adorned a nobleman's mantel collecting dust, which is exactly the fate Axe made for the nobleman's head.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Headpiece_of_the_Deadly_N: Although barely visible beneath the rim of this headpiece, Belladonna grants the wearer the enormous dilated eyes that so befit a seeker of mysterious truths.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Headress_of_the_Crescent_: Adorned with the wings of the sacred Lunar Moth, Luna rides into battle with strength and agility. Able to sense an attack before it happens, she can deftly avoid blows that would otherwise seek to harm her.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Headwraps_of_the_Acolyte_: No acolyte of Clasz needs eyes of flesh to observe the rites. Those who have them to begin with must soon part ways.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Healing_Fount_of_the_Lost: The healing arts of bygone lands have lost none of their potency.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Healing_Ward_of_the_KuurI: The gargoyles and spirit-watchers of the Kuur-Ishiminari craft-clan bear witness to deeds both glorious and profane with never closing eyes of jade.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heart_of_the_Inauspicious: Those who patrol the edge of the void must gird themselves in armor impregnable to evil's piercing rays.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heart_of_the_North_Set: Ready for the cold?  This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Heart of the North' set for Crystal Maiden:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hearts_of_Misrule: Though less verdant than her family's gardens in Roseleaf once were, Mireska soon found much to adore about the arid lands far to the southeast.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heat: Clinkz is not the only member of his clan to be preserved in a form of immortal bone. This bow, all that remains of his grandsire, is full of spirit fire and unwanted advice.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_HeavenPiercing_Pauldrons: While purely decorative in nature, these ornate shoulder pieces serve as a reminder that even the depthless celestial realm is vulnerable to being punctured by Invoker's power.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heaven_League_Season_1: More than 64 teams from CIS countries compete for the $350 prize pool!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heaven_Sent: When the innocent gaze upon Heaven Sent's internal glow, their souls are awash with tranquility and respite from pain. The wicked cannot bear its light. This is a weapon for Keeper of Light.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heavenly_General: Contains all of the items in the 'Heavenly General' set for Storm Spirit plus a loading screen. These items were created in partnership with ZSMJ, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heavy_Armor_of_the_World_: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Heavy Armor of the World Runner' set:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heavy_Barbed_Armor_Set: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Heavy Barbed Armor'' set for Bristleback.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heavy_Belt_of_the_World_R: If our world is but a shadow of Barathrum's real world, then this belt may be but a shadow of Spirit Breaker's real belt. But oh what a shadow!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heavy_Gauntlets_of_the_Wo: When prying wide the rifts between the planes, Spirit Breaker draws power from these mighty gauntlets.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heavy_Helm_of_the_World_R: Barathrum's mighty head is his battering ram. Protect it well with this heavy helm!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heavy_Pauldrons_of_the_Wo: A strange friction is generated on the physical forms of those who slide between the worlds, deeply scarring and cutting into their form. These pauldrons guard Spirit Breaker from the worst of the damage.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heavy_Steel_Armor_Set: Includes all of the items in the 'Heavy Steel Armor' set for Axe:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heavy_Steel_Axe: Forged for a brutal warlord who sought to challenge Axe in single combat.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heavy_Steel_Belt: A deep scratch shows at its center, a remnant of the only attack the original owner was able to deflect.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heavy_Steel_Shoulder: The warlord thought his forged armor would win the day.  Axe showed him otherwise.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heavy_Tenderizer: A few quick turns under Pudge's Tenderizer, and even the toughest foe goes down like butter.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heavyarm_Amateur_Cup: Heavyarm Amateur Cup is an amateur tournament in Malaysia sponsored by Heavyarm U-Garage Store. There will be 6 series of amateur cups with a total prizes up to 85 USD
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hecates_Belts: In the dim nether are shreds and shards of material, spectral matter lost in the ether.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hecates_Dress: Remnant fashion of a culture long lost to the ages.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heir_of_Terror: Contains the Heir of Terror set for Bane, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heiress_of_the_Coastal_Ki: Contains the Heiress of the Coastal Kingdom set for Mirana, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heirloom_of_the_Charred_B: An heirloom of a once-noble house, now one with the ashes of history.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heirloom_of_the_Temple_Pr: A gilded keepsake from her first assassination, this heirloom once graced the flowing locks of Queens.  Now Templar Assassin wears it as reminder that no one is beyond her reach.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heirlooms_of_Aeol_Drias: Contains all of the items in the 'Heirlooms of Aeol Drias' set for Silencer plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helios_Esports__Logitech_: An amateur tournament to showcase the top North American and European teams competing for prizes worth over $1500!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_HellSpar_Anathema: Forced to his knees before the altar of his own temple, Prelate Vidmar, head of the Order of the Crystal Echelon, knew vile hatred. His flock--acolytes and supplicants alike--lay in pieces around him. As the creature--it could not be called a man--raised its demonic hand once more, the Prelate focused on the fire of his own rage. With final breath, as Lion's dreadful power crashed into his body, Vidmar cursed the Demon Witch. Strengthened by the arcane conduit of the Demon Witch's spell, the Prelate's curse surged into Lion's hand, corrupting it with Crystal Rot. Only by fusing the Prelate's modified headpiece to the afflicted flesh was Lion able to slow the creep of crystalline blight...and a time will come when a more permanent solution must be found.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hell_League_: Register your team and fight your way throught the groupstage towards the grand final
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hellfire_Edge: Seared, hacked, and trampled. No indignity is too small to be meted out by Chaos Knight and his steed.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hellgazer: While Warlock is deep in study, his sentry keeps an eye out for Infernal interruptions--as well as more mundane intrusions.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hellish_Gemstaff: Each facet of the gem reflects the captured soul of a bound demon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hells_Ambassador_Set: Includes all of the items in the 'Hell's Ambassador' set for Lion:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hells_Glare: Only he that burns and is not consumed can wield a sword whose radiance cannot be quenched.  Forged at the same time and from the same ingot of steel as the great bell of Vashundol, the great-sword known as Hell'Âs Glare devours the darkness just as Doom devours the souls of the damned.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hells_Usher: A mysterious blade long rumored to exist.  Its razor sharp edge ushers enemies straight into hell.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hellthorn_Scepter: What evil beauty blossoms in the infernal pit, that Lion risked pricking his finger to pluck this lurid thorn?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_Burning_Turmoil: From realms beyond mortal knowledge rides forth a heaving darkness.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_Claszureme: The runes upon the brow give vision beyond the flow of time.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_Divine_Ascension: A helm befitting one who can ascend and raze his foes with divine arcana.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_Endless_Havoc: Forged in the tumult of the rift, the helm burns eternal.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_Impasse: A helm featuring horns touched by enchantment.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_Infernal_Despair: Hope fails as lives shatter, and the dark form of chaos rides forth.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_Retribution: The Skywrath Mage pierces his enemies with his gaze, shortly before he pierces them with his talons.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_Thunderwraths_Cal: A stylish and dramatic helm truly fitting a knight of the Omniscient.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_Unfettered_Malevo: Cursed chains forged by the Order of Ra'hul to bind the Night Stalker and bring his ancient power to heel. And bind Balanar they did, until darkness fell.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of__the_Dark_Wraith: A helm as dark as her soul.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Abyssal_Scour: When the Abyssal Horde comes, it will be Vrogros at the vanguard of the charge, eager to bend yet another new land to his vile will.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Ardalan_Inter: While nothing can get Kardel to divulge his means of transit to the Ardalan Nebula, he's more than happy to swap hogwhompers of his adventures there. Keep him in his cups long enough and he might even tell you about the mishap with the princess and the plasma gun.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Dark_Moon_Sta: The Dark Moon faithful consist of former scholars, laborers, orphans, and thieves. One may have served as magistrate of a city, another spilled blood as a warlord in the wilds. They have walked all imaginable paths to find Selemene. In her service, the trials and tragedies of the past matter not. They worship the Goddess together, guardians of the Nightsilver Woods.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_First_Dawn: All who see him shall know.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Flameguard: The Flameguard sect of the Vigil Knights are sworn to protect the ever-burning Holy Flame. While few in number, they are unmatched in swordsmanship.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Guardian_Cons:
Though depictions of his body and form differ in the telling, the crackle of the Lightning Revenant's whip is known to all of the blessed few who have returned to life from the Narrow Maze.

This item can be upgraded with the 'Compact of the Guardian Construct Style Unlock' granted to players who complete at least 40 stars on the Path of the Dominator.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Hidden_Talent: Silence is golden, as is the point on this mighty helm.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Hunters_Glory: Even the most skilled trackers may only hope to earn in a lifetime what Gondar claims on a single hunt.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Lost_Vigil: Were there any Vigil Knights still alive to tell the tale, they might share a favorite yarn of the \"Lost\" Vigil patrol, a mystery with endless variations. Though most believed the missing knights lost at sea, some insisted there had been sightings recorded by the elders of Ashkavor--that the knights had been seen in the mountains that guard the unforgiving jungle lands of Fellstrath--a region already feared long before the destruction of Ashkavor made any journey into those lands impossible.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Nimble_Edge: A well-trained mind is sharper than any blade.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Penitent_Scho: Only by candlelight does Dragonus dare investigate the means to restore his lost love.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Radiant_Crusa: The inside is reinforced and padded to protect against heavy blows.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Red_Conqueror: When Axe wears this helm, Axe sees red. Which is perfectly fine with Axe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Reef_Kyte_Rid: Astride a fintail reef kyte and protected against the crush by an enchanted helm, the moon rider serves as Selemene's champion and emissary in forging undersea alliances and keeping creatures of the deep at bay.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Revenant: A new storm is blowing across the battlefield.  Where there is thunder, there is sure to be lighting.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Silent_Guardi: A quiet, protected mind leads to a quick blade.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Slain_Dragon: A cage of gold for your knight's gilded head.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Slithereen_Ex: Stripped of her rank and station, the exile Slithice has been instructed to cover her headfin while among her people.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Slithereen_Kn: This helm and golden headpiece has long been a symbol of command among the Knights of the Slithereen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Umizar_Crawle: For those with a taste for gambling and excess treasure to spend, the hidden grottos of Crey host all manner of speculative bloodsports.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Warriors_Retr: Beneath his helm, Sven's thoughts are hidden. But the image he presents to the world may change like the weather.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helm_of_the_Wyrmforge_Sha: The demasted figurehead of the Wyrmforge is just one of many lost relics gathered by the One for safe keeping and occasional good use.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helmet_of_Omexe: When is a helmet both weapon and armor?  When it rests on the mighty head of Bradwarden.  Also, when it has spikes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helmet_of_the_Burning_Dec: The unsleeping huntsman patrols all reaches of The Hoven, one anguished step after another.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helmet_of_the_Chosen_Larv: Beneath this ornate helmet of hardened chitin rages a mind unlike any other in the insect world--a cold intelligence bent on the destruction of the chosen target.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helmet_of_the_Cryogenic_E: As Ulfsaar lay ravaged by battle and cold, the shaman bound parts of his life force to the nearby icicles until he recovered. The warrior now proudly wears this fur armor embedded with shards of that spellbound ice as a reminder of his spirit's victory over death itself.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helmet_of_the_Drake: Said to be forged from the iron that once chained the last of the great Drakinds, this helm is most coveted among dragon slayers.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Helmet_of_the_Fractured_O: 'Hey your plumage looks nicer than mine. Wanna trade?'
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Herald_of_Measureless_Rui: Includes all of the items in the 'Herald of Measureless Ruin' set for Outworld Devourer plus a loading screen. These items were created in partnership with Mushi, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hermes_the_Hermit_Crab: Hermes' arrival always delivers a smile to even the crabbiest of faces.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hermid: Well-meaning if a bit clumsy, Hermid is on the hunt for his oldest friend, who vanished one day after discovering the most curious red shell.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hero_Dota: This tournament gives an opportunity for semi-pro and non-pro teams from Russia, Ukraine, and Belarus to compete for the prize of $1,000 USD as well as prizes provided by sponsors and partners.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hero_Dota_Second_Chapter: Second season of tournament for semi-pro and non-pro team from Russia, Ukraine, Belarus. Any team can prove themselves fighting for the main prize of over $1,000 USD (32 thousand rubles), besides for special rewards provided by sponsors and partners.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hero_Dota_Third_Chapter: The top semi-pro teams from the CIS region compete for a $3500 prize pool. This bundle gives you access to view games from the Hero Dota: Third Chapter Tournament and the Stone Tranquility Earth Spirit Bundle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hero_Dota_Third_Chapter_T: The top semi-pro teams from the CIS region compete for a $3500 prize pool. This ticket only gives you access to view games from the Hero Dota: Third Chapter Tournament.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heroes_Within_Music_Pack: Composed by community artist Daniel Sadowski
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heroic_Effigy: A posed hero statue that can be equipped to customize your base.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heroic_Effigy_of_Fame: A hero statue commemorating an event in a Tournament Match.  Can be posed.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heroic_Effigy_of_Solid_Go: Celebrate The International with a solid gold posed hero statue, complete with an exclusive Aegis of Champions pedestal, that can be equipped to customize your base.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heroic_Effigy_of_The_Fall: Celebrate The Fall 2016 Battle Pass with a posed hero statue, complete with an exclusive pedestal, that can be equipped to customize your base.
Celebrate The Fall 2016 Battle Pass with a posed hero statue, complete with an exclusive pedestal, that can be equipped to customize your base.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heroic_Effigy_of_The_Inte: Celebrate The International with a posed hero statue, complete with an exclusive Aegis of Champions pedestal, that can be equipped to customize your base.
Celebrate The International with a posed hero statue, complete with an exclusive Aegis of Champions pedestal, that can be equipped to customize your base.
Celebrate The International with a posed hero statue, complete with an exclusive Aegis of Champions pedestal, that can be equipped to customize your base.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Heroic_Effigy_of_Winter_2: Celebrate Winter 2016 with a gilded, posed hero statue that can be equipped to customize your base.
Celebrate Winter 2016 with an icy, posed hero statue that can be equipped to customize your base.
Celebrate Winter 2016 with an icy, posed hero statue that can be equipped to customize your base.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hexgill_the_Lane_Shark: Hexgill was just like any other ordinary lane shark, stalking the well-worn paths and hiding in the trees, waiting to pounce.  But a lane shark's life is a simple thing, lacking in higher meaning.  Hexgill knew there was must be more.  When caught in a net and offered a chance to serve as courier, he knew he'd found his calling in life.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hidden_Flower: Includes all of the items in the 'Hidden Flower' set for Templar Assassin plus a loading screen:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hidden_Vector: Of all Korumite scholars, those deserving of greatest respect were the Spirit Wardens. At times, Inai will abandon austerity to don their garb -- though none alive know why.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hidden_Vector__Armor: Of all Korumite scholars, those deserving of greatest respect were the Spirit Wardens. At times, Inai will abandon austerity to don their garb -- though none alive know why.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hidden_Vector__Belt: Of all Korumite scholars, those deserving of greatest respect were the Spirit Wardens. At times, Inai will abandon austerity to don their garb -- though none alive know why.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hidden_Vector__Blade: Of all Korumite scholars, those deserving of greatest respect were the Spirit Wardens. At times, Inai will abandon austerity to don their garb -- though none alive know why.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hidden_Vector__Hat: Of all Korumite scholars, those deserving of greatest respect were the Spirit Wardens. At times, Inai will abandon austerity to don their garb -- though none alive know why.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_High_Fly_Winter_Cup_2016: The High Fly Winter Cup 2016 tournament is played by teams from Kazakhstan, competing for cash prizes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_High_School_Starleague_Do: The High School Starleague (HSL) is the premiere high school gaming tournament in North America, encompassing 7,000 schools and 30,000 students to date. Sign up and compete in the largest high school tournament in existence!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_High_School_Starleague_Sp: The High School Starleague (HSL) is the premiere high school gaming tournament in North America, encompassing 7,000 schools and 30,000 students to date. Sign up and compete in the largest high school tournament in existence!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_High_School_Starleague_Wi: The High School Starleague (HSL) is the premiere high school gaming tournament in North America, encompassing 7,000 schools and 30,000 students to date. Sign up and compete in the largest high school tournament in existence!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Highborn_Reckoning_Set: Includes all of the items in the 'Highborn Reckoning' set for Riki:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hitbox_EU_Championship_#4: 8 invited teams complete single elimination round to claim the 2.500 Euro prize pool!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hitbox_European_Champions: 8 invited teams complete single elimination rounds to claim the 2.500 prize pool!
8 invited teams complete single elimination round to claim the $2,500 prize pool!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hitbox_Obutto_Dota2_Champ: Hitbox Obutto Dota 2 Championship features the top eight teams from South-East Asian competing in a double elimination format for $3,000 cash prizes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_HlotlFeather_Necklace: Among the shrouded reaches of Xhacatocatl hunt terrible beasts, fanged and feathered. It is after the fashion of these stalkers that the Bloodseeker has been molded.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_HobblyBob: The fashionable way to keep bugs out of your sights.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hollow_Jack:
Tired of hauling a Diretide sack?
	Just hand it off to Hollow Jack!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Holy_Spear_of_Images: In each blade is reflected an army.  In each strike is reflected an ideal.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Holy_Words_of_the_Hieroph: A Hierophant of the Omniscience must always heed the words of his order.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Honey_Heist_Baby_Roshan: This little guy will go to any length necessary to feed his honey habit.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hood_of_Endless_Intellect: The Invoker has little need for this hood's magical intellect boosting enchantments. He is already far more intelligent than you could possibly ever comprehend.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hood_of_Lucid_Torment:
The dreamer's eyes are opened to a world of anguish.

This item can be upgraded with the 'Lucid Torment Style Unlock' granted to players who complete at least 40 stars on the Path of the Protector.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hood_of_Resonant_Vibrance: There is little that cannot be understood by one trained to know the powers beyond.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hood_of_the_Cruel_Magicia:
What mind muses within the shadows? Sometimes mystery itself can be cruelty.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hood_of_the_Demonic_Vesse: These items were created in partnership with Alliance, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hood_of_the_Frozen_Feathe: A day before the wizard descended into the glacier to begin his hibernation, he offered Crystal Maiden these last, precious gifts: armor and a staff, strong as ice but light as a feather, believed to have once belonged to a winter deity.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hood_of_the_Hierophant: A Hierophant of the Omniscience must always approach with head bowed.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hood_of_the_Infernal_Maw: While some amongst the Ultimyr faculty share concerns regarding the peculiar nature of Chief Curator Lannik's studies, none can deny that under his watch the Academy's archives of arcane knowledge have grown incomparably.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hood_of_the_Mothbinder: Dim though it has become, the spark of life that holds fast within the heart of the Death Prophet blazes like a signal beacon in the endless darkness of death's abyss, beckoning all manner of feasting shades that long to taste the essence of the animate world.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hood_of_the_Northlight: Ezalor is known throughout the realms as Keeper of the radiance of day, but legends from the remote, snowbound villages of the Wailing Mountains tell of him appearing in another guise: that of a champion of the lost, a bearer of the guiding light of the North Star.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hood_of_the_Rowdy_Firebra: \"I'm all for a good riot. But never got on much with looters. They don't like my style. They complain about it, but their screams stop eventually.\"
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hood_of_the_Scarlet_Raven: Fed on quivering heart-meat, the raven's inhuman eyes hum with scarlet hunger.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hood_of_the_Wandering_Fla: Seeking to restore the mantras of the Guardian Flame far beyond the embers of his ignition pyre in the Wailing Mountains, Xin loosed his remnants into the fury of a passing storm, casting them out in search of all who might still carry his spark.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hook_of_the_Atniw: Nature chose her guardian well, as any true warrior chooses a weapon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hook_of_the_Mad_Harvester: You want your meat tender, right?  Gotta bring it in close for that.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hook_of_the_Royal_Butcher: Though the carnage may go on without end, there are those alive still who can recall when it began. Ah, to be young and in the employ of the bloody King Brandalon once more.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hookblade_of_Skadi: In the depths of Dark Reef Prison, Slark dug up this Skadi Blade, buried by some long-forgotten inmate. This mysterious weapon encouraged him in his escape from Dark Reef, and silenced at least one guardian's cry of alarm along the way.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Horn_Mask: The bleached satyr horn mounted atop this mask is said to allow the wearer to channel an ancestor's power.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Horn_of_Luminous_Crystal: An enchantment passed down through the generations since the cold, dark heart of the last ice age, the Horn of the Luminous Crystal is a mark of distinction worthy of only the greatest warriors.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Horn_of_the_Hidden_Hive: Each Nyx Assassin's third kill is marked with the bestowing of this great horn--a ceremonial piece that must be blooded repeatedly if it is to be retained.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Horns_of_Blight: The beautiful horns of the succubus. Worn proudly by the queen herself.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Horns_of_Deep_Magma: These Player Items are created in partnership with Evil Geniuses, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Horns_of_Noblesse: A set of horns worthy of a king.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Horns_of_The_Malicious_Ef: Into the mortal universe pierce the horns of purest strife.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Horns_of_Twisted_Wisdom: Twisted is the mind that broods beneath these twisted horns. Twisted are the intentions that issue from that mind. Twisted is the fate of those who encounter Leshrac.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Horns_of_Wild_Reprisal: Includes particles and an ability icon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Horns_of_the_Betrayer: Though his mind remains very much his own, Lion has found that each life he takes with his grafted limb further feeds the transfiguration of his flesh, even infusing some of his other magics with aspects of the demon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Horns_of_the_Bone_Scryer: \"I scry with my little eye...a fabulous piece of headgear!\"
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Horns_of_the_Crypt_Guardi: With these horns to protect his skull, none shall quench the soul-fire of Clinkz.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Horns_of_the_Death_Charge:
With these four deadly horns, the Spirit Breaker has assembled a form that suits him well. They are an outward emblem of his inner strength.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Horns_of_the_Ephemeral_Ha: Chaotic emanations from a plane of violent power are conducted through these focal-horns and imbue Spectre with energy.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Horns_of_the_Iron_Will: Upon otherworldly horns are fiend and foe gored.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Horns_of_the_Malignant_Co: Far away beneath the Sunken Cities and through the Infernal Hollow, Buki'vak the Corrupted dwells in the depths forever expanding his corruption throughout the sea. Hearing of his power, Lion seeked to harvest his parts for a fresh demonoplasty. After a strenuous battle he defeated Buki'vak and gained the hand he desired as a reward, but it was not without cost. Just as his previous hand transformed him, so did this one. He became afflicted with the Malignant Corruption, causing unseemly shards of Obsidian to grow from his body and further disfigure him into something even more unrecognizeable from his original form.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Horns_of_the_PeaceBringer: Horns curved into a sigil of peace.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Horns_of_the_Wicked_Succu: From deepest twilight come temptations dark and terrifying.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Housemark_of_the_Great_Gr: Lycan long ago gave up the crest of his acestral lands.  That crest died the day he was reborn a wolf, and now a new housemark is worn upon his shoulder.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Howling_Wind_Bow: In the endless chill of the far north, it is said that the cold of death comes on a howling wind brought by a great white wolf.  Many a hunter has attempted to slay this grave spirit.  Yet in all the known histories, the stories record only one bow that has ever fired strong enough, and true enough, to pierce its side.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_HueBR_Cup_Season_1: 32 teams will compete for the HueBR Cup trophy and a prize of R$ 650!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_HueBR_Cup_Season_2: The best amateur teams from Brazil compete for the top spot in teh HueBR Cup Season 2.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Humble_Drifter: Contains all of the items in the 'Humble Drifter' set for Phantom Lancer plus a loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Hungarian_Dota_2_League_S:
Welcome to the Hungarian DOTA 2 League Tournament site!  HD2L is a start up hosted by the Hungarian DOTA 2 community. 
	
	The placement rounds have passed and the 26 teams that qualified have been assigned to divisions accordingly.
	
	In order to help with the organization of this tournament, we have started this website.  Here you will find information about the league, your upcoming fixtures and help facilitate communication with other teams.
	
	We kindly ask all participants to read the game regulations linked below.
	
	You can find information, rules and regulations on the website: https://www.facebook.com/hd2lpage/
	
	We are extremely grateful for the huge amount of interest in this tournament and would like to thank all league participants.
	
	We hope You are as excited as we are!  
	
	See you at the competition!
	
	Admins of -HD2L-

	You can find information, rules and regulations on the website: https://www.facebook.com/hd2lpage/
	
	We are extremely grateful for the huge amount of interest in this tournament and would like to thank all league participants.
	
	We hope You are as excited as we are!  
	
	See you at the competition!
	
	Admins of -HD2L-

Hewn upon an elemental forge--this helm draws energy from deposits sewn deep within the earth, harnessing the attractive forces of iron. This is the first try of a major E-Sports sponsor to lift up Israel's Dota 2 community to a competitive level and we have risen to the challenge.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Itsy: Not so itsy, say you? Her enormous elder siblings click their mandibles and roll their many eyes at their sister's puny proportions. To prove her worth, this fleet-footed spiderling will eagerly scuttle to your service and weave her web around your heart!

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_JJ_Lins_Timekeeper_Music_:
Includes JJ Lin's Timekeeper Music Pack and 'The Timekeeper' set for Templar Assassin.
	
	The Timekeeper TA set draws inspiration from JJ Lin's Timeline World Tour. In the world where man chimes the hour, our days are precious precisely because they are limited. From music to gaming, he weaves his role of The Timekeeper into the Templar Assassin. The package is designed such that it comes in gold or silver lining, with JJ and SMG logo on each side of the shoulders. The Templar Assassin's characteristic colour is purple, which happens to be a special color for JJ as well.

So long as his goddess tends to all of life, the jade warrior will answer the call to protect it.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Kin_of_the_Sangstrath_Fol: Rich in oral history, Ulfsaar's kin still celebrate the legends of the Sangstrath--ancient guardians of a fabled civilization and the first ancestors to settle the current lands of the ursine tribe after disaster befell their own.

This International 2019 Battle Pass reward enables an upgraded style to be unlocked on the Kin of the Sangstrath Fold set for Ursa through the style menu. You can use this item multiple times to unlock styles on all of the items in the set.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Kindred_of_the_Iron_Drago: The blood of Slyrak flows strong through the Dragon Knight, and its transformative powers have long been a thing of legend.  For a chosen few who have received dragon blood, the magic runs unusually thick, its effects magnified and distorted.  In these rare recipients, the reach of the transformation is enhanced, drawing strength not from any single dragon but from the oldest ancestral strains, and a forgotten age when whole kingdoms shook with fear, and eyeless, armored dragons raged wars across the countryside.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_LGD_Pennant:
Show your support with a Team Pennant!
	
	Having a Team Pennant in your Armory will increase that team's Pennant Score which is shown during matches in Valve-supported tournaments, and it will make you eligible to receive item drops while spectating their live tournament matches. Pennants for the same team can be combined to increase their contribution to that team's Pennant Score.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_LGDs_Golden_Skipper: The Golden Skipper is a species long-rumored to exist, but rarely seen in the wild. It can only be assumed that this is one such rare beast.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Lamb_to_the_Slaughter: Invented long ago as a way to combat insomnia, this spell will have you counting sheep in no time.  Provided you can only count to one.  With a wave of his wand, Shadow Shaman can clad even the deadliest wolf in sheep's clothing.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Laments_of_the_Dead: Forged by a necromantic smith, on whose anvil tortured souls were hammered into obedience, it is Rotund'jere's pleasure to make sure this deadly scythe fulfills its only wish: to reap the souls of the living.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Lantern_of_Deaths_Last_Li: With this lantern Warlock peers into the shadows of death itself.  Death shrinks from the light.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Lantern_of_the_Archivist: Certain tomes in the Ultimyr Archives have never seen the light of day, and never will. But their pages have seen this light many times.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Lantern_of_the_Infernal_M: While some amongst the Ultimyr faculty share concerns regarding the peculiar nature of Chief Curator Lannik's studies, none can deny that under his watch the Academy's archives of arcane knowledge have grown incomparably.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Lash_of_the_Lizard_Kin: It was an interesting and nearly fatal day when Rhasta realized that nothing prevented him from using his trademark transformations for even more useful alterations but the expandable limits of his own imagination.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Last_Judgement: When Doom passes Judgment, there is never any doubt as to its validity.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_LatinCup_Summer_2016: Enlace Gamer latest project by Pinzak Network investing in the LATAM market brings the LatinCup Summer 2016 an exclusive tournament for the Latin American region where each country will send their best team to represent them in a format similar to the Copa America for a prize pool of $2500.00 USD
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Latticean_Hierarchy: Already of singular status amongst his kind, the zealot assassin's powers and influence grew even stronger with the introduction of the shimmering crystals to his hive.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Latticean_Shards: The zealot assassin burrowed deeper than any of his predecessors had ever dared. Striking a rich seam of dense crystalline formation, he soon found the armored plates of his exoskeleton coated in the shimmering substance.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_League_RazerMiniMadness: Razer Mini Madness is a Dota 2 tournament hosted by It's Gosu eSports and generously sponsored by Razer. 	This will be a Captains Mode tournament for teams with less than a 3k average team MMR, and a maximum of 3.5k solo per player to keep in the spirit of new players.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Lefty: Dreaming of a less destructive life, this daring hand convinced its mate to sever it from their malevolent body and has been on the run ever since.
