Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Opus_of_the_Vizier_Exile:
While his talents may no longer directly serve Damathryx's cause, Ish'Kafel commits his legacy to the bindings of a massive tome with the hope it may one day be recovered by some planesfaring kin.

Contains the Opus of the Vizier Exile set for Dark Seer, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Orb_of_Deliverance: His search led deep into the earth, down into ruins undisturbed by surface dwellers for millennia. Every scrap of evidence he'd found told him a greater, far older civilization had preceded those whose technologies he had already pilfered. But there were reasons no surface dwellers had come this far in ages, and Disruptor would need to modify his equipment with secrets found along the way just to ensure he might continue a bit further.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Order_of_the_Wandering_Fl:
Seeking to restore the mantras of the Guardian Flame far beyond the embers of his ignition pyre in the Wailing Mountains, Xin loosed his remnants into the fury of a passing storm, casting them out in search of all who might still carry his spark.

Contains the Order of the Wandering Flame set for Ember Spirit, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Orena_Dota_2_Cup: 32 South African teams compete for a total prize pool of R12,700 and gaming equipment from SteelSeries!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Origin_of_the_Unmaking: What challenge is offered by the mortal mind to one who toys with gods?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Origins_of_Faith: At all times the Anti-Mage feels the flames of defining loss burning against his back, pushing him ever forward in pursuit of his blood-sworn oath.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ormr_the_Lunar_Dragon: From a race of dragons that normally patrols the dark side of the moon, Ormr wanted to see the world.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ornaments_of_the_Arkturan: There is power yet in these old bones.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Ornaments_of_the_Gleaming:
Though they shine by moonlight, in truth the blades serve to draw the eye away from death's true instrument.

This cosmically rare prize was awarded as a random drop while opening Immortal Treasures during The International 2019 Battle Pass season.

Only one Emblem can be active on a team, so in matches with multiple players with Emblems, the active Emblems are determined by players' Battle Pass levels. Expires prior to The International 2020.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pack_of_the_Blood_Stained: A necessity for traveling light across a hostile waste which offers nothing in the way of sustenance or shelter.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pack_of_the_Occultists_Pu: Mundane prey attracts the uninspired predator. A distinguished huntsman, on the other hand, seeks a prize not bound by earthly coils.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pack_of_the_Verdant_Outca: Never to plant his roots, always to wander the wilds.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Paddapon_of_Ribbitar:
Includes a Rare Prismatic Socket and custom colored particles. Socketing a Prismatic Gem will allow some of these colors to be replaced with the gem's color.

Padda'pon drums the song of death until the lives of Witch Doctor's enemies are extinguished.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pads_of_the_Blood_Stained: Relentless sun, scouring winds and the enemy's desperate slashes--these pads are proof against all.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pads_of_the_Crimson_Cutth: By the time Gondar was finished, little else remained of the Crimson Cut-throat's armor.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Paean_of_the_Ink_Dragon: Contains the Paean of the Ink Dragon set for Grimstroke, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pale_Augur: To hear the baleful dirge is to feel its compelling hunger. It calls the sleepless dead to stir beneath the battlefield, grasping upwards to hasten the world's decay.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pale_Mausoleum: The dirge howls from the deep. Its call is irresistible, its song a melody of dark and cold. All will fall under the spell, be they tyrant or peasant, soldier or thief. The dirge shall claim.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Palladium_Amateur_Battle: Semi-pro and amateur teams gather to play for the prize pool of $60.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_PandaFx_Tournament_1Vs1: PandaFx  200 Players in a 1Vs1 Tournament where they need to prove their skills to use only Pandas (Earth Spirit, Ember Spirit, Storm Spirit, Brewmaster) and a Prize Pool of 150$ or more!!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pangolin_Carapace: This shelled carapace armor is meant to offer both protection and camouflage.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pangolin_Scarf: A bright scarf marked with the sigil of the Pangolin hunters' guild.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pangolin_Shoulder_Armor: Mastercrafted pauldrons of the Pangolin guild. They offer the strength of platemail at a fraction of the weight.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pantaloons_of_the_Freelan: These fine pantaloons show that Sven's travels have led him into gold as much as glory.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_PantheonES_Cup: The top Dota 2 teams in Australia compete for the PantheonES CUP. Starting on the 21st and concluding on the 23rd, the tournament will put eight of the best Oceanic teams against each other to battle for a PantheonES Cup Title.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Paraflare_Cannon: Drifting in low-Clock orbit, this loyal satellite might not warrant designation as a moon, but it is no less honored a companion for all that. Its slow-falling flares are thorough spoilers of every enemy's shadowy plans.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Paragons_Poise: Some equipment hidden in the vault of Emauracus remains there for good reason -- certain pieces that deem a bearer unworthy will kill presumptuous wielders long before they encounter signs of an enemy.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Paragons_Pride: Some equipment hidden in the vault of Emauracus remains there for good reason -- certain pieces that deem a bearer unworthy will kill presumptuous wielders long before they encounter signs of an enemy.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Paragons_Pride_Bundle: Some equipment hidden in the vault of Emauracus remains there for good reason -- certain pieces that deem a bearer unworthy will kill presumptuous wielders long before they encounter signs of an enemy.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Paragons_Rebuke: The forgemaster of Emauracus boasts he's the finest smith alive. Some allow he may be right. Yet even he can only marvel at the enchanted works of the old ones--those long-dead knights who were amongst the first mortals to receive the blessings of the Omniscience.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Patch_Stash_and_Hobb: Patch charges in, and the others must follow. Stash bears the load, but utters no foul oaths. Hobb is just stuck here, consoled some by fresh oats.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pattern_of_the_Silken_Que: Contains Pattern of the Silken Queen set for Broodmother, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldron_of_AlFusha: Al-Fusha was a great satyr general in service to Verodicia. It is said that he fell in battle and much of his wargear lost. Of it, this spiked and goddess-blessed pauldron remains.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldron_of_Sir_Davion: A dragon knight is protected not by armor, but his faith.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldron_of_Teardrop_Ice: Of the twelve legendary teardrop gems, eight were shattered, creating a vast tundra where once stood a burning waste.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldron_of_the_Blood_Moo: Banehallow often takes solace in the company of any fellow afflicted he might encounter in his wanderings. Not all, however, find the company of their own kind so agreeable.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldron_of_the_Chiseled_: A heavy counterweight to a heavy blade.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldron_of_the_Dreadborn: In the eyes of King Ostarion, the lives of his champions lost fighting to fuel the Wraith-Night rituals were merely his due tribute.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldron_of_the_Nimble_Ed: Give your foe no angle from which to strike.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldron_of_the_Red_Conqu: It seems a shame to cover Axe's mighty thews with pauldrons, but at least these are suitably red.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldron_of_the_Silent_Gu: Crafted by ancient artisans, these pauldrons protect Silencer from those who would do him harm.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldron_of_the_Warriors_: The rogue shoulders more than his share of grief and retribution.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldrons_of_Eternal_Harv: Long past time evil takes its fill, the feast goes on forevermore.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldrons_of_Fury: Upon your broad shoulders, the weight of the war rests.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldrons_of_Impending_Tr: In the fires of the pit, these Pauldrons were forged of rancid steel and demon hide.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldrons_of_Polymorphia: Water, they say, has a memory--but Morphling's dissolves with every form he takes. These pauldrons serve as a reminder of his original being, rooted in Polymorphia.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldrons_of_Retribution: With shoulders high, Dragonus gazes far across the world to search those who have incurred the anger of the Skywrath.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldrons_of_Sacred_Light: Some brethren proselytize without speaking a word; their sermons may be heard only in the ringing blows of the hammer.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldrons_of_the_Battle_C: Once a field filled with swords and storms, Lina left little but a smoking crater and handful of grateful allies.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldrons_of_the_Battlera:
To some authorities, the line between ranger and ruffian is nearly nonexistent.

Includes pauldrons, bracer, waistcoat, and boots, and can be upgraded with the 'Bindings of the Battleranger Style Unlock' granted to players who complete all fifteen Three-Star objectives on the Path of the Spellbinder.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldrons_of_the_Boreal_W: Forged by the Northern Drow from the ore of the chasm, these pauldrons bear the mark of the Boreal Watch.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldrons_of_the_Crypt_Gu: These razor-sharp pauldrons bring new meaning to the term shoulder blade.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldrons_of_the_Frozen_F: A day before the wizard descended into the glacier to begin his hibernation, he offered Crystal Maiden these last, precious gifts: armor and a staff, strong as ice but light as a feather, believed to have once belonged to a winter deity.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldrons_of_the_Gwimyeon: To truly conquer a foe, one must best both stem and root.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldrons_of_the_Infernal: While some amongst the Ultimyr faculty share concerns regarding the peculiar nature of Chief Curator Lannik's studies, none can deny that under his watch the Academy's archives of arcane knowledge have grown incomparably.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldrons_of_the_Northern: Generations from now, the denizens of Njord's Hearth shall know Windranger by these pauldrons should she ever return to their demesne.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldrons_of_the_Occultis: Mundane prey attracts the uninspired predator. A distinguished huntsman, on the other hand, seeks a prize not bound by earthly coils.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldrons_of_the_One_True: In an age lost even to his own memory, Ostarion fed his lust for eternal life not with spectral essence, but a nigh-unending harvest of bone. The walls of his palace were formed of fired bone; the streets paved with bones of every sort of creature and every enemy. And those of the flesh who entered this domain took great care, for the King was first and foremost a collector, and nothing moved in the Empire of Bone without summoning the gaze of his unblinking eyes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldrons_of_the_Shifting:
Upon his demise, many of the sorcerer Throsho's unique armaments lay shattered.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pauldrons_of_the_Timekeep: \"Swift, agile, silent and fast, Templar Assassin fits my favorite style of play in DOTA2.\" -JJ LIN

Show your support with a Team Pennant!

Pennants for the same team can be combined to increase their contribution to that team's Pennant Score.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Penumbral_Cloak: A cloak no less concealing than the night's long shadows.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Penumbral_Crest: Emblazoned with the Crepuscular Sigil, this crest draws darkness over its wearer.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Penumbral_Hood: The assassin's face is hidden, yet you can still feel through the shadows the power of her gaze.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Penumbral_Shawl: Even creatures of the twilight can scarcely see the wearer of this shawl.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Penumbral_Vesture_Set: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Penumbral Vesture' set for Phantom Assassin:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Penumbral_Warblade: At the edge of darkness, her warblade shimmers like a piece of dusk cut loose.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Peregrine_Lance: As the peregrine flies, so too shall this blade.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Perversions_of_the_Bloodw: There was no prize in life Ethreain coveted more than the Bloodwhorl Crown, rumors of which drove him from kingdom to kingdom on a merciless hunt, and eventually to his mortal demise. Little did he know that no living creature may wear the crown, and had his quest succeeded before failing first, it would have proven his greatest failure of all.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Petals_of_the_Verdant_Out: As ages spent and seasons changed the leaves gathered upon his shoulder, returned to flourishing life.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Phantom_Advent: The many aspects of Mercurial are fragments of a single form no longer -- for one has stolen away from the many, and the realities of a new Spectre rise. Enticed and trapped by a cursed set of armor, a solitary shade of Mercurial finds that with each soul she harvests for the blighted plate, a stronger sense of self arrives along with it. While at first such forced separation enraged her, she now seeks this tantalizing freedom... Killing whomever she needs to earn more.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Prize_of_the_Saltworn_Mar:
When he was just a lowly midshipman, and a young boy first at sea, the stories were meant to frighten. Whole fleets lost to a razortooth pointer--measuring longer than a frigate and twice as fast--hunting for sailors in their ships like a wolf seeks marrow in the bone. But Kunkka paid the tales no mind. He thought them mere rum-fueled scuttle, swapped to scare the cabin boys, and he had ranks to climb. It was only many years later, after he earned his gold-laced buttons and half his legend hunting and killing such a beast, that he truly understood...there are always bigger fish in the sea.

This item will never be tradeable or purchasable on the marketplace. Unlock it at Battle Level 225 before The International ends. Players who complete the accompanying Quest Path will also receive an alternate style unlock for the Prestige item.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Progenitors_Bane: There are many who have long yearned in secret for the war that Mars now openly declares--including some amongst the race that first helped his father capture the thunderbolt and were willing to risk such a feat again.

	Each item includes a default style that rethemes these Immortal hallmarks to match this year's event, and a second style unlocked through playing that transforms each one into a form more akin to the recent offerings of the Immortal Treasure chests.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Provocation_of_Ruin: There lived those amongst the masked ones who had--through violation of one creed or another--been stripped of their honor and made to exist on the outskirts of society, unmasked and unable to influence the affairs of the Isle. Oft victimized by the common folk and lords alike, to defend these wretched folk even in the face of highborn deviance would invite certain exile--a fate considered far worse.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pudgling: There's them that says a well-fed lad's a happy lad.  They never met Pudge.  If it's a bite-sized snack for the road you want, he's got just the thing.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pudgling_Golden_Hook_Upgr: This item enables the 'Golden Hook'' style to be unlocked on the Pudgling through the style menu.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pulsar_Remnant: Gilded in celestial metals extracted from the cosmic barrage of Selemene's protective storm, the thrum of this bow sounds the invitation to more of its heavenly kin.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pumpkin_Head: Equippable in the global loadout, transforms the head of any hero you are playing into a seasonal Pumpkin Head that will really light up the battlefield.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Punctured_Crest: To face the guardians of the Narrow Maze is to deny eternity itself. Yet there are those who would dare defy their fate and strike at the source of their torment, only to be thrown down time and again. These insolent few may soon find themselves flung to the darkest reaches of the herebetween, and left to wander fateless, for all eternity.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Purple_Minnow_Ward_Upgrad: This International 2017 reward enables an upgraded color style to be unlocked for the Shifty Minnow ward in the style menu.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pursuit_of_the_Ember_Demo: Contains the Pursuit of the Ember Demons set for Huskar, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pyre: Give up hope and cast yourself upon the blazing Pyre!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pyrexaec_Floe: The Mer still tell tales of the dreadful night, when a raiding party of the finest Slithereen warriors returned with only two survivors. As each found the words, they warned of a two-headed demon that protected the bluffs of Grosche. At first the sea itself had saved the marauders from the lancing flames of one vile head. But the other, with the breath of frost and eyes of red, turned their own waters against them. The two survivors could only watch as their fellows were frozen in place atop icy waves, helpless to escape the renewed assault of cleansing fire.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pyrexaec_Flux: For the children who live in the underground caverns of the Riverwarren, the Day of Pyres is filled with stories and celebrations of a noble dragon protector who long ago descended from the surface world to help the Riverwarren's people in a time of great need. As the children get older, dreams of the dragon's return will assuredly fade, and attentions turn to fine spirits and foolhardy flame play, but for a time their young minds will grasp the truth.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Pyrion_Flax_Announcer_Pac: This pack replaces the Default announcer and Mega-Kills announcer with the unique and unruly humor of Dota 2 satirist Pyrion Flax.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Qaldin_Assassins_Dagger: Few hunters ever make contact with a Qaldin Assassin.  Fewer still are able to commission a blade from them.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Qaldin_Assassins_Glaive: Perfectly balanced and unbelievably sharp, the weapons of a Qaldin Assassin are considered a luxury among those who kill for their living.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Qaldin_Assassins_Slicer: Owning the weapon of a Qaldin Assassin is a mark of success that few hunters ever achieve.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Qualifier_BoraDota_STARS_: Qualifier for professional competition BoraDota STARS 2 BestGamers. Each qualifier will consist of 32 teams fighting for places in the main competition.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Quas_Essence: A crystal of pure Quas energy. It is cold and heavy, radiating a magical aura of stubborn tenacity.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Quirts_Summer_Stash: That disreputable scoundrel Quirt has lost a chest of plundered loot! You will need <font color='#9da1a9'>Quirt's Summer Key</font> to open the chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Beware! At the end of <font color='#9da1a9'>September 16, 2013</font> this chest will crumble into useless dust. This chest contains one of several mysterious new items.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Quiver_of_the_Northern_Wi: Held safely in this quiver, Windranger's arrows defy the threat of cold winds that might cause their sinews to crack.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Quiver_of_the_Shadowcat: Quiver and arrows made from the finest materials the forest offers and crafted together with the metals of the drow.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Quiver_of_the_Urushin_Hun:
Though known for a violent and capricious temper, the burning bowman is much revered throughout The Hoven.

This item can be upgraded with the 'Urushin Huntsman Style Unlock' granted to players who complete all fifteen Three-Star objectives on the Path of the Rogue.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Realm_of_Chaos_Pass:
This pass activates premium content in the Realm of Chaos custom game and supports the creators of this custom game.
Owning a Realm of Chaos Custom Game Pass will Unlock:
Gold UI Frame and Personal Title
Expand player's backpack from 36 to 54
Unlocks achievement system on player's account
Blessing Tree offering the following Boosters for all players:
Virtue Booster; virtue earned per monster killed increased by 100% (Stacks with other Pass owners)
Gold Booster; gold earned per monster killed is increased by 100% (Stacks with other Pass owners)
Upgrade Booster; increases upgrade success rate by 5% (Each additional Pass owner increases this by 1%)
Experience Booster; experience earned per monster is increased by 100% (Stacks with other Pass owners)
Saint Area opens without a key
Every State mastered gives 3x Upgrade Protection Stone and 1x Injection Protection Stone.
Player resurrection time decreased by 5 seconds
Players receive 1x Demon Wolf Pellet at the start of the game
New skill animations, icons and effects
New function to see loot lists when you click on a creep or boss
New mode: GM's Dedication, summons a Game Master to defend your base for you while you freely roam the map and enjoy the game's content. Once enabled, you will not be able to join the speed-rank board.

Expires 30 days after purchase
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Reapers_Wreath: Few topside rangers have ever seen the magnificent bloom of a bloodroot tree -- a specimen found only in sanctified underground caverns where long ago battles of horrific violence were waged to determine the fate of all Drow kind -- fewer still would survive an intrusion upon such holy ground to collect materials meant to wage further war. In fact, only one steeped in the etiquette of the Drow themselves might know the proper supplication required to hew a branch and live to use it.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Reaver: Forged in volcanic fire, bathed in the blood of countless foes, the Reaver is a weapon that has never known mercy.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_River_Vial_Blood:
Initially comes with 50 charges

Auctioned from the estate of a brilliant but failed alchemist, these mystical vials have the power to transform liquid water into nearly any substance. However, a steady hand is required. The next item on the auction block was the seeping corpse of the sneezing thaumaturge himself. Vial art, indeed.

Claim your River Vial at the in-game shop. Pour the contents into the river to transform it for 10 minutes. Transforming the river will consume one charge from your Armory supply, however no charges will be used if the item is sold, dropped, or destroyed during a game. Only one Vial can affect the river at a time.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Roshpit_Champions_Pass:
This pass activates premium content in the Roshpit Champions custom game and supports the creators of this custom game.
Owning a Roshpit Champions Custom Game Pass will Unlock:
8 more character save slots
18 more stash slots
A 50% immortal drop rate buff and 10% EXP gain. This buff is shared with all party members and stacks with other premium players.
A gold kill counter at the top of the UI to show who is a premium player.
Most importantly, purchasing a premium ticket supports the game and allows us
to build content better, faster, more consistently.

100% of the game's content will remain available to free tier players. Premium players just receive these quality of life benefits and support the game's development.
Expires 30 days after purchase.

SIC aims to provide a fair and professional platform for all Beijing university enthusiasts to demonstrate their skills, while also getting the young college players ready for the Dota2 professional ladders in the near future. The total Prize pool for the tournament-ship is currently sitting at 128,000 CNY.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_SUQA_Winter_Solo_Cup: Open tournament where 64 players compete for the $150 prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sabatons_of_the_Crested_C:
Below decks, behind a line of artillery primed to fire, sure footing is essential.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Saberhorns_Belt: This belt once belonged to Saberhorn, a legendary general from a bygone era.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Saberhorns_Heavy_Chopper: The legendary general Saberhorn was said to have been able to end any duel with a single swing.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Saberhorns_Helm: The helm of the legendary general Saberhorn has seen countless battles and wars.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Saberhorns_Pauldron: The sigil of Saberhorn's army is carved into the shoulder.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sable_Cup_2015__Defense_o: The Sable Cup is a Defense of the Australians non-professional DotA tournament focused to play in a competitive environment for Australian and New Zealand amateur Dota 2 teams.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacral_Apparel: The shrunken skull of the warrior who killed the first Tale-Teller has found a special place of honor with all Tellers since.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacred_Bones_Bracers: The runes upon the cuffs confer strength and courage upon the wearer.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacred_Bones_Helmet: The warriors of the Dezun Order hold dear the bones of those whose sacrifice has come before.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacred_Bones_Offhand_Weap: The bones of the earth that make the blade of this dagger are no less sacred than the warrior who once held it.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacred_Bones_Set: Includes all of the items in the \"Sacred Bones\" set for Huskar.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacred_Bones_Shoulder: The bones of those who came before are brought to the field of battle once more.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacred_Bones_Spear: The spear of a warrior remembers the chaos of many battles, and the taste of many lives.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacred_Light:
Some brethren proselytize without speaking a word; their sermons may be heard only in the ringing blows of the hammer.

Contains the Sacred Light set for Omniknight, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacred_Orb_Carapace: Once in a thousand cyclings of the hive, Nyx grants one of her Assassins the Carapace of the Sacred Orb. It is the most painful of molts...but legend requires great sacrifice.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacred_Orb_Helm: The Nyx Assassin, under the influence of the Sacred Orb, perceives even more of Nyx's bounty: So many targets to reap!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacred_Orb_Set: Includes all items in the 'Sacred Orb' set for Nyx Assassin:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacred_Orb_Venom_Claws: Against certain foes, the Nyx assassin imbues its blades with a venom that is their only weakness. Praise Nyx that they have even one such vulnerability!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacrificial_Blade_of_the_: The blade has seen the belly of many a beast so that knowledge may pour forth and forewarn those in need.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sacrificial_Shortblade: If it was good enough to cut the heart from a heretic, then it is good enough to cut the heart from anyone.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sagas_of_the_Cymurrin_Sag: Some amongst the Advisors to the shattered Seat of Cymurri accepted their fates without fear or anger, or complicity in Nerif's banishment. They accepted the easily beheld truth that their own decline was necessary to ensure the sanctity of their beliefs, for there was no doubting the words of an Oracle compared against the vile hearts of those with power.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Salvaged_Sword_and_Board: Sometimes you have to go with what you can find.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Samareen_Sacrifice: Contains the Samareen Sacrifice set for Huskar, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Samsung_Dota_2_Pro_League: The Cybergamer Pro League allows professional teams to compete for a prize pool which grows the more teams that participate!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Samurai_Soul: Contains all of the items in the 'Samurai Soul' set for Earthshaker plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sanction_of_the_Winged_Ha: Contains the Sanction of the Winged Harvest set for Visage, including the loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sanctums_of_the_Divine: Unlock this exclusive terrain before The International 10 Battle Pass ends. This item will never be tradeable or purchasable on the marketplace.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sandworn_Visage_of_the_An: Unearthed from the sand-scoured ruins of El'Harath, from this Visage the entire culture of the Sovereign has been resurrected.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sange_and_Yasha: A pair of magical short blades, balanced and light. Unpack this bundle to receive both Sange and Yasha for Riki.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sange_the_Backseeker: Sange, one of the two legendary moonblades, is said to be unnaturally accurate and able to change to a form that best fits the fighting style of its owner. In the hands of Riki the weapon becomes a small dagger.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sanguine_Moon_Armor: An eye for an eye makes leaves all the heroes blind.  Except for Lycan, because he's darn sure not going to lose his second eye.  You can be sure of that.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sanguine_Moon_Belt: Some have questioned the fashion sense of using a skull for a belt buckle.  The last guy who questioned it became a second belt buckle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sanguine_Moon_Head: That's not an eye-patch.  That's armor for his vision.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sanguine_Moon_Shoulder: For some heroes, a shoulder isn't a deadly weapon capable of eviscerating enemies.  Lycan isn't one of those heroes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sanguine_Royalty: Contains all of the items in the 'Sanguine Royalty' set for Queen of Pain plus loading screen. These items were created in partnership with Mushi, who will who receive a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sapphire_Cask: No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. The items in this treasure will not be tradable or marketable until March 1st, 2015.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sappler_the_Eager:
Not content to grow patiently upward, rather than waiting until he stood equal with the treetops before making his mark on the world, this earnest sapling found other means to speed the course of adventure.

Available to owners of the Winter 2017 Battle Pass and has four unlockable styles.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Saratov_Cup_Open_Finals: 100 Russian teams compete for a total prize of 50,000 Rubles!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sash_of_Deaths_Bride: When she departed, Death's Bride left little to her young apprentice.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sash_of_Divine_Ascension: A neatly tied sash is all one needs when extracting ascended vengeance.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sash_of_Yoskreth: In his gratitude, the sovereign of Yoskreth bid that fine robes be made for the warrior who had bested Sahsk's vile enchantments.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sash_of_the_Crested_Canno:
The falcon seal upon the sash is granted only to distinguished veterans of naval warfare.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sash_of_the_Fearful_Aria: Created in partnership with EternaLEnVy, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sash_of_the_Ravager: Made from the smooth belly of an otherwise spiny ravager.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sash_of_the_Third_Insight: In the eyes beyond, all that is found must then be appraised.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Saturday_DotA_League: The Saturday DotA League is a North American, amateur, DotA 2 league held on Saturdays. Free to watch.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Savage_Armor: In a savage age, before the Ursa earned the gift of speech, they communicated alliances and homelands through elaborately designed patterns and sigils.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Savage_Belt: A ceremonial covering honoring a savage time before the Ursa earned the gift of speech.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Savage_Bracer: In hallowed ceremony on honored days, the Ursa remember a savage time before they earned the gift of speech.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Savage_Helmet: A ceremonial headgarb to honor the ferocity of a savage age.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Savage_Mettle: Forged around a core of compact elemental energy, the heft of Barathrum's flail can cross the very planes of existence.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scabbards_of_the_Stormcha: Astride the focused storm, Disruptor stalks the boundaries of battle, ready to strike down his enemies and lead his tribe's return to a place of distinction and honor.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scale_of_the_Razorwyrm:
Fierce opponent turned staunch protector.

Includes all of the items in the 'Scale of the Razorwyrm' set for Ursa, which can be upgraded with the 'Scale of the Razorwyrm Style Unlock' granted to players who complete all fifteen Three-Star objectives on the Path of the Warrior.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scale_of_the_Razorwyrm_St: This International 2016 reward enables an upgraded style to be unlocked on the 'Scale of the Razorwyrm' set for Ursa through the style menu. You can use this item multiple times to unlock styles on all of the items in the set.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scarab_Pendant_of_the_Pri: This is no false idol, but an idol true, from which the sacred scarab of the faith may one day spread its golden wings and fly.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scarf_of_the_Bone_Scryer: When visions of Death bring a chill, this scarf keeps Death Prophet warm. Then again, she enjoys a little chill.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scarf_of_the_Deadly_Night: Whosoever wears this mantle, the spirit Tyrian ensures they shall shrug off any burden, while their identity and their purpose remain concealed.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scarlet_Flare_Style_Unloc: This item can be used to unlock an alternate style for the Scarlet Flare item set for Lina.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scarlet_League_Season_1: 32 Amateur teams compete for the $12,000 prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scarlet_Quarry: Contains all of the items in the 'Scarlet Quarry' set for Tiny.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scavenger_of_the_Basilisk: Contains the Scavenger of the Basilisk set for Pudge, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scavenging_Guttleslug: Those fish fresh to Dark Reef pray to Maelrawn's name that the tales of slithereen-sized guttleslugs devouring prisoners whole as they sleep are mere stories. The brinier amongst them insist guttleslugs will only eat carrion. But all things in Dark Reef will become carrion, if a guttleslug is patient enough.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scepter_of_Corrupted_Ambe: Far away beneath the Sunken Cities and through the Infernal Hollow, Buki'vak the Corrupted dwells in the depths forever expanding his corruption throughout the sea. Hearing of his power, Lion seeked to harvest his parts for a fresh demonoplasty. After a strenuous battle he defeated Buki'vak and gained the hand he desired as a reward, but it was not without cost. Just as his previous hand transformed him, so did this one. He became afflicted with the Malignant Corruption, causing unseemly shards of Obsidian to grow from his body and further disfigure him into something even more unrecognizeable from his original form.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scepter_of_the_Grand_Magu: Few know that Rubick's talents for mimicry extend to arcane assembly.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scepter_of_the_Sable_Void: To harness the powers of the burning nether requires a symbol feared for its malice.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scions_of_the_Sky_Loading: By wing and way, victory will be theirs.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scorched_Amber: Contains the Scorched Amber set for Dragon Knight
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scourge_Dominion: Contains the Scourge Dominion set for Necrophos, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scowl_of_the_Lost_Star: Created in partnership with Era, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Screeauks_Talon: Scree'auk's Talon was fashioned by a certain winged Mage, forged from shades of unrequited passion, tempered in grief, and quenched in the secret tears of her admirer. More's the pity that she uses it now, approximately half the time, to hunt him.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sculptors_Monument: No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. This treasure contains individual items.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sculptors_Pillar: No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. This treasure contains individual items.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sculptors_Pillar_2015: No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. This treasure contains full item sets.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scuttling_Scotty: Separated from his flock in an ice storm, the adventurous young pengling Scotty wandered the Blueheart Glacier, starving and alone, until he found himself rescued by a certain young Ice Maiden. Crystal Maiden nursed him back to health with love and fishy treats. Swearing to return her kindness, Scotty swore off adventuring, and now he has no urge other than to carry supplies and treats to those in need.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scythe_of_Ka: Includes custom particle and custom ability icon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scythe_of_Pestilence: Plague and pestilence are the Reaper's trusty tools for harvesting souls.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scythe_of_Sacrifice: It is an honor to be sacrificed on Phantom Assassin's scythe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scythe_of_Twin_Deaths: Heavy with the gifts granted by the plagued nobility, Rotund'jere had this frightening tool fashioned to remind those in his care of the ever-present likelihood of their demise.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scythe_of_Vyse: The most guarded relic of the cult of Vyse, it is a weapon coveted for its magical properties.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scythe_of_the_Hunters_Glo: Even the most skilled trackers may only hope to earn in a lifetime what Gondar claims on a single hunt.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Scythes_of_Sorrow: Lost to him in the final trial before his banishment to Foulfell, the reclamation of these scythes represents the penultimate step on Terrorblade's return to demonic glory. Only one aspect of his plan remains unfinished. The worlds of demon and man will soon know sorrow.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sea_Dragons_Armlet: The scaly hide of the Sea Dragon is one of the few substances tougher than Slardar's own integument.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sea_Dragons_Basher: For sport, the Slithereen hunt the great Sea Dragons of the ocean abyss. This basher is fashioned from the spoils of one such hunt.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sea_Dragons_Crown: Only those who prove themselves in hunt against the great Sea Dragon dare wear such a crown.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sea_Dragons_Fins: What appear as fins on Slardar are but the edge of the mighty Sea Dragon's tiniest gill-guards.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sea_Dragons_Set: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Sea Dragon' set for Slardar:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sea_Rakes_Bridle: Even before his time in Dark Reef, Slark discovered the weakest point of any cage was almost never the lock.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Seablight_Procession: Contains the Seablight Procession set for Undying, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Seaborne_Reprisal: Contains the Seaborne Reprisal set for Kunkka, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Seafarers_Shoes: A fine pair of leather shoes with rubber soles, for when the Captain must work his charms on land.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Seal_of_the_Shapers_Legac: No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. This treasure contains full item sets.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Searchlight_Helm_of_the_M: Created in partnership with June, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Searing_Dominator: The old tales tell of a scion of the Dead God, who led an army of the dead before being betrayed and destroyed by her own restless minions as they sought to return to their slumber. Atop the head of the scion's undead champion sat the Searing Dominator, a helm that ignited the blood of its wearer to fuel its terrible power.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Seasonal_Shimmer_Diretide: Contains the Diretide Shimmers for Enchantress, Bloodseeker, Centaur, Dazzle, Legion Commander, Luna, Magnus, Naga Siren, Skywrath Mage, and Drow.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Secret_Place__Season_1: Secret place - a new step in advancing amateur teams to the top. 32 teams will compete for the first prize of 8000 rubles.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Secrets_of_the_Katekhein: Contains the Secrets of the Katekhein set for Winter Wyvern, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Secrets_of_the_Merqueen: Contains the Secrets of the Merqueen set for Death Prophet, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sect_of_Kaktos: Contains the Sect of Kaktos set for Nyx Assassin, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Seed_of_Rebirth:
Should the lone Protector fall far from the nourishing eldritch soil of his homeland, the seedling that sprouts from his remains shall one distant day grow stout enough to carry forth the mission of its predecessor.

Contains the Eldritch Gnarl set for Treant Protector, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Seed_of_Rebirth_Arms: Should the lone Protector fall far from the nourishing eldritch soil of his homeland, the seedling that sprouts from his remains shall one distant day grow stout enough to carry forth the mission of its predecessor.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Seed_of_Rebirth_Head: Should the lone Protector fall far from the nourishing eldritch soil of his homeland, the seedling that sprouts from his remains shall one distant day grow stout enough to carry forth the mission of its predecessor.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Seed_of_Rebirth_Shoulder: Should the lone Protector fall far from the nourishing eldritch soil of his homeland, the seedling that sprouts from his remains shall one distant day grow stout enough to carry forth the mission of its predecessor.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Seekling: Even the Hound of the Flayed Twins entered his calling as a mere pup, tending to his predecessor's needs. Now a new pup has arrived seeking to take on the mantle, ready to aid warriors in their time of need.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Seers_Bounty: From clouded visions come just rewards.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Seismic_Berserker: Includes all of the items in the 'Seismic Berserker' set for Magnus plus a loading screen. Created in partnership with Ar1se, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Seismic_Berserker_Armor: Created in partnership with Ar1se, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Seismic_Berserker_Bracers: Created in partnership with Ar1se, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Seismic_Berserker_Club: Ambient particle effects can be unlocked on this item using the Treasure Upgrade Infuser - Winter 2016. Created in partnership with Ar1se, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Seismic_Berserker_Helm: Created in partnership with Ar1se, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Seismic_Berserker_Horn: Created in partnership with Ar1se, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Semipro_Cup_Series_Season: The Semipro Cup Series are cash prize tournaments with open registration for North and South American teams.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Semipro_Evening_Cup_Serie: SECS began in December 2009 and is the longest running Dota tournament series to date. There is open registration and cash prize every week!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sempiternal_Revelations_S: Includes all of the items in the \"Sempiternal Revelations'' set for Invoker including alternate head style.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sentinel_iCafe_Dota_2_Ser: Big Tournament in Indonesia organized by iCafe. All team will compete for the prizepool and to be a professional team in Indonesia. This Tournament supported by Dota Base Indonesia & Medan Gamers.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sentinel_of_the_Blackguar: In the early days following his escape from academia, long before he assumed the title of Invoker, the young magus sought to test his growing skill by any means attainable. Like many other young talents burning for a taste of adventure, it was not long before he answered the call to war.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sentinel_of_the_Lucent_Ga: Contains all of the items in the 'Sentinel of the Lucent Gate' set for Outworld Devourer plus loading screen. The weapon includes an ambient particle and each item includes an ability icon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sentinels_of_Ruin: After so long spent alone amidst the sprawling ruins--well removed from their days keeping watchful eye on an empire--these jungle sentinels are surprised to see anyone at all.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sentinels_of_the_Urushin_:
Though known for a violent and capricious temper, the burning bowman is much revered throughout The Hoven.

This item can be upgraded with the 'Urushin Huntsman Style Unlock' granted to players who complete all fifteen Three-Star objectives on the Path of the Rogue.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Serac_and_Floe___the_Seal: Contains Serac the Seal Courier and Floe the Seal Ward.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Serbian_Charity_Cup: Up to 32 teams from Serbia will compete in a tournament where all the money gathered will be going to charity!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Serbian_Dota_Premier_Leag: The top teams in the Balkan compete to become champion's of the Serbian Premier League and a prize!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Serbian_Weekly_Dota_2_Cup: A weekly Serbian tournament including all Balkan countries where top teams compete for a prize.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Serie_XLG_Dota_2__First_S: The Serie XLG Dota 2 is part of the company XLG (Xtreme League) an independent league of E-Sports. This league is a competition with the top teams in the Brazilian scene.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sermon_of_the_Frozen_Apos: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Sermon of the Frozen Apostle' set for Abaddon:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Serpent_of_the_Emerald_Se: Contains all of the items in the 'Serpent of the Emerald Sea' set for Medusa plus loading screen, cursors, ability icons and two tail styles.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Servant_of_the_Infernal_M: While some amongst the Ultimyr faculty share concerns regarding the peculiar nature of Chief Curator Lannik's studies, none can deny that under his watch the Academy's archives of arcane knowledge have grown incomparably.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_SevenSealed_the_Fur_Brace: This is merely a bracer of fur. It has no particular aspect of interest and offers no magical protections. Still, it bears a great name and in so doing illustrates the hollowness of baseless pride.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Severing_Lash: As his time away from the Narrow Maze lengthens, Razor finds the dark tinge of the Underscape seeping forth in the plasmatic charge of his whip.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shackles_of_the_Enduring_: Contains the Shackles of the Enduring Conscript set for Axe, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shade_of_Agony: They will crave her. They will reach for her. They cannot have her.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shade_of_the_Spiteful_Eye: Ambient particle effects can be unlocked on this item using the Tribute Upgrade Infuser - Fall Season 2015.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shadow_Brand: Such a blade will sear the stamp of chaos deep into the fabric of order.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shadow_Essence: A small marble of black crystal. Its perfectly polished surface consumes all light. A sense of terrible fear washes forth from its core.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shadow_Flame: Includes all of the items in the 'Shadow Flame' set for Dazzle and an additional style for the Headdress.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shadow_Hunter_Set:
Stalk your prey. Devour your foes.

These items were created in partnership with CaspeRRR, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shadow_Masquerade: While most family heirlooms were abandoned along with his former life, the last son of the Tahlin line still treasures the ancestral blades that adorned the sigil of his house.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shadow_Wars__Season_1: Our League site Dota International's 1st 1v1 Tournament where the only hero played will be Shadow Fiend and the winner will take home a Shadow Fiend Arcana and other cool item bundles
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shadow_in_the_Deep: Once impenetrable, the vaults of Dark Reef are ripe for plunder in the wake of Siltbreaker's upending of his sunken hell. For a former resident with a head for the layout and a talent for the knife, there's no telling what treasures might be raised.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shadow_in_the_Deep_Back: Once impenetrable, the vaults of Dark Reef are ripe for plunder in the wake of Siltbreaker's upending of his sunken hell. For a former resident with a head for the layout and a talent for the knife, there's no telling what treasures might be raised.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shadow_in_the_Deep_Helm: Once impenetrable, the vaults of Dark Reef are ripe for plunder in the wake of Siltbreaker's upending of his sunken hell. For a former resident with a head for the layout and a talent for the knife, there's no telling what treasures might be raised.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shadow_of_the_Dark_Age: Though long perished of form, some spiritual remnants of Balanar's lost brethren still haunt the edges of the void, drawn to the dark focus of their remaining One.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shadowforce_Gale: Contains the Shadowforce Gale set for Luna, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shadows_of_the_Wuxia: Contains the Shadows of the Wuxia set for Templar Assassin, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shadowshard: A bit of the dark world, broken off and ready to pierce the flesh and drain away the soul.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shadowshard__OffHand: A bit of the dark world, broken off and ready to pierce the flesh and drain away the soul.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shadowshards:
A bit of the dark world, broken off and ready to pierce the flesh and drain away the soul.
	
	Contains both of the Shadowshard Daggers for Riki:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shagbark: Shagbark is a trusty forest familiar who lives for the thrill of delivery. Fond of secrets and artifacts, he hopes you'll never finish farming.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shanghai_Dota2_Open: SDO planned by the Lanyou Culture of Shanghai , various teams compete with the prize pool of 520 thousand yuan.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shanghai_Dota2_Open_S2: SDO planned by the Lanyou Culture of Shanghai , various teams compete with the prize pool of 520 thousand yuan.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shanghai_Major: Witness teams from all around the world compete for a place at The Shanghai Major 2016.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shanghai_Major_Open_Quali: Witness teams from all around the world compete for a place at The Shanghai Major 2016.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shard_of_Blight: A dagger forged from the pain of lost souls.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shard_of_Retribution: \"Let not thine conviction blind thee, but embrace Retribution for the Redemption of thine Order.\" - Taken from Tael'Am
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shard_of_Vengeance: \"Let Vengeance be thine Radiance, so it may disperse the shadows that shroud the Wicked...\" - Taken from Tael'Am
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shard_of_the_Lost_Star_Lo: Created in partnership with Era, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shard_of_the_Rift: At the border between the realms lie stones that exist outside of time itself.  To be struck with such a stone is to feel an eternity of pain.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shards_of_Exile: The self-assembling crystals of the Outworld make a very good staff ... and an even better prison. Embodiments of the Void, the Shards offer a crash course in its essentials to Harbinger's opponents.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shards_of_Malice: Includes all of the items in the 'Shards of Malice' set for Wraith King plus a loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shards_of_Polymorphia_Set: Includes all of the items in the 'Shards of Polymorphia' set for Morphling:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shards_of_the_Falling_Com: Includes all of the items in the 'Shards of the Falling Comet' set for Morphling:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shards_of_the_Malignant_C: Far away beneath the Sunken Cities and through the Infernal Hollow, Buki'vak the Corrupted dwells in the depths forever expanding his corruption throughout the sea. Hearing of his power, Lion seeked to harvest his parts for a fresh demonoplasty. After a strenuous battle he defeated Buki'vak and gained the hand he desired as a reward, but it was not without cost. Just as his previous hand transformed him, so did this one. He became afflicted with the Malignant Corruption, causing unseemly shards of Obsidian to grow from his body and further disfigure him into something even more unrecognizeable from his original form.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sharpeyes_Momentoes: Sniper is an expert marksman.  Now he has the medals to prove it!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sharpstar_Armor: Contains the Sarpstar Armor set for Legion Commander, including the Loading Sceen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shatterblast_Core: Only Kaldr knows what fate awaits the universe in the time of the great equilibrium.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shatterblast_Crown: A warm headpiece is the last thing a cold being from the infinite void requires. This one is anything but. It is as uncomfortable as it looks, a chilly reminder of what the universe has in store.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shatterblast_Rule: The oldest depictions of Kaldr ever found by the archivists of Ultimyr are accompanied by unreadable script in a language long lost to the ages. And when the first deciphering spell drove its caster utterly mad, a ban was placed on attempting any more.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shattered_Destroyer: From the shards of numerous broken enemies, a weapon to be borne by one King alone.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shawl_of_Resonant_Vibranc: To harness such unpredictable power is a heavy burden. Or so say those who have not yet learned to turn back gravity!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shawl_of_the_Glacier_Dust:
A cozy garment to block the tundra's whipping winds.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shearing_Deposition: A frightening stillness falls, and the whispered prayers of salvation hang frozen in the air long after the lips of the sacrificed last passed breath.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shell_of_the_Hidden_Hive: Only those who preside in the Hidden Hive and share in the schemes of the goddess Nyx know the true significance of this ceremonial armor.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shell_of_the_Umizar_Crawl: For those with a taste for gambling and excess treasure to spend, the hidden grottos of Crey host all manner of speculative bloodsports.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shield_of_Burning_Turmoil: Cooled in the black nether between worlds, its core still bends and burns.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shield_of_Endless_Havoc: Let them loose their arrows and fling their axes.  The shield cares not.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shield_of_Stillness: This shield emanates calm and stillness, quieting Silencer's nearby foes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shield_of_the_Dark_Moon_S: The Dark Moon faithful consist of former scholars, laborers, orphans, and thieves. One may have served as magistrate of a city, another spilled blood as a warlord in the wilds. They have walked all imaginable paths to find Selemene. In her service, the trials and tragedies of the past matter not. They worship the Goddess together, guardians of the Nightsilver Woods.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shield_of_the_Drake: Although forged from silver and jeweled with crimsonstone, this enchanted Shield of the Drake is no ornamental bauble to hefted at tourneys.  It is the deepest kind of magic, and its bearer could find no better protection.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shield_of_the_Fractured_O: 'Hey your plumage looks nicer than mine. Wanna trade?'
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shield_of_the_Hazhadal_Ma: After besting the young mages of his order, Nortrom put his newfound skills to use suppressing the godless outlaws of the Hazhadall Barrens, routinely making short work of their vaunted enthrallers.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shield_of_the_Hidden_Tale: Whatever magic his enemies use, whatever spells his foes may cast in his direction, bounce soundlessly off this shield of silence.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shield_of_the_Reef_Kyte_R: Astride a fintail reef kyte and protected against the crush by an enchanted helm, the moon rider serves as Selemene's champion and emissary in forging undersea alliances and keeping creatures of the deep at bay.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shield_of_the_Silent_Guar: Sometimes a lack of magic is the greatest magic of all.  But for those times when it isn't, this shield might help.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shift_of_the_Silent_Guard: Cloaked in Silence, and also in this stylish shift.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shimmer_of_the_Anointed: Contains the Shimmer of the Anointed set for Nyx, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shivshell_Crawler: Contains the 'Shivshell Crawler' set for Slark, including the loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shock_of_the_Anvil: No mere battle hammer this. The Shock of the Anvil is the immovable object upon which a generation of weapons were born. Each battered and shaped upon the iron, and each imparting some vital essence, until at last the anvil crackled with piezoelectric power. When Magnus saw the hammer the blacksmith intended for him, he scoffed, choosing instead to make a weapon of the anvil itself.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shooting_Star: Contains the Shooting Star set for Sniper, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoreline_Sapper: Never coordinated well enough to swim with any stealth or grace, Ogre Magi relied on pilfered shipwright's tools and a bit of luck to survive a failed raid on Deshom Bay.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoreline_Sapper_Set_Styl: This International 2017 Battle Pass reward enables an upgraded style to be unlocked on the Shoreline Sapper set for Ogre through the style menu. You can use this item multiple times to unlock styles on all of the items in the set.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Short_Blade_of_Distant_Sa: Few assassins would dare use with such a finely wrought implement in combat, yet to the skilled this blade offers balance and sharpness more than equal to any task.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shotgun_Blade_of_the_Dark: 'You gonna do what the little guy says, or we collectin' with interest?'
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shotgun_Sling_of_the_Dark: 'You gonna do what the little guy says, or we collectin' with interest?'
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulder_Plate_of_the_Fer: As the young orphan outgrew adolescence and his mastery of the Turstarkuri scrolls improved, he became eager to test his blades and begin his longed-for crusade to rid the world of magic, ultimately finding first opportunity as a volunteer in the failed defense of Bakhwarren.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulder_of_the_Atniw: Ferocity takes shape.  Huge shoulders rise to shrug off attack.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulder_of_the_Golden_Ma: In each ferocious face is set determination without fear.  Such is required from those who would don the honors of the Golden Mane.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulder_of_the_Noble: Each nobleblood general of the Royal House of Ambry bore these pauldrons as a part of their formal wear.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulderguard_of_the_Free: Rogue swordmasters must balance the need for protection with the need for speed. This pauldron protects Sven's leading shoulder, but leaves his back arm unencumbered.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulderguards_of_the_Pen: The shoulderguards reflect the heavenly light above as a beacon of salvation visible from leagues away.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulderpads_of_the_Falco: Only a diving falcon can hope to avoid Windranger's arrows.  But this one didn't.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_Claszureme: For a traveler from Claszureme, one's place in the flow of time is uncertain.  These runes help ground the wearer within time's march.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_Petaluna: Though the priests of Dezun believe they alone possess the secrets of the ethereal shade, Dazzle's discovery of a race of insects in the lost jungles of Fellstrath capable of suckling energy directly from the Nothl Realm puts that claim to rest. But these creatures are inefficient with their feeding, and each puncture they create allows a bit of influence from the Nothl Realm to bleed into our own.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Ageless_: As the lone Protector's path takes him ever further from his home soil, the fresh growth of bark keeps record of the wonders he has seen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Burning_: The unsleeping huntsman patrols all reaches of The Hoven, one anguished step after another.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Comets_T: The stars themselves travel the skies in search of illumination.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Dark_Mag: In an age when fear surrounded sorcery, tales told of an oppressive wizard capable of limitless destruction.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Dark_Moo: The Dark Moon faithful consist of former scholars, laborers, orphans, and thieves. One may have served as magistrate of a city, another spilled blood as a warlord in the wilds. They have walked all imaginable paths to find Selemene. In her service, the trials and tragedies of the past matter not. They worship the Goddess together, guardians of the Nightsilver Woods.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Death_Ch:
It took the steel of two shields, melted down and recast, to cover the broad shoulders of Spirit Breaker.

These Player Items are created in partnership with your favorite player, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Forest_H: Deep in his thoughts, Earthshaker scarcely notices the occasional hop-on.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Fungal_L: Infused with the essence of the Father Mushroom.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Hidden_T: When a heavy silence falls, Nortrom will need mighty shoulders such as these to bear up under its weight.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_North: Keep the snow off your shoulders in these furry shoulders of winter.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Penitent: Only by candlelight does Dragonus dare investigate the means to restore his lost love.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Slain_Dr: Not the actual shoulders of a dragon, but a skilled artist's rendition of it.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Survivor: As even the faces of favored kin fade from recollection, the unholy forms of the Turstarkuri faithful rise perversely in the mind's eye.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shoulders_of_the_Twelfth_: In the custom of the Bear Clan, each warrior must carry his newborn in a satchel on his shoulder for eleven full days to prove his strength.  On the twelfth day, armor is bestowed.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_ShowMatch_Coliseo: The first season for the ShowMatch Coliseo league hosted by Isurus Gaming and Not Today.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shredder_of_the_Vandal: If you run out of arrows, you can always stab your enemies with this.  It has more points than Leshrac has horns.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shroom_Thing: Constructed from fungus and moss and infused with the essence of the Father Mushroom.. Shroom Thing is here to serve!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shroomling: Among all the shuffling fungi of Drowned Forest, Shroomlings are renowned for their fearless nature and love of all things dank and dark.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shroud_of_Ka: Includes custom abilty icon and custom particle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shroud_of_the_Archivist: Prevents cranial intrusions by a particularly pernicious form of bookwyrm that skulks in the Ultimyr Archives.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shroud_of_the_Awakened: \"May thine visage not be hindered by those of absent mind and eternal hunger, for thou shall bring an end to their suffering...\" - Taken from Tael'Am.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shroud_of_the_Shattered_S: To possess the power of a Demon Witch is to stand in defiance of powers seen and unseen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shrunken_Head_Staff: The head of Witch Doctor's mother hangs from this staff. Such a loving son.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shuriken_of_Distant_Sands: Those who worship the Solar Goddess of the eastern wastes are known for the skill forging gold.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shuriken_of_the_Blood_Sta: Flying edges bite, and the sand is christened anew.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shuriken_of_the_Crimson_C: Among the many weapons in the Crimson Cut-throat's home were a trio of small, curved knives which Gondar repurposed into a new shuriken.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shuriken_of_the_Hidden_Hu: This shuriken's blades are clean and sharp, a weapon fresh and ready.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Shuriken_of_the_Reaper: A shuriken made to be deadly regardless of how it makes contact.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Siarankucom_Tournament: DotA 2 Indonesia Tournament Project by Siaranku.com on main event 21 November - 28 November
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sibladder_Season_1: We are very pleased to announce the Dota 2 SIbladder.ru Season 1. Test your skills and celebrate your teams!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Siege_Engine: Contains the Siege Engine set for Timbersaw, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Siege_of_the_Arctic_Hall: Contains the Siege of the Arctic Hall set for Legion Commander, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sight_of_the_KhaRen_Faith: Contains the Sight of the Kha-Ren Faithful set for Drow.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sigil_Belt_of_the_Great_G: An protective iron belt hammered into the likeness of a wolf.  Long may the last of his house stalk the woods of Ambry.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sigil_of_the_Radiant_Crus: Those who don these fabrics must swear never to fall in battle, for it is considered a sin to defile such a garment with earth.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sigil_of_the_Stormcrow: A staff bearing the sigil of the stormcrow, crafted from its sacred bones.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sigil_of_the_Tahlin_Watch: Very few display the talent necessary to join the Tahlin Watch.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sign_of_the_Arachnid:
Required Level: 14

Passive: Arachnid Aura - Allies gain bonus movement and attack speed.

Bonus Agility: 15
Aura Bonus Move Speed: 15%
Aura Bonus Attack Speed: 20
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Silent_Champion: Contains all of the items in the 'Silent Champion' set for Silencer:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Silent_Guardian:
Even in his first memories, Nortrom's caretakers spoke ceaselessly of the glories that awaited their young ward, and the blessed favors each hoped to receive upon his fated day of ascension. It was those same handlers whose reverent administrations turned to spiteful neglect as the prospects of the child's rise dimmed in the shadows of his unmanifested abilities.

Contains the Silent Edict set for Silencer, including the Loading Screen.
