Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Silent_Wake: The midwinter drifts scatter in a silent gust from the passing ranger before settling gently back to earth, as if they were never disturbed at all.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Silent_Wake_of_the_Crimso: The midwinter drifts scatter in a silent gust from the passing ranger before settling gently back to earth, as if they were never disturbed at all.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Siltbreaker_Act_II_Emotic: Unlocks the Siltbreaker emoticon awarded for completing Act II of the Siltbreaker Campaign.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Siltbreaker_Reward: This treasure is only available during The International 2017 Battle Pass duration as a reward for the Siltbreaker Campaign event. It contains treasures, as well as the chance to receive an extremely rare Desert Baby Roshan.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Siltbreaker__Emoticon: Unlocks the Siltbreaker emoticon awarded for completing Act I of the Siltbreaker Campaign.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Siltbreakers_Dredged_Trid:
Hauled from the deep long ago, Siltbreaker made this destructive weapon his own.

+160 Damage

Required Level: 23

Passive: Critical Strike
Grants each attack a 35% chance to deal 350% additional damage.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Silver_2014_Compendium_Ge: Awarded for raising The International 2014 Compendium beyond level 25.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Silver_Dota_League: A South american league that help the teams to gain points in the rankings of Dota 2 Brazlian teams made by fans!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Silver_Dota_League_2: The Silver Dota League is an Amateur league featuring more than 100 South American teams competing for in-game items and a cash prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Silver_Spectator_Gem: Adding this gem to an item will enable that item to track games viewed for a league or team.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sina_Cup_Seaosn_5: The fifth season of the Sina Cup has Chinese teams competing for a prize pool of 100,000 Yuan!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sina_Cup_Supernova_Dota_2: The Sina Cup Supernova Dota 2 puts two top teams from the qualifiers against professional teams across Asia for a total prize pool of 30,000RMB.
Sina Cup Supernova Dota 2 Open is back for another season! In addition to the 8 invited teams, 4 teams will advance through qualifiers to compete for a total prize pool of 65,000RMB.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sina_Cup_Supernova_Season: Supernova tradition continues on with rising teams qualifying for chance to compete against top teams across China for prize pool of 90,000RMB.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Single_Battle_Point_Boost:
Use this item to increase the rate at which you earn Battle Points to 150% for a single match. Additionally, you will grant other players a stacking 5% bonus to their Battle Points rate.

Battle Point Boosters are only consumed whenever Battle Points are earned and features like spectating games or coaching do not deplete them.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Single_Item_Treasure: No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. This treasure contains individual items.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Singles_Day_Emoticon_Pack: Unlocks 9 emoticons earned via the Autumn Sale Treasure of the Venerable One
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sinister_Lightning: Includes all of the items in the 'Sinister Lightning' set for Invoker including alternate styles and a loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sinorian_Sphere_Staff: A Sinorian gemstone caps this staff, providing a magical focus for nature's incantations.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sithils_Stash: That disreputable scoundrel Sithil has lost a chest of plundered loot! You will need <font color='#9da1a9'>Sithil's Summer Key</font> to open the chest. You can pick one up at the DOTA 2 Store. Beware! At the end of <font color='#9da1a9'>July 31, 2012</font> this chest will crumble into useless dust. This chest contains one of several mysterious new items.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sixense_eSport_Online_Tou: More than 64 teams will compete in Sixense eSport Online Tournament Season 1 that held on February 5 - 7, 2016 to win over IDR 2.800.000 prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sizzling_Charge: Contains the Sizzling Charge set for Storm, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skadi_Rising: Contains all of the items in the Shard of the Lost Star item set for Morphling plus loading screen. Created in partnership with Era, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skarsnik_and_Gobbla: Contains the Skarsnik and Globbla set for Disruptor, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skeletal_Catch: There might still be a little meat on it.  But probably not.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skeletal_Claw_of_the_Vand: Lacking flesh, Clinkz adorns his skeletal hand with the claw of the Vandal.  Forged by smeevils in ages long past, this iron claw is for many hapless victims the iron grip of death itself.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skins_of_the_Incubus: Few facets of the utter foul wander the land unbidden. To claim such a skin is to declare primacy over the inferno.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skip_the_Delivery_Frog: What he lacks in size he makes up for in character.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skirt_of_Petaluna: Though the priests of Dezun believe they alone possess the secrets of the ethereal shade, Dazzle's discovery of a race of insects in the lost jungles of Fellstrath capable of suckling energy directly from the Nothl Realm puts that claim to rest. But these creatures are inefficient with their feeding, and each puncture they create allows a bit of influence from the Nothl Realm to bleed into our own.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skirt_of_the_Flameguard: Beyond reproach and unwavering in their devotion, the Flameguard stand as living avatars of Knightly Duty.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skirt_of_the_Guardian_Con:
Though depictions of his body and form differ in the telling, the crackle of the Lightning Revenant's whip is known to all of the blessed few who have returned to life from the Narrow Maze.

This item can be upgraded with the 'Compact of the Guardian Construct Style Unlock' granted to players who complete at least 40 stars on the Path of the Dominator.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skirt_of_the_Mage_Slayer: Time and practice would persuade the Anti-Mage against such a heavy garment, yet its use in combat has not diminished.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skirt_of_the_Mothbinder: Dim though it has become, the spark of life that holds fast within the heart of the Death Prophet blazes like a signal beacon in the endless darkness of death's abyss, beckoning all manner of feasting shades that long to taste the essence of the animate world.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skirt_of_the_Revenant: A new storm is blowing across the battlefield.  Where there is thunder, there is sure to be lighting.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skittering_Desolation: When Weaver slipped through time, he found something impossible just beyond the rift.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skull_Mask_o_Wicked_Badne: A mask crafted from the polished bones of a cruel Prefecturan noble. The Witch Doctor wears this mask when he wants influential spirits to take notice of his work.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skull_Staff_of_Grim_Rites: The life essence of a sacrificial totem beast imbues this ritual staff.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skull_of_the_First_Hunt:
A kit's first tools must come from the remains of its prey.

This item can be upgraded with the 'Kit of the First Hunt Style Unlock' granted to players who complete at least 40 stars on the Path of the Saboteur.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skull_of_the_Ravager: Only the fiercest hunter may lay claim to the skull of a spiked ravager.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skull_of_the_Razorwyrm:
Fierce opponent turned staunch protector.

This item can be upgraded with the 'Scale of the Razorwyrm Style Unlock' granted to players who complete all fifteen Three-Star objectives on the Path of the Warrior.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skullsplitter_Axe: Axe never had the heart to wipe the original owner's blood from the edge.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_SkyHigh_Warship: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Sky-High Warship' set for Gyrocopter plus loading screen. These items were created in partnership with Alliance, who receive a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skyfire_Apostate: Contains the Skyfire Apostate set for Keeper of the Light, including the loading screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skywarriors_Countenance: A holy relic passed down from the emperors of the ancient clouded city of Aesthera, this spellbound helm bestows the golden visage of the vulture goddess upon only the most elite warriors of the realm.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skywrath_Mages_ti8_back: Only by candlelight does Dragonus dare investigate the means to restore his lost love.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skywrath_Mages_ti8_belt: Only by candlelight does Dragonus dare investigate the means to restore his lost love.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skywrath_Mages_ti8_weapon: Only by candlelight does Dragonus dare investigate the means to restore his lost love.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Skywrath_Sentinel: Although she may never reach the lofty hights of the Ghastly Eyrie again, Shendelzare still has allies that will grant her assistance when she requires it.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slab_of_Erupting_Wrath: Ambient particle effects can be unlocked on this item using the Tribute Upgrade Infuser - Fall Season 2015.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slardar_Set_Back: During his long-ago tenure as a Dark Reef Enforcer, Slardar sharpened his spines breaking up escape attempts and quelling constant insurrections.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slasher_of_the_Umizar_Cra: For those with a taste for gambling and excess treasure to spend, the hidden grottos of Crey host all manner of speculative bloodsports.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slashing_Quickslicer: If cross words lead to crossed swords, then it's best to be polite to the Naga Siren.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slashing_Quickslicer_Pack: This bundle contains both the main and off-hand Slashing Quickslicer.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slashing_Quickslicer__Off: If cross words lead to crossed swords, then it's best to be polite to the Naga Siren.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_SlayerSword_of_Sir_Davion: When facing a dragon the edge of one's blade means less than the sharpness of one's mind.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slayers_Glare: Why light a fire if you can't watch it burn?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sleeves_of_Lucid_Torment:
The dreamer's eyes are opened to a world of anguish.

This item can be upgraded with the 'Lucid Torment Style Unlock' granted to players who complete at least 40 stars on the Path of the Protector.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sleeves_of_the_Blackguard: In the early days following his escape from academia, long before he assumed the title of Invoker, the young magus sought to test his growing skill by any means attainable. Like many other young talents burning for a taste of adventure, it was not long before he answered the call to war.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sleeves_of_the_Charred_Bl: The rubies sewn into the sleeves are prized among the Misrule nobility.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sleeves_of_the_Ephemeral_: A billowing sleeve for Spectre, charged with the excess energy that overflows from Spectre's present form.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sleeves_of_the_Jiang_Shis: Should the mob ever come for him a second time, Ethreain will be ready.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sleeves_of_the_Royal_Butc: Though the carnage may go on without end, there are those alive still who can recall when it began. Ah, to be young and in the employ of the bloody King Brandalon once more.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sleeves_of_the_Scorching_: The sleeves flare out like the fiery soul who wears them.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sleeves_of_the_Solar_Divi: During her training in the flame arts, Lina chose to travel east to study with the followers of the Solar Goddess.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slicer_of_the_Depths: A shiv assembled from contraband gems. Better not ask how Slark kept it concealed in Dark Reef Prison.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slim_Blade_of_the_Tahlin_: When death is the price, one can never swing too many blades.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slime_Vial:
Auctioned from the estate of a brilliant but failed alchemist, these mystical vials have the power to transform liquid water into nearly any substance. However, a steady hand is required. The next item on the auction block was the slimy corpse of the sneezing thaumaturge himself. Vial art, indeed.

Stand in the river to reveal the vial interface. Pour the contents into the river to transform it for 3 minutes. Each vial can be used once per game.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slippers_of_the_Abyss:
In the voluminous depths, those who cannot move swiftly will be the first to die.

+15 Strength
+15 Agility

Required Level: 19

Active: Aqueous Rush
Increase movement speed by 200 for 4 seconds.

BONUS MOVEMENT SPEED: 90
BONUS ATTACK SPEED: 100
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Slumbering_Terror: In the presence of Bane Elemental, to wake from the nightmare brings only the start of one's troubles. The dark tidings of evil travel not alone.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Small_Majesty_Of_The_Colo: In ages past, long before the settlements in the Azuran region were abandoned to ruin, the Odobenus forebearers harnessed the powers of rock, root, and iron to create fearsome guardians to watch over the tombs of their fallen legions even after the memories of their deeds had passed from the world. Little did they know the raw stone materials they'd utilized in one such creation also contained a powerful life force of its own, one not content to sit idly waiting for the threats of the outlands to arrive--one who would venture forth to stand watch over all lands in need of protection.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Smeevil: Tis said among artisan and warrior alike that there is no finer servant than a trusty smeevil.  However, a hero who chooses a smeevil as their courier may soon find these clever critters taking new forms in order to gain assistants of their own. Inspired by the great battles they bear witness to, a smeevil may become emboldened to press ever more exotic beasts to their cause.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Smeevil_Treat: A tasty snack used to unlock new Smeevil styles.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Smeevils_Penance:
Most smeevils find contentment in the endless tasks of a servant's duty, rarely creatures of idle thought. Banished to his post from a role in the lanes, Ar'zurm the Smeevil sees things differently.

This ward for The International 2016 can be upgraded with 4 different Smeevil's Penance Upgrade Style items. Upgrades unlock different colors.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Smeevils_Penance_Upgrade_: This International 2016 reward enables an upgraded color style to be unlocked for the Smeevil's Penance ward in the style menu.
This International 2016 reward enables an upgraded color style to be unlocked for the Smeevil's Penance ward in the style menu.
This International 2016 reward enables an upgraded color style to be unlocked for the Smeevil's Penance ward in the style menu.
This International 2016 reward enables an upgraded color style to be unlocked for the Smeevil's Penance ward in the style menu.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Smoke_Bomb_of_Wild_Repris: Includes particles and an ability icon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Smoldering_Journey: Includes all of the items in the 'Smoldering Journey' set for Lina plus a loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snaggletooth: From the forests beneath the Wailing Mountains, a new friend and companion appears, small in stature but enormous in spirit.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snelfret_the_Snail: The original rebel snail, Snelfret refused to conform to a social order that enforced lethargy, a world that told him he must not move too fast. So he loaded up his shell and headed for more dynamic climes, determined to redefine the meaning of snail's pace.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_SngLadder_Season_One: Hundreds of players fight for the top spot and valuable prizes in the SngLadder Season One League.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snowdrop_Hood: Able to withstand the toughest onslaughts with nary a hair out of place, the Maiden of the North gives truth to the old adage that looks can kill.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snowdrop_Mantle: For those times when giving someone the cold shoulder is only the beginning.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snowdrop_Mittens: Crystal Maiden hardly needs to keep her hands warm in freezing weather. We suspect these are strictly a fashion statement.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snowdrop_Staff: Not one for outward displays of force, Crystal Maiden understands the necessity of putting on a show. This brilliant staff is but a symbol of her inner power, and for all its luster, barely hints at the depths of her mastery.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snowdrop_Tassels: No Wolf of Icewrack tail was harmed in the making of these tassels. They are formed entirely of soft, fluffy ice.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snowl: The Goddess of the Moon presses many forest creatures into her service.  Always crafty, ever vigilant, little Snowl would give his all to aid the guardians of the Nightsilver.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snowman_Noses: He'll stay friends as long as he can.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Snowstorm_Huntress: Contains all of the items in the 'Snowstorm Huntress' item set for Mirana plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Soaring_Cache: This treasure is only available to Fall 2015 Compendium owners.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Solar_Forge: An ancient relic pulled from the massive, dune-swept crater at the edge of the Scintillant Waste.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Solar_Gyre: Long separated from the matching headpiece, these relics were unearthed by a playful dragon toad in some corner of one desert or another--the dragon toad in question isn't so good with names--only regaining their shine when his friend traded them away to their surprisingly-shrewd rightful owner.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Solo_Mid_Battle_by_Terrik: Players from CIS will fight for the RAR.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Somos_Doteros_Tournament: An amateur tournament on sudamerica. Its focused on new teams who never participated in a tournament.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Somos_Gamer_Cup: Amateur tournament to test all the skill and strategy of Peru teams.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sorcerer_of_the_Black_Poo: Includes all of the items in the 'Dead Winter' set for Lich plus a loading screen:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Soul_Diffuser: By this blade shall you know her, bringer of death, bearer of your final moments of mortal terror.  She who renders your soul diffuse, your body lifeless dark, mere meat and viscera.  In a flash of movement, she slices your soul's tether, and frees you to learn the truth of the last great mystery.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Soul_Shredder: While he'll shred with proper style when a soul hangs in the balance, on his own time Doom generally prefers to dabble in areas more torturously avant-garde.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Soul_Shredder_Bundle: While he'll shred with proper style when a soul hangs in the balance, on his own time Doom generally prefers to dabble in areas more torturously avant-garde.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Soul_of_the_Brightshroud: Contains the Soul of the Brightshroud set for Death Prophet, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Souls_Tyrant: Contains the Souls Tyrant set for Shadow Fiend
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_South_American_Amateur_Do: Where all amateurs South American Teams fight for Glory and a prize in cash!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_South_American_Elite_Leag: The most talented players in South America compete for $1,000 in the classic in-house league format for six weeks.
The most talented players in South America compete in the classic inhouse league format.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_South_American_Fire_Cup: The best cup with the best South American amateur teams compete for a $320 prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_South_Sumatera_DOTA_2_Ama: The second annual DOTA 2 competition for all amateur team in South Sumatera region sponsored by Command Centre Game Station and Intikom.

Main event of the third annual DOTA 2 competition for all amateur DOTA 2 teams in South Sumatera region, organized by Emporium and Command Centre also  sponsored by ASUS ROG and Zowie a Brand by Benq.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_South_Sumatera_Dota_2_Ama: South Sumatera Dota 2 Amateur League is a Dota 2 competition between 15 most talented amateur teams in the region.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_South_Ural_League_Season_: Teams compete in an online competition to earn a spot in the top 16 teams which compete in a LAN finals.

The third season of the South Ural League is upon us! The league consists of 16 teams in the pro division and 80 teams in the amateur division. The LAN finals will take place in Chelyabinsk.  Bundle includes the ticket and Green Ural HUD skin!

The third season of the South Ural League is upon us! The league consists of 16 teams in the pro division and 80 teams in the amateur division. The LAN finals will take place in Chelyabinsk.  This ticket only gives you access to view games from the South Ural League Season 3.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Southamerican_Championshi: 24 South American teams: 16 qualified and 8 invited, compete for a  prize pool of $1,500.  Organized by TTesports, MyRevenge and DreamliveTV in partnership with AzubuTV.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Souvinir_of_the_Bone_Ru: Even skulls get lonely up in the ruins.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sovereign_of_the_Hive: Includes all of the items in the 'Sovereign of the Hive' set for Nyx Assassin plus a loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sovereign_of_the_Kray_Leg: Contains the Sovereign of the Kray Legions set for Sand King, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spade_of_the_Gluttonous: Though crafted in symbolic likeness to the great wheel books of the ruined city, the Spade of the Gluttonous whistles no song but the song of death.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Span_of_Black_Nihility: Beneath the wings of Black Nihility lies terrible darkness. Those in their shadow must supplicate and despair.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Span_of_Sorrow: Like a shadow that chills the noonday sun, the span of the demon marauder is sure to darken any day.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spanish_Dota_2_Pro_Series: The Spanish Dota 2 Pro Series is the first  professional league for Dota 2 in Spain created with the 8 best teams from Spain!
The finals of the Dota 2 Pro Series are the biggest event of Dota 2 in Spain. The live event will take place in Madrid from June 27th-29th.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spark_of_the_Lightning_Lo: These items were created in partnership with Team Empire, who receive a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sparrowhawk_Bow: Strong, but light as a feather, this bow of the sparrowhawk will fly your arrows true to their targets.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sparrowhawk_Cape: In addition to being stylish, this cape of the sparrowhawk manages the trick of also being camouflaging, provided that you're standing next to a flock of sparrowhawks.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sparrowhawk_Hood: It takes a spectacular hood to tame your fiery red hair.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sparrowhawk_Quiver: Proving that every part of the sparrowhawk can be turned into a stylish item for Lyralei to wear, this quiver speaks to the utility of sparrowhawks as a species.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sparrowhawk_Wings: Tired of your shoulders being devoid of sparrowhawk feathers?  Then this item is for you.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spaulder_of_Burning_Turmo: Within the astral turmoil, heat bends and matter swirls.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spaulder_of_the_Steppe: Many a centaur was gored with this spiny spaulder.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spaulder_of_the_Wandering: Seeking to restore the mantras of the Guardian Flame far beyond the embers of his ignition pyre in the Wailing Mountains, Xin loosed his remnants into the fury of a passing storm, casting them out in search of all who might still carry his spark.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spaulders_of_The_Howling_: Bone-carved shoulder spaulders display the ceremonial markings of the Frosted Winds tribe.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spaulders_of_the_Exact_Ma: Created in partnership with YYF, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spaulders_of_the_Fracture: 'Hey your plumage looks nicer than mine. Wanna trade?'
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spaulders_of_the_Lost_Vig: Were there any Vigil Knights still alive to tell the tale, they might share a favorite yarn of the \"Lost\" Vigil patrol, a mystery with endless variations. Though most believed the missing knights lost at sea, some insisted there had been sightings recorded by the elders of Ashkavor--that the knights had been seen in the mountains that guard the unforgiving jungle lands of Fellstrath--a region already feared long before the destruction of Ashkavor made any journey into those lands impossible.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spaulders_of_the_Wyrmforg: The demasted figurehead of the Wyrmforge is just one of many lost relics gathered by the One for safe keeping and occasional good use.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spear_of_Teardrop_Ice: The two teardrop gems pressed into the haft ensure the spear's icy edge never thaws.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spear_of_the_First_Hunt:
A kit's first tools must come from the remains of its prey.

This item can be upgraded with the 'Kit of the First Hunt Style Unlock' granted to players who complete at least 40 stars on the Path of the Saboteur.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spear_of_the_Golden_Mane: To wield such a prized spear, one must have courage and ferocity befitting the honors of the Golden Mane.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spear_of_the_Herald: An ancient weapon from an unknown craftsman, it was said to have been forged for he whom destiny calls worthy. Each swing heralds another step toward a new age.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spear_of_the_Wildwings_Bl: It is unfortunate that a few rogue Wildkin must spoil the proud race's reputation, but when it is time to hunt those few rascals down, Enchantress bears a spear granted her by the wisest of the Wildwing race.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spectator_Gem: Adding this gem to an item will enable that item to track games viewed for a league or team.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spectral_Conservator: In her myriad manifestations, Spectre finds herself adapting to the exigencies of war. Slowly, she has converged on a more suitable form.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spectral_Light: When moving between certain dark angles of creation, it is important that one not be mistaken for prey. The sigils on this headpiece serve as a warning to some interdimensional predator, but an invitation to others less visible.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spectrolite_Staff: A staff bearing an array of spectrolite mana focusing crystals set in gold.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Speed_Boot_Shell_Style_Up: This International 2017 reward enables an upgraded shell to be unlocked for Hermes the Hermit Crab in the style menu.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Speed_Demon: This imp has trained all his life for this moment. He is SO ready to go. He will deliver your loot on time or suffer eternal damnation in the sixty-four planes of the Lesser Hells.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spell_Surveyor: The Spell Surveyor is always on the lookout for spells that might be stolen!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spellbinders_Catalytic_Ma: When Rubick dons his catalytic mantle, things really start happening.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spellbinders_Forgotten_Gr: Rubick completely forgot about this greatstaff until just this moment!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spellbinders_Mask_of_Shap: Feeling ferocious, or simply for a lark, Rubick likes to take this old thing out and show it off from time to time.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spellbinders_Tattered_Clo: It is difficult in battle for even a great mage to entirely avoid treading on his cloak. Eventually it begins to show wear.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spellbreaker_of_Yoskreth: The sovereign of Yoskreth insisted that their champion be given the finest guard they could forge.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spetum_of_the_Disciplined: While a sharp point may make a weapon dangerous, it takes a disciplined arm to make it deadly.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spider_of_Purple_Nightmar: Includes all of the items in the 'Spider of Purple Nightmare' set for Witch Doctor:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spidering_of_the_Gluttons: Though the endless march of adventuring fools certainly disturbed the safety of her spiderlings, the constant supply of fresh treasure hunters did wonders for Arachnia's figure.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spiked_Bracers_of_the_Rav: To kill a ravager is a sacred rite for the ursa, and every piece of the carcass must be put to use.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spiked_Guard_of_the_Ancie: All who dared stand against the Bramble Lord well knew how easily his powers could catch and pierce their lives.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spiked_Pauldrons_of_the_C: Made from the leather of a full grown thunderhide, this armor is a match for any blade.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spikes_of_the_Umizar_Craw: For those with a taste for gambling and excess treasure to spend, the hidden grottos of Crey host all manner of speculative bloodsports.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spinal_Slicer: The prized spine of a red drake provides this heavy blade with an excellent counter-balance.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spinal_Slicer__OffHand: The prized spine of a red drake provides this heavy blade with an excellent counter-balance.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spinal_Slicers__Pair: Pack includes both the main and off-hand Spinal Slicer.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spine_Sword: Most see being stabbed in the back as a hindrance, but for a few, it's an inspiration.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spine_of_Omexe: Forged from the melted shields of a dozen fallen gladiators, this armor has the centaur's back.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spines_of_the_Dreadful_Ab: From strange waters come stranger properties.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spines_of_the_Lost_Star: Created in partnership with Era, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spiral_Staff: A crystalline focus hung at the center of the staff gives the Witch Doctor unnatural sight.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spiral_Staff_of_the_First: A twisted staff that holds a captive memory of the initial blaze of creation.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spirethorn: Ambient particle effects can be unlocked on this item using the Tribute Upgrade Infuser - Fall Season 2015.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spirethorn_Regalia: Contains the Spirethorn Regalia set for Leshrac, including the loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spirit_Breaker_TI10_Caver: This is not the first battle of import on this plane to necessitate the intervention of Barathrum at his master's behest.
This is not the first battle of import on this plane to necessitate the intervention of Barathrum at his master's behest.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spirit_Crusher: Your enemy's spirits will be crushed by the sight of this dread weapon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spirit_of_Calm: Though doom and ruin they saw, the visions of the haruspex brought to Sylla a sense of destined calm. During mediations, he found his spiritual projections altered to appear less intimidating.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spirit_of_the_Atniw: A projection of inner strength, and the bond of the bear clan.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spirit_of_the_Emeraldine_: Contains the Spirit of the Emeraldine Rider set for Luna, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spirit_of_the_Howling_Wol: Includes all of the items in 'Spirit of The Howling Wolf' set for Sniper:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spirits_of_the_Mothbinder: Dim though it has become, the spark of life that holds fast within the heart of the Death Prophet blazes like a signal beacon in the endless darkness of death's abyss, beckoning all manner of feasting shades that long to taste the essence of the animate world.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Splattering_Forcipule: The darkest wilds of Jidi Isle are home to wondrous horrors. A distant relative to the Spitterpede family, the Splattering Forcipule can often be found growing in damp crevices or between the roots of trees. They will spend their entire lives bound to a single location, and the toxic venom they eject upon any creature foolish enough wander nearby is often more than sufficient to poison the hapless victim, as well as begin its digestion. Once this poor soul expires, their melting remains are quickly absorbed into the earth where they fall, allowing the Forcipule's subterranean root-tendrils to absorb the nutrients.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Splendor_of_the_Protean_E: Contains the Splendor of the 'Splendor of the Protean Emperor' set for Morphling, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Splintering_Awe: Contains the Splintering Awe set for Treant, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spoils_from_the_Shifting_:
Shatter their sorcery.

These items were created in partnership with BurNing, who receives a portion of every purchase.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spoils_of_the_Bone_Ruins_: Contains all of the items in the 'Spoils of the Bone Ruins' for Meepo:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spoils_of_the_Vodou_Rover: Contains the Spoils of the Vodou Rover set for Witch Doctor, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spottin_Goggles: Able to see a tic on a mouse's back at a thousand paces, Sniper's Spottin' Goggles are a marvel to behold.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Spring_Cup: A battle for the title of Spring Cup Champions.

SLCG has become the largest e-Sports tournament in the country, and this year it aims to take the culture of games to the next level. Watch top Dota 2 teams compete in the largest event in Sri Lanka!

SLCG, the biggest e-Sports event in the country is back for its 9th edition, as it expands to Jaffna, Galle, Kandy and the main event in Colombo. Casual gamers, cyber athletes, comic book fans and cosplayers unite as the annual games festival takes the country by storm. Dota 2 takes centre stage yet again this year as the best teams in Sri Lanka battle it out for prestige and honor!

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Staff_of_Petaluna: Though the priests of Dezun believe they alone possess the secrets of the ethereal shade, Dazzle's discovery of a race of insects in the lost jungles of Fellstrath capable of suckling energy directly from the Nothl Realm puts that claim to rest. Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Staff_of_the_Frozen_Feath: A day before the wizard descended into the glacier to begin his hibernation, he offered Crystal Maiden these last, precious gifts: armor and a staff, strong as ice but light as a feather, believed to have once belonged to a winter deity.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sufferwood_Sapling: Nature is not a unified cause or philosophy. Feared by all that is green, the tainted Sufferwood hosts a consciousness bent on dominating everything that grows, sending forth blooming horrors to corrupt the wilds to its purpose.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sullen_Harvest: The hooded figure that waits beyond the veil pays close mind to the path of the Necrophos. For where Rotund'jere's footsteps fall, the reaper's work will surely follow.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sullen_Hollow: Idly drumming phantom phalanges, Sullen Hollow barely restrains its impatience to lash out and administer tainted browbeatings to the foes of Necrophos.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sullen_Rampart: In a lost corner of the underworld, endless damned souls scrape and claw to reach the top of their unfathomable mass, none comprehending that no such summit exists, and only by the whims of their tormentor himself might a chosen few briefly see the light of day again.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Summers_Bounty: Who would want to run away from such a beautiful spear?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Summers_Charm: Bedizened with oaken branches, Enchantress easily blends into the rich summer shade.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Summers_Light: Wearing these luminous pauldrons, Enchantress honors the glory of the summer sky.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Summers_Mirth: Mirth and merriment bedeck the lovely Enchantress. Ivy is cool in summer and who cares about winter anyway?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Summers_Warmth: Every warm summer day must eventually give way to the cool breezes of evening. This light covering is more than enough to ward off goosebumps.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Summertime_Madness_Champi: Watch 24 South African teams battle it out in the first annual Summertime Madness Dota 2 Championship
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Summon_Penguin: Summons a friendly penguin who slides around.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sunbreeze_Birthright: While Mireska happily left nearly every trapping of her old life behind when she fled Revtel, she knew the only thing that might displease her father more than losing the family birthright in the fire would be to imagine it in the hands of his delinquent daughter.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sunday_Evening_Amateur_Le: The Sunday Evening Amateur League is based in the Pacific Timezone of North America.  Players of all skill levels are formed into teams that compete for roughly three months.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sunday_Evening_Cup_Series: The Sunday Evening Cup Series (SECS) began in December 2009 and is the longest running Dota tournament series to date. SECS provides an open competitive platform for North and South American teams to gain real tournament experience.

The Sunday Evening Cup Series (SECS) began in December 2009 and is the longest running Dota tournament series to date. SECS provides an open competitive platform for North and South American teams to gain real tournament experience.
SECS is back for Season 2! SECS has been around since 2009 and provides an open competitive platform for North and South American teams to gain real tournament experience.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sunken_Emblem:
Equippable by all heroes, the Sunken Emblem imbues its chosen bearers with an exclusive emblem featuring the Aegis of Champions and custom ambient effect.

This exceedingly rare prize was awarded for landing the winning shot in Slark's Riptide Rumble during The International 2017 Battle Pass season.

Only one Sunken Emblem can be active on a team, so in matches with multiple players with Sunken Emblems, the active Sunken Emblems are determined by players' Battle Pass levels. Expires prior to The International 2018.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sunken_Gaoler_Set_Style_U: This International 2017 Battle Pass reward enables an upgraded style to be unlocked on the Sunken Gaoler set for Slardar through the style menu. You can use this item multiple times to unlock styles on all of the items in the set.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sunrise_Challenge: The biggest Far East e-sports festival. Check out the latest news on sunrisecup.ru
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sunt_CDEC_New_Star_Cup: New Star is the continuation of traditional selection mode, the new team through the online registration will challenge pro teams which include DK, iG, LGD, VG and fight for 100000RMB price pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Super_Battle_of_the_Citie: 32 teams across Russian cities compete for a prize of $2000!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Support_TI10_Cavern_Crawl: This item can be used to unlock an alternate style for the Echoes of Ultoria Divine Path item set for Spirit Breaker.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Supreme_Black_Orc_Warboss: Contains the Supreme Black Orc Warboss set for Axe, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Surgical_Precision: Bored with careless slaughter, the butcher takes aim at a new occupation, though he brings the same talent for slaughter.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sven_TI7_Immortal_Sword: Amongst the debris of a sunken galley that once sailed beneath the Vigil banner, the Rogue Knight lay hands on a prized relic worthy of setting the Outcast Blade aside.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Swag_Cup_Season_1: 32 teams from the CIS will battle for a prize of 100$
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Swamp_Fins: Nobody is certain whether this display means the Tidehunter is angry or in heat.  Either way, none have survived to ask.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sweaty_Cup: Semi-pro teams and amateurs compete in this tournament for 16,000 Rubles!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sweaty_Cup_2: 32 semi-pro and professional teams participate in the 2nd season of the Sweaty Tournament with a $1,200 prize pool. This bundle gives access to view games from the Sweaty Cup 2 Tournament and the Deep Observer ward.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sweaty_Cup_2_Ticket: 32 semi-pro and professional teams participate in the 2nd season of the Sweaty Tournament with a $1,200 prize pool. This ticket only gives access to view games from the Sweaty Cup 2 Tournament.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sweep_of_Black_Nihility: The presence of primordial night lingers even as darkness passes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sweep_of_Forsaken_Beauty: Silken cloths sweep the ground where Medusa wanders.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Swift_Claw: You may flee from his rage. You may leave his echoing roar far behind. And you may think yourself safe, perhaps in a clearing or canyon, with no sign of your pursuer. Then, suddenly, his claws find you, and it is the last you know.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Swift_Pathfinder: Contains the Roving Pathfinder set for Windranger, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Swine_Arsenal: Techies Demolitions built hundreds of custom-built explosives to use with The Swine, but Spleen thought they were so adorable he couldn't bear to part with them as they were loading the cannon onboard the galley.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Swine_Helmet: When constructing The Swine, Techies Demolitions also forged some stylish headgear for its crew.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Swine_Powder_Barrel: Safely firing The Swine requires a custom mix of flammable powders, which Squee completely forgot to mention to the crew of the doomed galley who purchased the cannon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Swine_Visor: For some reason, the galley captain who commissioned The Swine didn't want the headgear that came with it. His loss.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Swooping_Elder: Contains the Swooping Elder set for Gyrocopter, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sword_of_Impending_Transg: A sword ever being forged, red hot, glowing with the heat of all the seven hells.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sword_of_the_Admirable_Ad: An exceptional specimen, surely the Captain's first pick of the loot. The hilt is dressed in worked gold and exotic stones. The blade blessed with a strangely glowing enchantment.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sword_of_the_Drake: One of only a dozen swords in existence known to have slain more than one dragon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sword_of_the_Flameguard: A heavily weighted sword fashioned in the two-handed style of the Flameguard sect of the Vigil Knights.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sword_of_the_Freelancer: \"Bitter the orphans journey--and lonely the orphan's grave.\"
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sword_of_the_Mono_Militis: The Mono Militis are one of several sects among the Vigil Knights. Adherents have tasked themselves with hunting down those who have strayed from the teachings of the Vigil Codex.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sword_of_the_One_True_Kin: In an age lost even to his own memory, Ostarion fed his lust for eternal life not with spectral essence, but a nigh-unending harvest of bone. The walls of his palace were formed of fired bone; the streets paved with bones of every sort of creature and every enemy. And those of the flesh who entered this domain took great care, for the King was first and foremost a collector, and nothing moved in the Empire of Bone without summoning the gaze of his unblinking eyes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sword_of_the_Seventy_Seve: Here we have a weapon truly worthy of a man such as Kunkka. Exotic and well-balanced, this cutlass cuts an image as smartly as it cuts a man.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sword_of_the_Smoldering_S: In life, the warrior-poet's later-day accomplishments were even more impressive than those of his youth, as the wisdom of his years finally grew to match the purity of his martial arts.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sword_of_the_Warriors_Ret: A weapon that once belonged to Sven's father, it was years before the son discovered its transformative properties.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylnashar_the_Winged_Axe: Lost for centuries, the winged axe known as Sylnashar was once the favored weapon of an ancient king.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Cascade: A cape woven from the finest wind-strewn filaments of enchanted ephemera, this is a garment of both rare beauty and unexpected utility.  For she who wears the cape of the Sylvan Cascade, the wind will be always at her back.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Guards_Boots: The guardians of the forest paths walk in perfect silence, betrayed not by their cunning footwear.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Guards_Bow: Drow has nothing to learn from the Sylvan Guard, but from time to time she relieves one of them of their bow, that she might test its quality. Even by her standards, this one is adjudged very fine.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Guards_Cape: Stealth is of utmost importance to those who number themselves among the Sylvan Guard. Even Drow finds this an acceptable cape for moving unseen through the wooded ways.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Guards_Cuffs: In her youth, Drow was tempted once or twice to throw over her lonely ways and join the Sylvan Guard. These cuffs were a large part of the attraction.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Guards_Dress_Armor: It must be admitted: Drow admires the Sylvan Guard. When from time to time she puts on their gear, and pretends to adopt their ways, she can hardly suppress her joy in having an excuse to don this stylish armor.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Guards_Finery_Set: All the finery of the Sylvan Guard, complete!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Guards_Hair: While not a member of the Sylvan Guard, Drow spies upon them in their marches, and occasionally admires their passing fashions.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Guards_Quiver: The archers of the Sylvan Guard shoot only arrows crafted specifically for their use. When Drow uses their gear, such arrows are de rigeur.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Sylvan_Vedette: Though the battle prowess of a tested ranger is never in doubt, it is the reconnaissance upon which one's tactics are based that allows for survival into yet another day.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Symbol_of_the_King_Restor: \"Do you mind if I slip into something from my 'Classics' period?\"
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Synergy_League_Season_1: The top teams from Europe, South-East Asia, and China compete for the $50,000+ prize pool. Purchase the ticket and increase the prize pool. This bundle includes the Warhawk Vestiments Lina set andy grants access to view games from the Synergy League Season 1.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tactic_Hive_League_Season: Tactic Hive League is designed for semi-professionals and amateur Dota 2 gamers. Tactic Hive is a ladder where players can have fun, compete and win prizes. Teams compete for the $2,000 prize pool.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tahlin_Occult_Dagger: There are none so stabbed as those who will not see.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tahlin_Occult_Dagger__Off: A blade lifted from the corpse of Riki's father on the night that House Tahlin fell, this blade has been sheathed in many foes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tahlin_Occult_Daggers:
There are none so stabbed as those who will not see.
	
	Contains both of the Tahlin Occult Daggers for Riki:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tahlin_Occult_Hood: A trickster's hood to hide your eyes.  But it will take a trickster's heart to hide your sins.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tahlin_Occult_Set: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Tahlin Occult' set for Riki:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tahlin_Occult_Shoulder_Si: Enscribed with the symbol of the house of Tahlin, this shoulder mark is a symbol to all with the eyes to see it.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tail_Fins_of_the_Slithere: Naga dons these noble fins, and recalls the glory days in which they slithered up the grand stairs of the sunken palace.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tail_Plates_of_Apocalypti: A stygian tail of finest demon armor, forged in the fifth of the seven hells.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tail_Sleek: With a playful flick of his mighty tail, a centaur registers approval.  With his flail, disapproval.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tail_of_Fury: Poets will tell the tale of the great fury of Barathrum.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tail_of_Impending_Transgr: This tail will swish till damnation come.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tail_of_Sundering: A transformation of a standard tail, into a weapon which pulses desolation.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tail_of_Twisted_Wisdom: Rumors have it that Leshrac once lost his tail, and after much searching and despair, an artificial appendage was attached. Perhaps this was the source of his bleak brand of wisdom.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tail_of_Ultoria: This is not the first battle of import on this plane to necessitate the intervention of Barathrum at his master's behest.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tail_of_Unfettered_Malevo: Cursed chains forged by the Order of Ra'hul to bind the Night Stalker and bring his ancient power to heel. And bind Balanar they did, until darkness fell.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tail_of_the_Death_Charge:
One tail is much like another, unless it's this tail. A bifurcated appendage like no other.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tail_of_the_Ethereal_Mona: The royal regalia of Undertree? A juvenile dragon's nameday finery? Only Puck knows, and it's not telling.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tail_of_the_Fatal_Bloom: Unseen by Lesale in his urgent compounding, the orchid of his salvation was also host to the pulsing cocoon of a Fradjan moth.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tail_of_the_Ferocious_Tox: Ambient particle effects can be unlocked on this item using the Treasure Upgrade Infuser - Winter 2016.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tail_of_the_Fractured_Ord: 'Hey your plumage looks nicer than mine. Wanna trade?'

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tales_of_the_Ardalan_Inte: While nothing can get Kardel to divulge his means of transit to the Ardalan Nebula, he's more than happy to swap hogwhompers of his adventures there. Keep him in his cups long enough and he might even tell you about the mishap with the princess and the plasma gun.

One talon to hold his victims pinned fast.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Brood_Queen_Set: Many are the knights and noble youths who have intruded on the hunting grounds of the Broodmother, disturbing her peace with the clatter of armor, their boots setting atwitch her silken web. The intruders are like succulent shelled insects upon whose innards she's gorged, all the while growing curious of the adornments that drape their bodies, until that day when a blacksmith found his way into her web.  Armor he promised her, the finest in the land, if only she would set him free. And so a deal was struck, and the blacksmith measured, and toiled, taking as his materials the finest steel to be found among the husked corpses of silk-wrapped knights.  When the new armor was finished, the spider kept her promise and set the blacksmith free.  Then she watched her brood devour him. Contains all of the items in the 'Brood Queen' set for Broodmother:

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Gallows_Understudy_Se:
Far from the temples of the Flayed Twins, Bloodseeker stumbled upon a land that lauded execution above sacrifice, relying on hempen rope and metal blades instead of black stone and the will of bloodthirsty gods. Yet there was something in their crude approach that appealed to him, and so he spent a season studying the executioners, watching from the crowd that turned out for every morbid spectacle, until he realized that the mob itself was the god to whom they made their sacrifices. With a leer that matched those to be seen on the faces of the enrapt audience, he made his way home to share the lessons he had learned with his own bloody masters of the priestly caste. 
	
	Includes all items from the Gallows Understudy Set.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Gallows_Understudy_Sk: Bloodseeker found many uses for the gallows rope he stole from a corpse's distended neck, in order to study this crude means of execution at his leisure.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Magus_Cypher: Most Magi believed the Puzzle of Perplex to be a mere curiosity. Yet generations of wizards had broken themselves trying to solve it. And even after the Grand Magus thought he finally grasped the crux of its secret, the epiphany of true meaning came only much later--that the knowledge at the heart of Perplex might allow him to alter the very foundations of magic itself. Now, no longer limited to masterful mimicry, Rubick toys with the boundaries of arcane artistry, reshaping the world of magic as he sees fit; always hungry for new preternatural mysteries to unravel and respool, and the undiscovered kingdoms of magic they too might reveal.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Mysterious_Vagabond_S: In the final years of the Sordid Era, after thirteen seasons of drought, shamanic ways fell into disrepute, with all itinerant mages blamed for failing crops and disease. In order to continue his travels, Rhasta was forced to adopt a new appearance. While still offering many of the same services, during the end of this Era he disclaimed all knowledge of shamanism and professed only the knowledge that any vagabond might acquire along the road, and practice (in a strictly nonprofessional sense) for a few coins. Thus he survived into the next era, when many another was separated from their hide and stretched out along the roads as a warning to the next shaman who might happen along. Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_One_True_King_Bundle: In an age lost even to his own memory, Ostarion fed his lust for eternal life not with spectral essence, but a nigh-unending harvest of bone. The walls of his palace were formed of fired bone; the streets paved with bones of every sort of creature and every enemy. And those of the flesh who entered this domain took great care, for the King was first and foremost a collector, and nothing moved in the Empire of Bone without summoning the gaze of his unblinking eyes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Order_of_Cyprin: Slithice was barely a cycle into her first deployment with the Guard, and still without thoughts of a command of her own, when she was sent with a Slithereen battalion to aid the Conclave at the Battle of Stonefish Gate. For her valor in the face of gravest threat, and against her protestations otherwise, she would earn the highest honors awarded to one of her kind, gaining acceptance into an ancient order, and setting a course for her rise to preeminence.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Riftshadow_Roamers_Se: Trinkets and tall tales are just a few of the ways a drifter can make a living out in Riftshadow, but there's a lot more in the waste if you know how to look, and where. You'll want a guide and someone who knows their way in a fight, that should let you scratch the surface and take in some history. Getting rich from the ruins though, that's another matter. If you want to learn Riftshadow's darkest secrets, you better tip well and know how to keep your mouth shut. This here bundle includes all of the items in 'The Riftshadow Roamer' set for Meepo:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Roiling_Surge: Contains The Roiling Surge set for Morphling, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Rough_Rider_of_Yama_R: This bundle includes all of the items in the 'Rough Rider of Yama Raskav' set for Batrider:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Rowdy_Firebrand:
\"I'm all for a good riot. But never got on much with looters. They don't like my style. They complain about it, but their screams stop eventually.\"

Contains the The Rowdy Firebrand set for Batrider, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Savage_Orchid: A garnet rod constructed from the essence of a fire demon.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Second_Disciple: Includes all of the items in the 'Second Disciple' set for Bounty Hunter:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Second_Disciples_Bast: Sometimes a bounty does not need to be collected immediately if the hunter believes there is more to gain on a job. Gondar enlists in the army of the infidel in order to obtain sturdy gear and learn the stolen secrets of Soruq that have been bestowed upon the undeserving army.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Second_Disciples_Blad: This blade, fashioned of salvaged equipment from the battlefield, serves as a reminder to both Gondar and his enemies of what happens to those who betray sacred trusts.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Second_Disciples_Chak: Carried upon his back, this weapon serves as both defense and offense on the field of battle.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Second_Disciples_Dagg: Stolen from the betrayer himself, Gondar used this weapon to slit the throat of the deceitful war general and seal the fate of the army founded on infidelity.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Second_Disciples_Satc: Gondar carries his important materials and implements in his satchel, always prepared for future hunts.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Second_Disciples_Veil: With the power imbued in the veil of the second disciple, Gondar learned a rare and useful technique passed down from his old master. With the sigil of the enchanted blade, the hunter can feel a great power that was nearly lost to the filthy traitor.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Seers_Command_Set: Includes all of the items in 'The Seers Command' set for Dark Seer:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Serakund_Tyrant: Includes all of the items in the 'Serakund Tyrant' set for Lich plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Sharpshooter_Set: As a craftsman is no better than his tools, a traveler is no better than the kit he carries on his back.  With this gear, Sniper treks through dangerous territory, confident in his ability to get the job done.  Contains all of the items in the 'Sharpshooter' set for Sniper:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Sharpshooters_Bullet_: Why carry your bullets in a bag when you can slot them into your bracers for quick reloading?
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Sharpshooters_Cloak: A cloak is every traveler's friend.  A warm covering for the cold, and it confuses the silhouette, making the wearer a more difficult target at long range.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Sharpshooters_Pauldro: These shoulder pads provide protection against both the enemy, and the occasional bruised shoulder of the long-distance shootist.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Sharpshooters_Stache: The Keen Folk are, for the most part, a finely mustachioed people, and Sniper is no exception.  It took him nearly three days to grow out this stache.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Shattered_Blade_of_Le: The Duke of Levinthal, Elector of the Gleaming City, withstood Ostarion's besieging undead legions for many days before sallying forth to face the Immortal King in personal combat. This broken blade is the sole legacy of that ill-fated act of defiance.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Shell_Slicer: Even those who huddle inside their tight-shut shells cannot consider themselves safe from Slark.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Silent_Ripper: Perfect for sliding through the bars of a cell, for a silent shiv in the dark. Just don't ask where he hides it.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Silver_Fox: Contains The Silver Fox set for Sniper.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Skeleton_Key: It used to open some ancient triumphal arch, but the structure was damaged during excavation.  Using explosives probably didn't help.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Skeleton_Key_Bandana: Once in a while you find bandits living in the ruins.  Once in a while they forget things while they're being evicted.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Slithereen_Exile_Set: No Slithereen may fail. Though Slithice swam victorious at the battle of Crey, a single jeweled chalice was taken. The punishment for the lost bauble: banishment. So she wandered the deeps, bitterly searching for the chalice, and where once dwelt honor and humility now crept the tendrils of cruelty and malice. If she was to be exiled, then so be it. She shed the lighter tones of her ancestral armor, instead taking up darker armaments, and all who looked upon her felt the indomitable will of the exiled siren. This bundle contains all of the items in 'The Slithereen Exile' set for Naga Siren:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Slithereen_Knight: This bundle contains all the items in the 'Slithereen Knight' set for Naga Siren:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Soul_Reaper: The plagued dying threw themselves at Rotund'jere, offering their very souls for deliverance.  He was only too happy to accept.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Spellbinders_Shape_Se: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Spellbinder's Shape' set for Rubick:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Spiritual_Spirits: Among the Brewmasters of Oyo diligent drunkenness is the only path to enlightenment.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Spoils_of_Dezun: Few in the Order of Dezun know the true source of the ingredients used to attempt a journey into the Nothl realm. Yet, after his resurrection to the lands of the living, Huskar possessed secrets of a kind none of the elders could begin to account for -- secrets he was determined to employ towards his own ends.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Steadfast_Voyager: Includes all of the items in the 'Steadfast Voyager' set for Kunkka:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Stinger: This one is gonna sting a little.  Oh, yes.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Stoneshard_Majesty_Se: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Stoneshard Majesty' set for Earthshaker:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Storm_Riders_Bracer: This armor comes from an age long forgotten, and it crackles with the ancient power of the stormrider.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Storm_Riders_Deflecto: Found in an ancient temple in Druud, this armor turns away blades and spells.  Storms are not so easily deflected.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Storm_Riders_Sight: An eye for an eye, and a storm for his enemies; no foe can escape the piercing glare of the storm rider.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Stormcrows_Spirit_Set:
In hushed tones, legends have long been whispered of the near-mythical stormcrows.
	
	Enormous, powerful and reclusive, these strange, scarce birds range across the highest peaks of the Prefect mountains, hidden from the world by a constant bank of dark cloud. Their rare sighting are considered ill omens, said to portend of storms soon to follow.
	
	Legends also tell of those few who have dared face the dangerous trials required to harness the power of these creatures for themselves. 
	
	For the only way to return after stealing the egg of a stormcrow - a potent source of power - is to wrestle control of one of the enormous black birds and ride it down to the ground, miles below.  Includes all of the items in 'The Stormcrow's Spirit' set for Witch Doctor:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Stumpgrinder: Contains all items from the The Stumpgrinder set, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Subtle_Demons_Blades:
One must use care in the handling of such a blade, for it will cut the wielder as well as surely as the rival.
	
	This bundle contains both of the Subtle Demon's Blades for Riki:
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Summit: The Summit is a global Dota 2 event! Top teams from Europe, America, & Asia will fight to qualify via online play. The best four teams will fly to LA to challenge invited teams Na'Vi & DK on LAN for a base prize pool of $80,000! Each ticket purchased increases the prize pool by $2.50! Bundle includes the DotaTV ticket, Harbinger of War Axe set, and loading screen!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Summit_2: The Summit 2 is the long-awaited sequel to a global Dota 2 event! The world's best teams will fight online for 4 slots at the LAN Finals this December, where they will challenge Evil Geniuses and another invited team for $100,000+. 25% of each bundle sold goes towards the prize pool and the bundle includes Compendium access, a courier, loading screen, and DotaTV ticket!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Summit_2_Ticket: The Summit 2 is the long-awaited sequel to a global Dota 2 event! The world's best teams will fight online for 4 slots at the LAN Finals this December, where they will challenge Evil Geniuses and another invited team for $100,000+. This ticket only gives you access to view games from The Summit 2.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Swine_of_the_Sunken_G: After months of work, Techies Demolitions proudly unveiled their latest commission: The Swine, the most powerful cannon ever designed. Yet during its first frantic use aboard a homebound galley, the Swine's awesome blast tore its host ship asunder, rocketing the cannon itself backwards toward the shore. It was found days later, deeply embedded in a rocky cliffside just below its makers' workshop.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Timekeeper:
\"Swift, agile, silent and fast, Templar Assassin fits my favorite style of play in DOTA2.\" -JJ LIN
	
	The Timekeeper TA set draws inspiration from JJ Lin's Timeline World Tour. In the world where man chimes the hour, our days are precious precisely because they are limited. From music to gaming, he weaves his role of The Timekeeper into the Templar Assassin. The package is designed such that it comes in gold or silver lining, with JJ and SMG logo on each side of the shoulders. The Templar Assassin's characteristic colour is purple, which happens to be a special color for JJ as well.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Timekeeper_Music_Pack: Composed, scored and produced by JJ  Lin and JFJ Productions.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Toy_Butcher: Feared most amongst the fluff-stuffed denizens of the toybox, The Toy Butcher stalks the corners and shadows of the bin, always on the hunt for his next kill. Every toy knows that once the butcher gets his hook in you, your stuffing and your life are forfeit--like as not to be left strewn about the lanes as the plushy monster jaunts happily away from your lonely, ragged remains.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_The_Twin_Blades_of_Aureli: Forged in the gilded smithery beneath the forgotten city, the Eternal Radiance Blades are a lost civilization's greatest achievement in alchemical transmutation.  No longer steel, but not quite gold, the twin blades are something rarer and stronger than both.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Thorned_Skitterers_of_Des: Even outside the Thorny Wastes, Broodmother affects the look--as much because it appeals to her eyes as for its defensive properties.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_ThreeFold_Mien_of_the_Boa: The aspect of the boar brings health, virility, and alacrity. The primal sign of four-seven-twelve.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_ThriceGemmed_Barding_of_S: Three times your steed has saved your life.  Three times you have graced its barding with a gem.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Throe: There is no home for the wandering Throe. Apparent in some fierce battles, but hidden from others, his myth is both his curse and inconsistency brought to the battlefield. Once believed to be led by demons unknown, only fear now leads this wandering stag through the plains of war.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Throes_of_Anguish_Set: This bundle contains all of the items in the 'Throes of Anguish' set for Queen of Pain:

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Thursday_Evening_Cup_Seri: The Thursday Evening Cup Series is a new semipro tournament series based on SECS, the longest running DotA tournament series to date. TECS provides an open competitive platform for North and South American teams to gain real tournament experience.

The Thursday Evening Cup Series returns for its second season! This semi-pro tournament series is for North and South American teams. Every week there is a best-of-1 single elimination bracket, $100 winner-take-all.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Thyrsus_of_the_Inauspicio: On the world at the rim grow a species of crystalline tree in whose branches visions of the future are tangled. From such a tree, Outworld Devourer fashioned this staff.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tiara_of_Enduring_Torment: To give riches is torture.  To take riches is bliss.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tica_Legends_League_Seaso: 24 costaricans teams will compete for a prize fund of over $600 and sponsors products, in 3 different divisions
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tickled_Tegu: A friendly Tegu from the dragon infested Cathauran Wastes. He smiles as if he knows something you do not.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tidal_Blade: Within this blade, runs the true essence of the earth and sea.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tidehunter_Blink_Dagger: Accurate or not, an untrustworthy anemone convinced Tidehunter that his blink dagger would have extra blinking power with this optional organic power-pack.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tigress_of_the_Dark_Moon_: The Dark Moon faithful consist of former scholars, laborers, orphans, and thieves. One may have served as magistrate of a city, another spilled blood as a warlord in the wilds. They have walked all imaginable paths to find Selemene. In her service, the trials and tragedies of the past matter not. They worship the Goddess together, guardians of the Nightsilver Woods.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_TimeMace_of_the_Acolyte_o: One may be merely an acolyte, and yet have mastery of all the infinities of Clasz. For full knowledge of Claszureme, more dedication to dimensional defense is required.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tines_of_Tybara: One of Gondar's first mentors, Tybara was the master of the single-strike execution. Surprisingly, she was also the hunter of choice for those who wanted unruly targets returned alive, give or take a few working parts.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tinkbot: Fed up with conventional delivery methods, Tinker set to work on something he felt was a bit more reliable.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tiny_Majesty_Of_The_Colos: In ages past, long before the settlements in the Azuran region were abandoned to ruin, the Odobenus forebearers harnessed the powers of rock, root, and iron to create fearsome guardians to watch over the tombs of their fallen legions even after the memories of their deeds had passed from the world. Little did they know the raw stone materials they'd utilized in one such creation also contained a powerful life force of its own, one not content to sit idly waiting for the threats of the outlands to arrive--one who would venture forth to stand watch over all lands in need of protection.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Top_Hat_of_the_Occultists: Mundane prey attracts the uninspired predator. A distinguished huntsman, on the other hand, seeks a prize not bound by earthly coils.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Torment_Unbound: Her hair down, your queen is relaxed in her work.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Torment_of_the_Chainbreak:
The cruelties devised by the nobles of Devarque and their progeny remained novel long after N'aix's mind could no longer fathom the meaning of punishment.

Contains the Torment of the Chainbreaker set for Lifestealer, including the Loading Screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tormenta:
A true maestro knows victory without artistry is no victory at all.

Contains the Corridan Maestro set for Storm Spirit, including the Loading Screen.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tormented_Staff_of_Eminen: The first weapon ever wielded by the Tormented Soul's previously-empty hands, the Tormented Staff not only changed the animation of Leshrac's Split Earth ability, but also introduced completely new animations for attacking, spawning, teleport completion, and death.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Torn_Guard_of_the_Vandal: Tired of your clavicle being exposed to the world?  Here is an enchanted armor designed to shield old bones from plight of combat.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Torneio_FaAC_de_Dota_2: 16 teams will compete for a prize pool of R$ 320,00.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Torneo_GPG_Ica_Gamer: The top 16 teams in the Region of Ica - Peru, competing for a grand prize
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Torneo_Tecnobar_De_Dota_2: The Giant Rocket League pits 8 teams against each other to compete at a LAN Final at TecnoBar!

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Torneos_Dota_Latino_Seaso: The first season of the Torneos Dota Latino league puts 32 teams competing in an online tournament to be crowned champions.
64 teams from South America will compete in the second season of the TDL for a prize pool of $450!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Torresmo_Legacy_League: The Torresmo Legacy League gives amateur teams in Brazil an opportunity to play for a $900 monthly prize pool!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Torresmo_Legacy_League_2n: Th second season of the Torresmo Legacy League gives amateur teams in Brazil an opportunity to play for a prize pool!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Torso_of_Axe_Unleashed: Lost, alone, and without his precious namesake in a strange land... Axe is exactly where he wants to be!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tory_the_Sky_Guardian:
It's been told that Tory, the Sky Guardian, has been riding the winds since the beginning of time, serving the ancient tribes faithfully as a proficient messenger. 
	Everlasting glory shall be provided to those who are chosen by Tory as allies, as the winds seem to open a path for him while he gracefully flies towards his destination. 
	A skilled companion who can fly above the highest mountain and glide over the bloodiest battlefield, Tory can surpass every flying being in every way possible.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tourr_Captains_Draft_Leag: Watch 32 teams in their battle to win the title of the most versatile team, and a prizepool of $25.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Trapjaw_the_Boxhound: Within the dungeons of the Severed Keep there sits a treasure hoard long abandoned. Many are the raiders who have set their sights on its wonders, yet only one has ever returned, telling grisly tales of a family of enchanted chests brimming with gold, devouring his friends.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tribal_Terror: Contains all of the items in the 'Tribal Terror' set for Bloodseeker plus loading screen.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tribal_Totem_Mask: Not all of the Witch Doctor's enslaved spirits are ancestors. This household totem contains the trapped soul of a swamp dwelling Yando beast.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tribute_Upgrade_Infuser__: This consumable item unlocks ambient particle effects on the following items available through Fall Season 2015 Compendium Treasures: Leshrac's Spirethorn, Lina's Dress of the Bewitching Flame, Spectre's Crest and Edge of the Flowering Shade, Tusk's Cannon Punch of the Barrier Rogue, Tidehunter's Aquemerald Blade, Ursa's Claws of the Ferocious Heart, Drow's Algid Legacy, Phantom Assassin's Armor of the Fearful Aria, Shadow Shaman's Shade of the Spiteful Eye, Magnus's Slab of Erupting Wrath, Vengeful Spirit's Blade of Flightless Fury, and Batrider's Queen of the Jack Bomber
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tribute_of_the_Piercing_B: Each set within this treasure contains at least one item that can be transformed to include ambient particles by using a Tribute Upgrade Infuser - Fall Season 2015.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tribute_of_the_Sharpened_: Each set within this treasure contains at least one item that can be transformed to include ambient particles by using a Tribute Upgrade Infuser - Fall Season 2015.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Tricorne_of_the_Drowned: A well crafted tricorne edged in gold.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Trident_of_the_Deep_One: Once the temple's caryatids looked out upon a mountain fastness, but those lofty peaks have long since slumped beneath the waves. No one remembers who carved those guardian figures, or even what that nation called itself. And the statue merely scowled a little when Slardar slipped the ancient trident free of its barnacle-encrusted paws.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Trident_of_the_Sea_Stalke: A trident cursed by a host of sea gods and sealed within in the depths of the Coral Breach for thousands of years.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Trine_Announcer_Pack: This pack replaces the Default announcer and Mega-Kills announcer with the soothing tones of Trine's tale-weaving narrator.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_TriniDota_2_League: The top teams of Trinidad and Tobago compete to be crowned champions!
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Triumph: Many will fight.  Few will achieve immortality.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Triumph_of_the_Four_Corne: Contains the Triumph of the Four Corners set for Brewmaster, including the Loading Screen
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Troll_Warlords_Default_Me: Troll Warlord's Default Melee Off-Hand Weapon
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Trove_Carafe: No seal or key is needed to open this treasure, as it is already unlocked. This treasure contains individual items.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_WESG:
World Electronic Sports Games (WESG)
	On March 30, 2016, we Alisports announced our original e-sports tournament World Electronic Sports Games (WESG) which feature a total prize pool of US$5.5 million across all disciplines. We have announced four disciplines so far: 
	
	DotA2  US$ 1,500,000
	Counter Strike: Global Offensive  US$ 1,500,000
	Starcraft II  US$ 400,000
	Hearthstone  US$ 300,000
	
	WESG will cover almost all of the continents in the world and involve more than 120 countries. The Chinese online qualifiers will start from May 14 to August. Chinese LAN final will be held in October. The overseas online qualifiers will start from August to November. Global LAN final will be held in December.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Winter_Snowdrop: It is little known of Crystal Maiden, that in her long study of the Frozen Arts, she once greatly displeased her Ice Wizard master and to restore herself to his graces and prove worthy of his instruction, she passed a year dwelling in the climes of slush where the Blueheart Glacier spends itself at the edge of the Boiling Sea. Here, where snow had never fallen, Rylai spent months in deep meditation, mastering her powers, before waking one afternoon with a single frigid word upon her lips: 'Snowdrop!' For a moment, the steam that filled the air turned to ice, and the warm precipitation became a softly falling snow. When she returned to her old teacher, she found him waiting with a smile, fully aware of the magic she had wrought, as he presented her this outfit to show her worth and mastery.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Winter_Solstice_Fashion: Furred in the down of glacial tusk-foxes, this scarf will keep you warm and looking good in the coldest of snowstorms.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Winter_Wars_2015__DSP: This tournament is open registration, and any team can sign up for free at Legionbattles.com to compete for $1200. This bundle grants access to the Argent Spear Skywrath Mage weapon and access to view games from Winter Wars 2015.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Wraithbinder: Though unable to cross over of their own will, some types of wraith love nothing more than to consume the energies of the mortal plane. Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_WyrmGuard_of_Uldorak: Dowager Queen Tansis XII called upon a brave dragon slayer to ambush Uldorak upon her son's crowning day. Expecting no plots from the cowed people of Candoness, Uldorak was caught by surprise and slain.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Wyrm_Bracer_of_Uldorak: The Kings of Candoness suffered under the tyranny of the Time-Dragon Uldorak for many generations. For with each passing of the Candonite Crown, the dragon would appear demanding tribute in gold and magic trinkets.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Wyrm_Helm_of_Uldorak: Many years before his fateful encounter with the Eldwurm, the Dragon Knight battled with and slew the Time-Dragon Uldorak. The much relieved and newly crowned King Tansis XIII ordered this helm forged as a gift and reward.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Wyrm_Pauldron_of_Uldorak: Upon this pauldron the crest horns of the Time-Dragon Uldorak are mounted.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Yasha_the_Quickblade: Yasha, one of two legendary moonblades, is said to take on a form that best matches its owner's chosen martial art. In the hands of Riki this weapon takes the blade of a small, well balanced dagger.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_YoDota_Championship_Seaso: 32 teams from South America compete to earn one of eight qualifying spots in the second season of the YoDota Championship. Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Yonexs_Rage: In the blood-mists of the fiercest of battles, the dragon finds its true calling... the call of Invictus Gaming.
