Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_Yulsarias_Mantle:
In an age now lost to time, the Frozen Witch Yulsaria ruled the whitelands, summoning blizzards and hail storms upon those who displeased her, while an army of ice golems roamed the lands to snuff out all warmth. In time, her southward expansion angered the Eldwurm Slyrak who, in his terrible rage, melted Yulsaria's armies with his endless flame before conquering the Frozen Witch herself. Now, centuries later, shifts in the ice have uncovered yet another shard of her empire: her frosty mantle.

Immortal items cannot be traded or marketed through The International 2018, but can still be gifted once.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_sven_ti10_immortal_head: Though he spurns their company and their cause, a small band of Vigil-in-exile have sworn allegiance to Sven -- their \"Rogue Commander\" -- and seek to use what little influence they still possess to return to the Vigil Keep and take control of the remnants of the waning order.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_ti8_bristleback_armor: And here Rigwarl thought \"Crystalback\" had a nice ring to it...
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_ti8_bristleback_head: And here Rigwarl thought \"Crystalback\" had a nice ring to it...
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_treant_ti7_immortal: On less robust trees, the creeping vines of a stuntwood sproutling would signal a slow, starving death. The fae folk consider the vines and their issue as invasive species to be killed on sight. For Treant Protector, however, the sproutlings are a bit of harmless company whose vines offer a patch of thorny armor on his flanks.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_troll_ti10_immortal_shoul: Given his abiding distaste for negotiations, barter, and population centers in general, Jah'rakal must display rare restraint with his axework when he decides to acquire something nice.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_undying_fall20_immortal_t: Though the Dirge itself makes the Dead God's will known to his followers, there are times when a more direct means of communication with the world of the living is called for, when an emissary is chosen from amongst the many to bear the transformation and come to speak for the lord of horror.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_viper_immortal_head_ti7: Though he spurned most of the magics practiced by his naive captor, the inquisitive Netherdrake did take interest in his master's success in the realm of augmentations.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_warrior_of_the_steppe_arm: In parade to and from the arena of Omexe, no other fighter dares ride close to the Warrunner.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_warrior_of_the_steppe_bac: No centaur shall ever wear a saddle, but a caparison such as this one is looked upon with high regard--provided one has earned it.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_warrior_of_the_steppe_bel: Not the fabled plate of Omexe, but the next best thing.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_warrior_of_the_steppe_hel: Near the height of his climb through the ranks of the arena, Bradwarden donned this helm, and could be recognized by cheering crowds when the first tip of horn appeared from the arena gates.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_warrior_of_the_steppe_tai: In the arenas of Omexe, it would not do to offer an opponent much of a grip.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_wavecutter: This fin will slice the water like its owner's blade will slice your throat.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_wd_ti10_immortal_weapon: As Awaleb's destructive powers grew, so too did the influence of his healing touch. Indeed, one only need look for the flourishing lands and overgrown fauna to follow the path of his great atrocities.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_wd_ti8_immortal_bonkers: Though the origins of Zharvakko's brand of arcanism are somewhat murky, and largely apocryphal, the exploits of the influential healer Awaleb are known far and wide. In an age of famine, disease, and unending violence, Awaleb concluded that the ailments of his people amounted to mere symptoms of a much greater sickness. So he began to turn his legendary cauldron towards the dark arts of harm. His people could always trust his word and prescriptions, but his greater act of service to them was a willing corruption of sacred vows in the name of protection, and the twisted legacy he would leave behind.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_wk_ti8_weapon: Though the lifespans of Ostarion's subjects are not eternal, the forever king's dark magic ensures their loyalties will be.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_Desc_zeus_2021_immortal_gold: Though his powers may not be what they once were -- a temporary issue of course -- the god of thunder isn't keen to let his position in the pantheon slip so easily away.

Tokens.DOTA_Item_League_GEST_Desc: The Gigabyte E-Sports Tournament is sponsored by Gigabyte and hosted by DotaTalk. The winners of six qualifiers from South-East Asia will face off against veteran teams for a cash prize of $1,500 and the chance to compete against two of the best Chinese teams, IG and LGD, for another $1500.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_League_PremierLeague_Desc: Fueled by joint forces of TwitchTV and SteelSeries, Season 3 is the newest edition of The Premier League. Watch 10 of the best teams from both Europe and North America contend for $6,000 with 5 intense matches every week for 9 weeks. Commentary by TriumphOfMan.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_League_RaidCall_Desc: The RaidCall Dota 2 League is a $10,000 online Dota 2 tournament series featuring the top Dota 2 teams from around the globe. Broadcast four days a week for over eight weeks, the D2L (as it's commonly called) is commentated live by Ayesee and invited guests.
Tokens.DOTA_Item_League_StarLadderS2: Star Series Season II Lan Final
Tokens.DOTA_Item_League_StarSeries3_Desc: StarLadder's Star Series is one of the most prestigious Dota 2 leagues, powered by Intel & Asus and casted by v1lat and TobiWan. The keystone of Star Series is the LAN final, held in Kiev CyberSport Arena, Ukraine. Watch the best Dota 2 teams compete for $15,000 and the title Star Series Champion.
